\ldblquote\i I\lang3081\i0\rquote\lang1033\i ve just been attacked by dementors and I might be expelled from Hogwarts. I want to know what\rquote s going on and when I\rquote m going to get out of here.\i0\par
Harry copied these words onto three separate pieces of parchment the moment he reached the desk in his dark bedroom. He addressed the first to Sirius, the second to Ron, and the third to Hermione. His owl, Hedwig, was off hunting; her cage stood empty on the desk. Harry paced the bedroom waiting for her to come back, his head pounding, his brain too busy for sleep even though his eyes stung and itched with tiredness. His back ached from carrying Dudley home, and the two lumps on his head where the window and Dudley had hit him were throbbing painfully.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Up and down he paced, consumed with anger and frustration, grinding his teeth and clenching his fists, casting angry looks out at the empty, star-strewn sky every time he passed the window. Demen\-tors sent to get him, Mrs. Figg and Mundungus Fletcher tailing him in secret, then suspension from Hogwarts and a hearing at the Min\-istry of Magic \emdash  and \i still\i0  no one was telling him what was going on.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And what, \i what,\i0  had that Howler been about? Whose voice had echoed so horribly, so menacingly, through the kitchen?\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Why was he still trapped here without information? Why was everyone treating him like some naughty kid? \i Don\rquote t do any more magic, stay in the house. \'85\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033 He kicked his school trunk as he passed it, but far from relieving his anger he felt worse, as he now had a sharp pain in his toe to deal with in addition to the pain in the rest of his body.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Just as he limped past the window, Hedwig soared through it with a soft rustle of wings like a small ghost.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote About time!\rdblquote  Harry snarled, as she landed lightly on top of her cage. \ldblquote You can put that down, I\rquote ve got work for you!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hedwig\rquote s large round amber eyes gazed reproachfully at him over the dead frog clamped in her beak.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Come here,\rdblquote  said Harry, picking up the three small rolls of parch\-ment and a leather thong and tying the scrolls to her scaly leg. \ldblquote Take these straight to Sirius, Ron, and Hermione and don\rquote t come back here without good long replies. Keep pecking them till they\rquote ve written decent-length answers if you\rquote ve got to. Understand?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hedwig gave a muffled hooting noise, beak still full of frog.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Get going, then,\rdblquote  said Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She took off immediately. The moment she\rquote d gone, Harry threw himself down onto his bed without undressing and stared at the dark ceiling. In addition to every other miserable feeling, he now felt guilty that he\rquote d been irritable with Hedwig; she was the only friend he had at number four, Privet Drive. But he\rquote d make it up to her when she came back with Sirius\rquote s, Ron\rquote s, and Hermione\rquote s answers.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They were bound to write back quickly; they couldn\rquote t possibly ig\-nore a dementor attack. He\rquote d probably wake up tomorrow to three fat letters full of sympathy and plans for his immediate removal to the Burrow. And with that comforting idea, sleep rolled over him, stifling all further thought.\lang3081\par
