\lang1033\ldblquote Ron and Hermione will explain everything, dear, I\rquote ve really got to dash,\rdblquote  Mrs. Weasley whispered distractedly. \ldblquote There\rdblquote  \emdash  they had reached the second landing \emdash  \ldblquote you\rquote re the door on the right. I\rquote ll call you when it\rquote s over.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And she hurried off downstairs again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry crossed the dingy landing, turned the bedroom doorknob, which was shaped like a serpent\rquote s head, and opened the door.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He caught a brief glimpse of a gloomy high-ceilinged, twin-bedded room, then there was a loud twittering noise, followed by an even louder shriek, and his vision was completely obscured by a large quan\-tity of very bushy hair \emdash  Hermione had thrown herself onto him in a hug that nearly knocked him flat, while Ron\rquote s tiny owl, Pigwidgeon, zoomed excitedly round and round their heads.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote HARRY! Ron, he\rquote s here, Harry\rquote s here! We didn\rquote t hear you arrive! Oh, how \i are\i0  you? Are you all right? Have you been furious with us? I bet you have, I know our letters were useless \emdash  but we couldn\rquote t tell you anything, Dumbledore made us swear we wouldn\rquote t, oh, we\rquote ve got so much to tell you, and you\rquote ve got to tell us \emdash  the dementors! When we heard \emdash  and that Ministry hearing \emdash  it\rquote s just outrageous, I\rquote ve looked it all up, they can\rquote t expel you, they just can\rquote t, there\rquote s provision in the Decree for the Restriction of Underage Sorcery for the use of magic in life-threatening situations \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Let him breathe, Hermione,\rdblquote  said Ron, grinning, closing the door behind Harry. He seemed to have grown several more inches during their month apart, making him taller and more gangly looking than ever, though the long nose, bright red hair, and freckles were the same.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione, still beaming, let go of Harry, but before she could say another word there was a soft whooshing sound and something white soared from the top of a dark wardrobe and landed gently on Harry\rquote s shoulder.\lang3081\par
