\lang1033 Ron had not asked Dumbledore to give him the prefect badge. This was not Ron\rquote s fault. Was he, Harry, Ron\rquote s best friend in the world, going to sulk because he didn\rquote t have a badge, laugh with the twins behind Ron\rquote s back, ruin this for Ron when, for the first time, he had beaten Harry at something?\lang3081\par
\lang1033 At this point Harry heard Ron\rquote s footsteps on the stairs again. He stood up, straightened his glasses, and hitched a grin onto his face as Ron bounded back through the door.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Just caught her!\rdblquote  he said happily. \ldblquote She says she\rquote ll get the Clean\-sweep if she can.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
