\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah,\rdblquote  said Ron, \ldblquote yeah, I suppose. \'85 Well, we\rquote d better get our trunks packed, hadn\rquote t we?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 It was odd how widely their possessions seemed to have scattered themselves since they had arrived. It took them most of the afternoon to retrieve their books and belongings from all over the house and stow them back inside their school trunks. Harry noticed that Ron kept moving his prefect\rquote s badge around, first placing it on his bedside table, then putting it into his jeans pocket, then taking it out and lay\-ing it on his folded robes, as though to see the effect of the red on the black. Only when Fred and George dropped in and offered to attach it to his forehead with a Permanent Sticking Charm did he wrap it tenderly in his maroon socks and lock it in his trunk.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Mrs. Weasley returned from Diagon Alley around six o\rquote clock, laden with books and carrying a long package wrapped in thick brown pa\-per that Ron took from her with a moan of longing.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Never mind unwrapping it now, people are arriving for dinner, I want you all downstairs,\rdblquote  she said, but the moment she was out of sight Ron ripped off the paper in a frenzy and examined every inch of his new broom, an ecstatic expression on his face.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Down in the basement Mrs. Weasley had hung a scarlet banner over the heavily laden dinner table, which read CONGRATULATIONS RON AND HERMIONE \emdash  NEW PREFECTS. She looked in a better mood than Harry had seen her all holiday.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I thought we\rquote d have a little party, not a sit-down dinner,\rdblquote  she told Harry, Ron, Hermione, Fred, George, and Ginny as they entered the room. \ldblquote Your father and Bill are on their way, Ron, I\rquote ve sent them both owls and they\rquote re \i thrilled,\i0\rdblquote  she added, beaming.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Fred rolled his eyes.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Sirius, Lupin, Tonks, and Kingsley Shacklebolt were already there and Mad-Eye Moody stumped in shortly after Harry had got himself a butterbeer.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, Alastor, I am glad you\rquote re here,\rdblquote  said Mrs. Weasley brightly, as\lang3081  \lang1033 Mad-Eye shrugged off his traveling cloak. \ldblquote We\rquote ve been wanting to ask you for ages \emdash  could you have a look in the writing desk in the draw\-ing room and tell us what\rquote s inside it? We haven\rquote t wanted to open it just in case it\rquote s something really nasty.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No problem, Molly \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Moody\rquote s electric-blue eye swiveled upward and stared fixedly through the ceiling of the kitchen.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Drawing room \'85\rdblquote  he growled, as the pupil contracted. \ldblquote Desk in the corner? Yeah, I see it. \'85 Yeah, it\rquote s a boggart. \'85 Want me to go up and get rid of it, Molly?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No, no, I\rquote ll do it myself later,\rdblquote  beamed Mrs. Weasley. \ldblquote You have your drink. We\rquote re having a little bit of a celebration, actually. \'85\rdblquote  She gestured at the scarlet banner. \ldblquote Fourth prefect in the family!\rdblquote  she said fondly, ruffling Ron\rquote s hair.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Prefect, eh?\rdblquote  growled Moody, his normal eye on Ron and his mag\-ical eye swiveling around to gaze into the side of his head. Harry had the very uncomfortable feeling it was looking at him and moved away toward Sirius and Lupin.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, congratulations,\rdblquote  said Moody, still glaring at Ron with his normal eye, \ldblquote authority figures always attract trouble, but I suppose Dumbledore thinks you can withstand most major jinxes or he wouldn\rquote t have appointed you. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron looked rather startled at this view of the matter but was saved the trouble of responding by the arrival of his father and eldest brother. Mrs. Weasley was in such a good mood she did not even complain that they had brought Mundungus with them too; he was wearing a long overcoat that seemed oddly lumpy in unlikely places and declined the offer to remove it and put it with Moody\rquote s traveling cloak.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, I think a toast is in order,\rdblquote  said Mr. Weasley, when everyone had a drink. He raised his goblet. \ldblquote To Ron and Hermione, the new Gryffindor prefects!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron and Hermione beamed as everyone drank to them and then applauded.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I was never a prefect myself,\rdblquote  said Tonks brightly from behind Harry as everybody moved toward the table to help themselves to food. Her hair was tomato-red and waist length today; she looked like Ginny\rquote s older sister. \ldblquote My Head of House said I lacked certain neces\-sary qualities.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
