\lang1033\ldblquote Cheers, Harry!\rdblquote  said Fred delightedly, when Mundungus had emptied his pockets into the twins\rquote  outstretched hands and scuttled off toward the food. \ldblquote We\rquote d better get these upstairs. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry watched them go, feeling slightly uneasy. It had just oc\-curred to him that Mr. and Mrs. Weasley would want to know how Fred and George were financing their joke shop business when, as was inevitable, they finally found out about it. Giving the twins his Tri-wizard winnings had seemed a simple thing to do at the time, but what if it led to another family row and a Percy-like estrangement? Would Mrs. Weasley still feel that Harry was as good as her son if she found out he had made it possible for Fred and George to start a ca\-reer she thought quite unsuitable?\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Standing where the twins had left him with nothing but a guilty weight in the pit of his stomach for company, Harry caught the sound of his own name. Kingsley Shacklebolt\rquote s deep voice was audible even over the surrounding chatter.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\'85 why Dumbledore didn\rquote t make Potter a prefect?\rdblquote  said Kingsley.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He\rquote ll have had his reasons,\rdblquote  replied Lupin.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But it would\rquote ve shown confidence in him. It\rquote s what I\rquote d\rquote ve done,\rdblquote  persisted Kingsley, \ldblquote  \rquote specially with the \i Daily Prophet\i0  having a go at him every few days. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry did not look around; he did not want Lupin or Kingsley to know he had heard. He followed Mundungus back toward the table, though not remotely hungry. His pleasure in the party had evaporated as quickly as it had come; he wished he were upstairs in bed.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Mad-Eye Moody was sniffing at a chicken leg with what remained of his nose; evidently he could not detect any trace of poison, because he then tore a strip off it with his teeth.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\'85 the handle\rquote s made of Spanish oak with anti-jinx varnish and in-built vibration control \emdash\rdblquote  Ron was saying to Tonks.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Mrs. Weasley yawned widely.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, I think I\rquote ll sort out that boggart before I turn in. \'85 Arthur, I don\rquote t want this lot up too late, all right? \rquote Night, Harry, dear.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She left the kitchen. Harry set down his plate and wondered whether he could follow her without attracting attention.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You all right, Potter?\rdblquote  grunted Moody.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, fine,\rdblquote  lied Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Moody took a swig from his hip flask, his electric blue eye staring sideways at Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Come here, I\rquote ve got something that might interest you,\rdblquote  he said.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 From an inner pocket of his robes Moody pulled a very tattered old Wizarding photograph.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Original Order of the Phoenix,\rdblquote  growled Moody. \ldblquote Found it last night when I was looking for my spare Invisibility Cloak, seeing as Podmore hasn\rquote t had the manners to return my best one. \'85 Thought people might like to see it.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry took the photograph. A small crowd of people, some waving at him, others lifting their glasses, looked back up at him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote There\rquote s me,\rdblquote  said Moody unnecessarily, pointing at himself. The Moody in the picture was unmistakable, though his hair was slightly less gray and his nose was intact. \ldblquote And there\rquote s Dumbledore beside me, Dedalus Diggle on the other side \'85 That\rquote s Marlene McKinnon, she was killed two weeks after this was taken, they got her whole family. That\rquote s Frank and Alice Longbottom \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry\rquote s stomach, already uncomfortable, clenched as he looked at Alice Longbottom; he knew her round, friendly face very well, even though he had never met her, because she was the image of her son, Neville.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Poor devils,\rdblquote  growled Moody. \ldblquote Better dead than what happened\lang3081  \lang1033 to them \'85 and that\rquote s Emmeline Vance, you\rquote ve met her, and that there\rquote s Lupin, obviously \'85 Benjy Fenwick, he copped it too, we only ever found bits of him \'85 shift aside there,\rdblquote  he added, poking the pic\-ture, and the little photographic people edged sideways, so that those who were partially obscured could move to the front.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote That\rquote s Edgar Bones \'85 brother of Amelia Bones, they got him and his family too, he was a great wizard \'85 Sturgis Podmore, blimey, he looks young \'85 Caradoc Dearborn, vanished six months after this, we never found his body \'85 Hagrid, of course, looks exactly the same as ever \'85 Elphias Doge, you\rquote ve met him, I\rquote d forgotten he used to wear that stupid hat\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 Gideon Prewett, it took five Death Eaters to kill him and his brother Fabian, they fought like heroes \'85 budge along, budge along \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The little people in the photograph jostled among themselves, and those hidden right at the back appeared at the forefront of the picture.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote That\rquote s Dumbledore\rquote s brother, Aberforth, only time I ever met him, strange bloke \'85 That\rquote s Dorcas Meadowes, Voldemort killed her per\-sonally \'85 Sirius, when he still had short hair \'85 and \'85 there you go, thought that would interest you!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry\rquote s heart turned over. His mother and father were beaming up at him, sitting on either side of a small, watery-eyed man Harry rec\-ognized at once as Wormtail: He was the one who had betrayed their whereabouts to Voldemort and so helped bring about their deaths.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Eh?\rdblquote  said Moody.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry looked up into Moody\rquote s heavily scarred and pitted face. Evi\-dently Moody was under the impression he had just given Harry a bit of a treat.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah,\rdblquote  said Harry, attempting to grin again. \ldblquote Er \'85 listen, I\rquote ve just remembered, I haven\rquote t packed my \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He was spared the trouble of inventing an object he had not packed; Sirius had just said, \ldblquote What\rquote s that you\rquote ve got there, Mad-Eye?\rdblquote  and Moody had turned toward him. Harry crossed the kitchen,\lang3081  \lang1033 slipped through the door and up the stairs before anyone could call him back.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He did not know why he had received such a shock; he had seen his parents\rquote  pictures before, after all, and he had met Wormtail\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 but to have them sprung on him like that, when he was least expecting it\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 No one would like that, he thought angrily. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And then, to see them surrounded by all those other happy faces \'85 Benjy Fenwick, who had been found in bits, and Gideon Prewett, who had died like a hero, and the Longbottoms, who had been tor\-tured into madness \'85 all waving happily out of the photograph forevermore, not knowing that they were doomed. \'85 Well, Moody might find that interesting \'85 he, Harry, found it disturbing. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry tiptoed up the stairs in the hall past the stuffed elf heads, glad to be on his own again, but as he approached the first landing he heard noises. Someone was sobbing in the drawing room.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hello?\rdblquote  Harry said.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was no answer but the sobbing continued. He climbed the remaining stairs two at a time, walked across the landing, and opened the drawing-room door.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Someone was cowering against the dark wall, her wand in her hand, her whole body shaking with sobs. Sprawled on the dusty old carpet in a patch of moonlight, clearly dead, was Ron.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 All the air seemed to vanish from Harry\rquote s lungs; he felt as though he were falling through the floor; his brain turned icy cold \emdash  Ron dead, no, it couldn\rquote t be \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But wait a moment, it \i couldn\rquote t\i0  be \emdash  Ron was downstairs \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Mrs. Weasley?\rdblquote  Harry croaked.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i R-r-riddikulus\i0 !\rquote\rquote\lang3081  \lang1033 Mrs. Weasley sobbed, pointing her shaking wand at Ron\rquote s body.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\i Crack.\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033 Ron\rquote s body turned into Bill\rquote s, spread-eagled on his back, his eyes wide open and empty. Mrs. Weasley sobbed harder than ever.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i R-riddikulus\i0 !\rdblquote  she sobbed again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\i Crack.\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033 Mr. Weasley\rquote s body replaced Bill\rquote s, his glasses askew, a trickle of blood running down his face.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No!\rdblquote  Mrs. Weasley moaned. \ldblquote No \'85 \i riddikulus\i0 ! \i Riddikulus\i0 ! \i RIDDIKULUS\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\i Crack.\i0  Dead twins. \i Crack.\i0  Dead Percy. \i Crack.\i0  Dead Harry \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Mrs. Weasley, just get out of here!\rdblquote  shouted Harry, staring down at his own dead body on the floor. \ldblquote Let someone else \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What\rquote s going on?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Lupin had come running into the room, closely followed by Sirius, with Moody stumping along behind them. Lupin looked from Mrs. Weasley to the dead Harry on the floor and seemed to understand in an instant. Pulling out his own wand he said, very firmly and clearly, \ldblquote\i Riddikulus\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry\rquote s body vanished. A silvery orb hung in the air over the spot where it had lain. Lupin waved his wand once more and the orb van\-ished in a puff of smoke.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh \emdash  oh \emdash  oh!\rdblquote  gulped Mrs. Weasley, and she broke into a storm of crying, her face in her hands.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Molly,\rdblquote  said Lupin bleakly, walking over to her, \ldblquote Molly, don\rquote t\lang3081  \lang1033\'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Next second she was sobbing her heart out on Lupin\rquote s shoulder.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Molly, it was just a boggart,\rdblquote  he said soothingly, patting her on the head. \ldblquote Just a stupid boggart\lang3081  \lang1033\'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I see them d-d-dead all the time!\rdblquote  Mrs. Weasley moaned into his shoulder. \ldblquote All the t-t-time! I d-d-dream about it\lang3081  \lang1033\'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Sirius was staring at the patch of carpet where the boggart, pre\-tending to be Harry\rquote s body, had lain. Moody was looking at Harry, who avoided his gaze. He had a funny feeling Moody\rquote s magical eye had followed him all the way out of the kitchen.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote D-d-don\rquote t tell Arthur,\rdblquote  Mrs. Weasley was gulping now, mopping\lang3081  \lang1033 her eyes frantically with her cuffs. \ldblquote I d-d-don\rquote t want him to know. \'85 Being silly \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Lupin handed her a handkerchief and she blew her nose.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry, I\rquote m so sorry, what must you think of me?\rdblquote  she said shakily. \ldblquote Not even able to get rid of a boggart\lang3081  \lang1033\'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Don\rquote t be stupid,\rdblquote  said Harry, trying to smile.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m just s-s-so worried,\rdblquote  she said, tears spilling out of her eyes again. \ldblquote Half the f-f-family\rquote s in the Order, it\rquote ll b-b-be a miracle if we all come through this. \'85 and P-P-Percy\rquote s not talking to us. \'85 What if something d-d-dreadful happens and we had never m-m-made up? And what\rquote s going to happen if Arthur and I get killed, who\rquote s g-g-going to look after Ron and Ginny?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Molly, that\rquote s enough,\rdblquote  said Lupin firmly. \ldblquote This isn\rquote t like last time. The Order is better prepared, we\rquote ve got a head start, we know what Voldemort\rquote s up to \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Mrs. Weasley gave a little squeak of fright at the sound of the name.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, Molly, come on, it\rquote s about time you got used to hearing it \emdash  look, I can\rquote t promise no one\rquote s going to get hurt, nobody can promise that, but we\rquote re much better off than we were last time, you weren\rquote t in the Order then, you don\rquote t understand, last time we were outnumbered twenty to one by the Death Eaters and they were picking us off one by one. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry thought of the photograph again, of his parents\rquote  beaming faces. He knew Moody was still watching him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Don\rquote t worry about Percy,\rdblquote  said Sirius abruptly. \ldblquote He\rquote ll come round. It\rquote s a matter of time before Voldemort moves into the open; once he does, the whole Ministry\rquote s going to be begging us to forgive them. And I\rquote m not sure I\rquote ll be accepting their apology,\rdblquote  he added bitterly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And as for who\rquote s going to look after Ron and Ginny if you and Arthur died,\rdblquote  said Lupin, smiling slightly, \ldblquote what do you think we\rquote d do, let them starve?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Mrs. Weasley smiled tremulously.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Being silly,\rdblquote  she muttered again, mopping her eyes.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But Harry, closing his bedroom door behind him some ten minutes later, could not think Mrs. Weasley silly. He could still see his parents beaming up at him from the tattered old photograph, unaware that their lives, like so many of those around them, were drawing to a close. The image of the boggart posing as the corpse of each member of Mrs. Weasley\rquote s family in turn kept flashing before his eyes.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Without warning, the scar on his forehead seared with pain again and his stomach churned horribly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Cut it out,\rdblquote  he said firmly, rubbing the scar as the pain receded again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote First sign of madness, talking to your own head,\rdblquote  said a sly voice from the empty picture on the wall.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry ignored it. He felt older than he had ever felt in his life, and it seemed extraordinary to him that barely an hour ago he had been worried about a joke shop and who had gotten a prefect\rquote s badge.\lang3081\par
