\lang1033 But the great black dog gave a joyful bark and gamboled around them, snapping at pigeons, and chasing its own tail. Harry couldn\rquote t help laughing. Sirius had been trapped inside for a very long time. Mrs. Weasley pursed her lips in an almost Aunt Petunia-ish way.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 It took them twenty minutes to reach King\rquote s Cross by foot and nothing more eventful happened during that time than Sirius scaring a couple of cats for Harry\rquote s entertainment. Once inside the station they lingered casually beside the barrier between platforms nine and ten until the coast was clear, then each of them leaned against it in\lang3081  \lang1033 turn and fell easily through onto platform nine and three quarters, where the Hogwarts Express stood belching sooty steam over a plat\-form packed with departing students and their families. Harry inhaled the familiar smell and felt his spirits soar. \'85 He was really going back. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I hope the others make it in time,\rdblquote  said Mrs. Weasley anxiously, staring behind her at the wrought-iron arch spanning the platform, through which new arrivals would come.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Nice dog, Harry!\rdblquote  called a tall boy with dreadlocks.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Thanks, Lee,\rdblquote  said Harry, grinning, as Sirius wagged his tail frantically.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh good,\rdblquote  said Mrs. Weasley, sounding relieved, \ldblquote here\rquote s Alastor with the luggage, look \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
