\lang1033 A warning whistle sounded; the students still on the platform started hurrying onto the train.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Quick, quick,\rdblquote  said Mrs. Weasley distractedly, hugging them at ran\-dom and catching Harry twice. \ldblquote Write. \'85 Be good. \'85 If you\rquote ve for\-gotten anything we\rquote ll send it on. \'85 Onto the train, now, hurry. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 For one brief moment, the great black dog reared onto its hind legs and placed its front paws on Harry\rquote s shoulders, but Mrs. Weasley shoved Harry away toward the train door hissing, \ldblquote For heaven\rquote s sake act more like a dog, Sirius!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote See you!\rdblquote  Harry called out of the open window as the train began to move, while Ron, Hermione, and Ginny waved beside him. The figures of Tonks, Lupin, Moody, and Mr. and Mrs. Weasley shrank rapidly but the black dog was bounding alongside the window, wag\-ging its tail; blurred people on the platform were laughing to see it chasing the train, and then they turned the corner, and Sirius was gone.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He shouldn\rquote t have come with us,\rdblquote  said Hermione in a worried voice.\lang3081\par
