\lang1033\ldblquote Fine,\rdblquote  said Harry again. \ldblquote Well, I-I might see you later, then.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, definitely,\rdblquote  said Ron, casting a shifty, anxious look at Harry. \ldblquote It\rquote s a pain having to go down there, I\rquote d rather \emdash  but we have to \emdash  I mean, I\rquote m not enjoying it, I\rquote m not Percy,\rdblquote  he finished defiantly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I know you\rquote re not,\rdblquote  said Harry and he grinned. But as Hermione and Ron dragged their trunks, Crookshanks, and a caged Pigwidgeon off toward the engine end of the train, Harry felt an odd sense of loss. He had never traveled on the Hogwarts Express without Ron.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Come on,\rdblquote  Ginny told him, \ldblquote if we get a move on we\rquote ll be able to save them places.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Right,\rdblquote  said Harry, picking up Hedwig\rquote s cage in one hand and the handle of his trunk in the other. They struggled off down the corridor, peering through the glass-paneled doors into the compartments they passed, which were already full. Harry could not help noticing that a lot of people stared back at him with great interest and that several of them nudged their neighbors and pointed him out. After he had met this behavior in five consecutive carriages he remembered that the \i Daily Prophet\i0  had been telling its readers all summer what a lying show-off he was. He wondered bleakly whether the people now star\-ing and whispering believed the stories.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 In the very last carriage they met Neville Longbottom, Harry\rquote s fel\-low fifth-year Gryffindor, his round face shining with the effort of pulling his trunk along and maintaining a one-handed grip on his struggling toad, Trevor.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hi, Harry,\rdblquote  he panted. \ldblquote Hi, Ginny. \'85 Everywhere\rquote s full. \'85 I can\rquote t find a seat. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What are you talking about?\rdblquote  said Ginny, who had squeezed past Neville to peer into the compartment behind him. \ldblquote There\rquote s room in this one, there\rquote s only Loony Lovegood in here \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Neville mumbled something about not wanting to disturb anyone.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Don\rquote t be silly,\rdblquote  said Ginny, laughing, \ldblquote she\rquote s all right.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She slid the door open and pulled her trunk inside it. Harry and Neville followed.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hi, Luna,\rdblquote  said Ginny. \ldblquote Is it okay if we take these seats?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The girl beside the window looked up. She had straggly, waist-length, dirty-blond hair, very pale eyebrows, and protuberant eyes that gave her a permanently surprised look. Harry knew at once why Neville had chosen to pass this compartment by. The girl gave off an aura of distinct dottiness. Perhaps it was the fact that she had stuck her wand behind her left ear for safekeeping, or that she had chosen to wear a necklace of butterbeer caps, or that she was reading a magazine upside down. Her eyes ranged over Neville and came to rest on Harry. She nodded.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Thanks,\rdblquote  said Ginny, smiling at her.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry and Neville stowed the three trunks and Hedwig\rquote s cage in the luggage rack and sat down. The girl called Luna watched them over her upside-down magazine, which was called \i The Quibbler.\i0  She did not seem to need to blink as much as normal humans. She stared and stared at Harry, who had taken the seat opposite her and now wished he had not.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Had a good summer, Luna?\rdblquote  Ginny asked.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes,\rdblquote  said Luna dreamily, without taking her eyes off Harry. \ldblquote Yes, it was quite enjoyable, you know. \i You\rquote re\i0  Harry Potter,\rdblquote  she added.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I know I am,\rdblquote  said Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Neville chuckled. Luna turned her pale eyes upon him instead.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And I don\rquote t know who you are.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m nobody,\rdblquote  said Neville hurriedly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No you\rquote re not,\rdblquote  said Ginny sharply. \ldblquote Neville Longbottom \emdash  Luna Lovegood. Luna\rquote s in my year, but in Ravenclaw.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Wit beyond measure is man\rquote s greatest treasure,\i0\rdblquote  said Luna in a singsong voice.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She raised her upside-down magazine high enough to hide her face and fell silent. Harry and Neville looked at each other with their eye\-brows raised. Ginny suppressed a giggle.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The train rattled onward, speeding them out into open country. It was an odd, unsettled sort of day; one moment the carriage was full of sunlight and the next they were passing beneath ominously gray clouds.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Guess what I got for my birthday?\rdblquote  said Neville.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Another Remembrall?\rdblquote  said Harry, remembering the marblelike device Neville\rquote s grandmother had sent him in an effort to improve his abysmal memory.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No,\rdblquote  said Neville, \ldblquote I could do with one, though, I lost the old one ages ago. \'85 No, look at this. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He dug the hand that was not keeping a firm grip on Trevor into his schoolbag and after a little bit of rummaging pulled out what ap\-peared to be a small gray cactus in a pot, except that it was covered with what looked like boils rather than spines.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Mimbulus mimbletonia,\i0\rdblquote\lang3081  \lang1033 he said proudly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry stared at the thing. It was pulsating slightly, giving it the rather sinister look of some diseased internal organ.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It\rquote s really, really rare,\rdblquote  said Neville, beaming. \ldblquote I don\rquote t know if there\rquote s one in the greenhouse at Hogwarts, even. I can\rquote t wait to show it to Professor Sprout. My great-uncle Algie got it for me in Assyria. I\rquote m going to see if I can breed from it.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry knew that Neville\rquote s favorite subject was Herbology, but for the life of him he could not see what he would want with this stunted little plant.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Does it \emdash  er \emdash  do anything?\rdblquote  he asked.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Loads of stuff!\rdblquote  said Neville proudly. \ldblquote It\rquote s got an amazing defen\-sive mechanism \emdash  hold Trevor for me. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He dumped the toad into Harry\rquote s lap and took a quill from his schoolbag. Luna Lovegood\rquote s popping eyes appeared over the top of her upside-down magazine again, watching what Neville was doing. Neville held the \i Mimbulus mimbletonia\i0  up to his eyes, his tongue be\-tween his teeth, chose his spot, and gave the plant a sharp prod with the tip of his quill.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Liquid squirted from every boil on the plant, thick, stinking, dark-green jets of it; they hit the ceiling, the windows, and spattered Luna Lovegood\rquote s magazine. Ginny, who had flung her arms up in front of her face just in time, merely looked as though she was wearing a slimy green hat, but Harry, whose hands had been busy preventing the es\-cape of Trevor, received a face full. It smelled like rancid manure.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Neville, whose face and torso were also drenched, shook his head to get the worst out of his eyes.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote S-sorry,\rdblquote  he gasped. \ldblquote I haven\rquote t tried that before. \'85 Didn\rquote t realize it would be quite so \'85 Don\rquote t worry, though, Stinksap\rquote s not poiso\-nous,\rdblquote  he added nervously, as Harry spat a mouthful onto the floor.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 At that precise moment the door of their compartment slid open.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh \'85 hello, Harry,\rdblquote  said a nervous voice. \ldblquote Um \'85 bad time?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry wiped the lenses of his glasses with his Trevor-free hand. A very pretty girl with long, shiny black hair was standing in the doorway smiling at him: Cho Chang, the Seeker on the Ravenclaw Quidditch team.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh \'85 hi,\rdblquote  said Harry blankly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Um \'85\rdblquote  said Cho. \ldblquote Well\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 just thought I\rquote d say hello \'85 \rquote bye then.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She closed the door again, rather pink in the face, and departed. Harry slumped back in his seat and groaned. He would have liked Cho to discover him sitting with a group of very cool people laughing\lang3081  \lang1033 their heads off at a joke he had just told; he would not have chosen to be sitting with Neville and Loony Lovegood, clutching a toad and dripping in Stinksap.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Never mind,\rdblquote  said Ginny bracingly. \ldblquote Look, we can get rid of all this easily.\rdblquote  She pulled out her wand. \ldblquote\i Scourgify\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The Stinksap vanished.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Sorry,\rdblquote  said Neville again, in a small voice.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron and Hermione did not turn up for nearly an hour, by which time the food trolley had already gone by. Harry, Ginny, and Neville had finished their Pumpkin Pasties and were busy swapping Choco\-late Frog cards when the compartment door slid open and they walked in, accompanied by Crookshanks and a shrilly hooting Pig\-widgeon in his cage.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m starving,\rdblquote  said Ron, stowing Pigwidgeon next to Hedwig, grabbing a Chocolate Frog from Harry and throwing himself into the seat next to him. He ripped open the wrapper, bit off the Frog\rquote s head, and leaned back with his eyes closed as though he had had a very ex\-hausting morning.\lang3081\par
