\lang1033\ldblquote And guess who\rquote s a Slytherin prefect?\rdblquote  said Ron, still with his eyes closed.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Malfoy,\rdblquote  replied Harry at once, his worst fear confirmed.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote  \rquote Course,\rdblquote  said Ron bitterly, stuffing the rest of the Frog into his mouth and taking another.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And that complete \i cow\i0  Pansy Parkinson,\rdblquote  said Hermione vicious\-ly. \ldblquote How she got to be a prefect when she\rquote s thicker than a concussed troll\lang3081  \lang1033\'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Who\rquote s Hufflepuff?\rdblquote  Harry asked.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ernie Macmillan and Hannah Abbott,\rdblquote  said Ron thickly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And Anthony Goldstein and Padma Patil for Ravenclaw,\rdblquote  said Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You went to the Yule Ball with Padma Patil,\rdblquote  said a vague voice.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Everyone turned to look at Luna Lovegood, who was gazing un-blinkingly at Ron over the top of \i The Quibbler.\i0  He swallowed his mouthful of Frog.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, I know I did,\rdblquote  he said, looking mildly surprised.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote She didn\rquote t enjoy it very much,\rdblquote  Luna informed him. \ldblquote She doesn\rquote t think you treated her very well, because you wouldn\rquote t dance with her. I don\rquote t think I\rquote d have minded,\rdblquote  she added thoughtfully, \ldblquote I don\rquote t like dancing very much.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She retreated behind \i The Quibbler\i0  again. Ron stared at the cover with his mouth hanging open for a few seconds, then looked around at Ginny for some kind of explanation, but Ginny had stuffed her knuckles in her mouth to stop herself giggling. Ron shook his head, bemused, then checked his watch.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We\rquote re supposed to patrol the corridors every so often,\rdblquote  he told Harry and Neville, \ldblquote and we can give out punishments if people are misbehaving. I can\rquote t wait to get Crabbe and Goyle for something. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote re not supposed to abuse your position, Ron!\rdblquote  said Hermione sharply.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, right, because Malfoy won\rquote t abuse it at all,\rdblquote  said Ron sarcastically.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So you\rquote re going to descend to his level?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No, I\rquote m just going to make sure I get his mates before he gets mine.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote For heaven\rquote s sake, Ron \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote ll make Goyle do lines, it\rquote ll kill him, he hates writing,\rdblquote  said Ron happily. He lowered his voice to Goyle\rquote s low grunt and, screwing up his face in a look of pained concentration, mimed writing in midair. \i\ldblquote I\lang3081\i0  \lang1033\'85 \i must\lang3081\i0  \lang1033\'85 \i not\lang3081\i0  \lang1033\'85 \i look\lang3081\i0  \lang1033\'85 \i like\lang3081\i0  \lang1033\'85 \i a\i0  \'85 \i baboon\rquote s\lang3081\i0  \lang1033\'85 \i backside\i0 . \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Everyone laughed, but nobody laughed harder than Luna Love\-good. She let out a scream of mirth that caused Hedwig to wake up and flap her wings indignantly and Crookshanks to leap up into the luggage rack, hissing. She laughed so hard that her magazine slipped out of her grasp, slid down her legs, and onto the floor.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote That was \i funny\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Her prominent eyes swam with tears as she gasped for breath, staring at Ron. Utterly nonplussed, he looked around at the others, who were now laughing at the expression on Ron\rquote s face and at the ludicrously prolonged laughter of Luna Lovegood, who was rocking backward and forward, clutching her sides.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Are you taking the mickey?\rdblquote  said Ron, frowning at her.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Baboon\rquote s \'85 backside!\rdblquote  she choked, holding her ribs.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Everyone else was watching Luna laughing, but Harry, glancing at the magazine on the floor, noticed something that made him dive for it. Upside down it had been hard to tell what the picture on the front was, but Harry now realized it was a fairly bad cartoon of Cornelius Fudge; Harry only recognized him because of the lime-green bowler hat. One of Fudge\rquote s hands was clenched around a bag of gold; the other hand was throttling a goblin. The cartoon was captioned: How Far Will Fudge Go to Gain Gringotts?\lang3081\par
