\lang1033\ldblquote Oh no,\rdblquote  said Umbridge, smiling so widely that she looked as though she had just swallowed a particularly juicy fly. \ldblquote Oh no, no, no. This is your punishment for spreading evil, nasty, attention-seeking stories, Mr. Potter, and punishments certainly cannot be adjusted to\lang3081  \lang1033 suit the guilty one\rquote s convenience. No, you will come here at five o\rquote clock tomorrow, and the next day, and on Friday too, and you will do your detentions as planned. I think it rather a good thing that you are missing something you really want to do. It ought to reinforce the lesson I am trying to teach you.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry felt the blood surge to his head and heard a thumping noise in his ears. So he told evil, nasty, attention-seeking stories, did he?\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She was watching him with her head slightly to one side, still smil\-ing widely, as though she knew exactly what he was thinking and was waiting to see whether he would start shouting again. With a massive effort Harry looked away from her, dropped his schoolbag beside the straight-backed chair, and sat down.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote There,\rdblquote  said Umbridge sweetly, \ldblquote we\rquote re getting better at controlling our temper already, aren\rquote t we? Now, you are going to be doing some lines for me, Mr. Potter. No, not with your quill,\rdblquote  she added, as Harry bent down to open his bag. \ldblquote You\rquote re going to be using a rather special one of mine. Here you are.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She handed him a long, thin black quill with an unusually sharp point.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I want you to write \lquote\i I must not tell lies,\i0\rquote  \rdblquote\lang3081  \lang1033 she told him softly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote How many times?\rdblquote  Harry asked, with a creditable imitation of politeness.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, as long as it takes for the message to \i sink in,\i0\rdblquote  said Umbridge sweetly. \ldblquote Off you go.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She moved over to her desk, sat down, and bent over a stack of parchment that looked like essays for marking. Harry raised the sharp black quill and then realized what was missing.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You haven\rquote t given me any ink,\rdblquote  he said.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, you won\rquote t need ink,\rdblquote  said Professor Umbridge with the mer\-est suggestion of a laugh in her voice.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry placed the point of the quill on the paper and wrote: \i I must not tell lies.\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033 He let out a gasp of pain. The words had appeared on the parch\-ment in what appeared to be shining red ink. At the same time, the words had appeared on the back of Harry\rquote s right hand, cut into his skin as though traced there by a scalpel \emdash  yet even as he stared at the shining cut, the skin healed over again, leaving the place where it had been slightly redder than before but quite smooth.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry looked around at Umbridge. She was watching him, her wide, toadlike mouth stretched in a smile.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
