They had expected to have to comb Hermione\rquote s \i Daily Prophet\i0  carefully next morning to find the article Percy had mentioned in his letter. However, the departing delivery owl had barely cleared the top of the milk jug when Hermione let out a huge gasp and flat\-tened the newspaper to reveal a large photograph of Dolores Um\-bridge, smiling widely and blinking slowly at them from beneath the headline:\par
\par
\pard\qc MINISTRY SEEKS EDUCATIONAL REFORM\par
DOLORES UMBRIDGE APPOINTED FIRST-EVER \ldblquote HIGH INQUISITOR\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi284\qj\lang1033\par
\ldblquote  \lquote High Inquisitor\rquote ?\rdblquote  said Harry darkly, his half-eaten bit of toast slipping from his fingers. \ldblquote What does \i that\i0  mean?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione read aloud:\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i In a surprise move last night the Ministry of Magic passed new legis\-lation giving itself an unprecedented level of control at Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry.\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033\ldblquote  \lquote\i The Minister has been growing uneasy about goings-on at Hogwarts\lang3081\i0  \lang1033\i for some time\i0 ,\rquote\i  said Junior Assistant to the Minister, Percy Weasley. \i0\lquote\i He is now responding to concerns voiced by anxious parents, who feel the school may be moving in a direction they do not approve.\i0\rquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i This is not the first time in recent weeks Fudge has used new laws to effect improvements at the Wizarding school. As recently as August 30th Educational Decree Twenty-two was passed, to ensure that, in the event of the current headmaster being unable to provide a candidate for a teaching post, the Ministry should select an appropriate person.\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033\ldblquote  \lquote\i That\rquote s how Dolores Umbridge came to be appointed to the teaching staff at Hogwarts\i0 ,\rquote\i  said Weasley last night. \i0\lquote\i Dumbledore couldn\rquote t find any\-one, so the Minister put in Umbridge and of course, she\rquote s been an imme\-diate success\i0  \emdash\rquote  \rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote She\rquote s been a WHAT?\rdblquote  said Harry loudly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Wait, there\rquote s more,\rdblquote  said Hermione grimly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote  \lquote\emdash\lang3081  \lang1033\i an immediate success, totally revolutionizing the teaching of Defense Against the Dark Arts and providing the Minister with on-the-ground feedback about what\rquote s really happening at Hogwarts.\i0\rquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i It is this last function that the Ministry has now formalized with the passing of Educational Decree Twenty-three, which creates the new posi\-tion of \i0\lquote\i Hogwarts High Inquisitor.\i0\rquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote  \lquote\i This is an exciting new phase in the Minister\rquote s plan to get to grips with what some are calling the \i0\ldblquote\i falling standards\i0\rdblquote  \i at Hogwarts\i0 ,\rquote\i  said Weasley. \i0\lquote\i The Inquisitor will have powers to inspect her fellow educators and make sure that they are coming up to scratch. Professor Umbridge has been offered this position in addition to her own teaching post, and we are delighted to say that she has accepted.\i0\rquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i The Ministry\rquote s new moves have received enthusiastic support from parents of students at Hogwarts.\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033\ldblquote  \lquote\i I feel much easier in my mind now that I know that Dumbledore is being subjected to fair and objective evaluation,\rquote  said Mr. Lucius Malfoy, 41, speaking from his Wiltshire mansion last night. \lquote Many of us with our children\rquote s best interests at heart have been concerned about some of\lang3081\i0  \lang1033\i Dumbledore\rquote s eccentric decisions in the last few years and will be glad to know that the Ministry is keeping an eye on the situation.\i0\rquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Among those \i0\lquote\i eccentric decisions\i0\rquote  \i are undoubtedly the controversial staff appointments previously described in this newspaper, which have in\-cluded the hiring of werewolf Remus Lupin, half giant Rubeus Hagrid, and delusional ex-Auror \i0\lquote\i Mad-Eye\i0\rquote  \i Moody.\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Rumors abound, of course, that Albus Dumbledore, once Supreme Mugwump of the International Confederation of Wizards and Chief Warlock of the Wizengamot, is no longer up to the task of managing the prestigious school of\lang3081  \lang1033 Hogwarts.\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033\ldblquote  \lquote\i I think the appointment of the Inquisitor is a first step toward ensur\-ing that Hogwarts has a headmaster in whom we can all repose confidence\i0 ,\rquote  \i said a Ministry insider last night.\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Wizengamot elders Griselda Marchbanks and Tiberius Ogden have resigned in protest at the introduction of the post of Inquisitor to Hogwarts.\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033\ldblquote  \lquote\i Hogwarts is a school, not an outpost of Cornelius Fudge\rquote s office\i0 ,\rquote\i  said Madam Marchbanks. \i0\lquote\i This is a further disgusting attempt to discredit Al\-bus Dumbledore\i0 .\rquote\i  \i0 (\i For a full account of Madam Marchbanks\rquote  alleged links to subversive goblin groups, turn to page 17\i0 ).\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione finished reading and looked across the table at the other two.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So now we know how we ended up with Umbridge! Fudge passed this \lquote Educational Decree\rquote  and forced her on us! And now he\rquote s given her the power to inspect other teachers!\rdblquote  Hermione was breathing fast and her eyes were very bright. \ldblquote I can\rquote t believe this. It\rquote s \i outrageous. \'85\i0\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I know it is,\rdblquote  said Harry. He looked down at his right hand, clenched upon the tabletop, and saw the faint white outline of the words Umbridge had forced him to cut into his skin.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But a grin was unfurling on Ron\rquote s face.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What?\rdblquote  said Harry and Hermione together, staring at him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, I can\rquote t wait to see McGonagall inspected,\rdblquote  said Ron happily. \ldblquote Umbridge won\rquote t know what\rquote s hit her.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, come on,\rdblquote  said Hermione, jumping up, \ldblquote we\rquote d better get go\-ing, if she\rquote s inspecting Binns\rquote s class we don\rquote t want to be late. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But Professor Umbridge was not inspecting their History of Magic lesson, which was just as dull as the previous Monday, nor was she in Snape\rquote s dungeon when they arrived for double Potions, where Harry\rquote s moonstone essay was handed back to him with a large, spiky black D scrawled in an upper corner.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I have awarded you the grades you would have received if you pre\-sented this work in your O.W.L,\rdblquote  said Snape with a smirk, as he swept among them, passing back their homework. \ldblquote This should give you a realistic idea of what to expect in your examination.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Snape reached the front of the class and turned to face them.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The general standard of this homework was abysmal. Most of you would have failed had this been your examination. I expect to see a great deal more effort for this week\rquote s essay on the various varieties of venom antidotes, or I shall have to start handing out detentions to those dunces who get D\rquote s.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He smirked as Malfoy sniggered and said in a carrying whisper, \ldblquote Some people got \i D\rquote s\i0 ? Ha!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry realized that Hermione was looking sideways to see what grade he had received; he slid his moonstone essay back into his bag as quickly as possible, feeling that he would rather keep that information private.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Determined not to give Snape an excuse to fail him this lesson, Harry read and reread every line of the instructions on the blackboard at least three times before acting on them. His Strengthening Solution was not precisely the clear turquoise shade of Hermione\rquote s but it was at least blue rather than pink, like Neville\rquote s, and he delivered a flask of it to Snape\rquote s desk at the end of the lesson with a feeling of mingled defi\-ance and relief.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, that wasn\rquote t as bad as last week, was it?\rdblquote  said Hermione, as they climbed the steps out of the dungeon and made their way across\lang3081  \lang1033 the entrance hall toward lunch. \ldblquote And the homework didn\rquote t go too badly either, did it?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 When neither Ron nor Harry answered, she pressed on, \ldblquote I mean, all right, I didn\rquote t expect the top grade, not if he\rquote s marking to O.W.L. standard, but a pass is quite encouraging at this stage, wouldn\rquote t you say?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry made a noncommittal noise in his throat.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Of course, a lot can happen between now and the exam, we\rquote ve got plenty of time to improve, but the grades we\rquote re getting now are a sort of baseline, aren\rquote t they? Something we can build on \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They sat down together at the Gryffindor table.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Obviously, I\rquote d have been \i thrilled\i0  if I\rquote d gotten an O \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hermione,\rdblquote  said Ron sharply, \ldblquote if you want to know what grades we got, ask.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I don\rquote t \emdash  I didn\rquote t mean \emdash  well, if you want to tell me \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I got a P,\rdblquote  said Ron, ladling soup into his bowl. \ldblquote Happy?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, that\rquote s nothing to be ashamed of,\rdblquote  said Fred, who had just ar\-rived at the table with George and Lee Jordan and was sitting down on Harry\rquote s right. \ldblquote Nothing wrong with a good healthy P.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But,\rdblquote  said Hermione, \ldblquote doesn\rquote t P stand for \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote  \lquote Poor,\rquote  yeah,\rdblquote  said Lee Jordan. \ldblquote Still, better than D, isn\rquote t it? \lquote Dreadful\rquote ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry felt his face grow warm and faked a small coughing fit over his roll. When he emerged from this he was sorry to find that Hermione was still in full flow about O.W.L. grades.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So top grade\rquote s O for \lquote Outstanding,\rquote  \rdblquote  she was saying, \ldblquote and then there\rquote s A \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No, E,\rdblquote  George corrected her, \ldblquote E for \lquote Exceeds Expectations.\rquote  And I\rquote ve always thought Fred and I should\rquote ve got E in everything, because we exceeded expectations just by turning up for the exams.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They all laughed except Hermione, who plowed on, \ldblquote So after E, it\rquote s A for \lquote Acceptable,\rquote  and that\rquote s the last pass grade, isn\rquote t it?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yep,\rdblquote  said Fred, dunking an entire roll in his soup, transferring it to his mouth, and swallowing it whole.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Then you get P for \lquote Poor\rquote  \rdblquote  \emdash  Ron raised both his arms in mock celebration \emdash  \ldblquote and D for \lquote Dreadful.\rquote  \rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And then T,\rdblquote  George reminded him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote T?\rdblquote  asked Hermione, looking appalled. \ldblquote Even lower than a D? What on earth does that stand for?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote  \lquote Troll,\rquote  \rdblquote  said George promptly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry laughed again, though he was not sure whether or not George was joking. He imagined trying to conceal from Hermione that he had received T\rquote s in all his O.W.L.s and immediately resolved to work harder from now on.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You lot had an inspected lesson yet?\rdblquote  Fred asked them.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No,\rdblquote  said Hermione at once, \ldblquote have you?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Just now, before lunch,\rdblquote  said George. \ldblquote Charms.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What was it like?\rdblquote  Harry and Hermione asked together.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Fred shrugged.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Not that bad. Umbridge just lurked in the corner making notes on a clipboard. You know what Flitwick\rquote s like, he treated her like a guest, didn\rquote t seem to bother him at all. She didn\rquote t say much. Asked Alicia a couple of questions about what the classes are normally like, Alicia told her they were really good, that was it.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I can\rquote t see old Flitwick getting marked down,\rdblquote  said George, \ldblquote he usually gets everyone through their exams all right.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Who\rquote ve you got this afternoon?\rdblquote  Fred asked Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Trelawney \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote A T if ever I saw one \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\emdash  and Umbridge herself.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, be a good boy and keep your temper with Umbridge today,\rdblquote  said George. \ldblquote Angelina\rquote ll do her nut if you miss any more Quidditch practices.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But Harry did not have to wait for Defense Against the Dark Arts\lang3081  \lang1033 to meet Professor Umbridge. He was pulling out his dream diary in a seat at the very back of the shadowy Divination room when Ron el\-bowed him in the ribs and, looking round, he saw Professor Umbridge emerging through the trapdoor in the floor. The class, which had been talking cheerily, fell silent at once. The abrupt fall in the noise level made Professor Trelawney, who had been wafting about handing out \i Dream Oracles,\i0  look round.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Good afternoon, Professor Trelawney,\rdblquote  said Professor Umbridge with her wide smile. \ldblquote You received my note, I trust? Giving the time and date of your inspection?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Professor Trelawney nodded curtly and, looking very disgruntled, turned her back on Professor Umbridge and continued to give out books. Still smiling, Professor Umbridge grasped the back of the near\-est armchair and pulled it to the front of the class so that it was a few inches behind Professor Trelawney\rquote s seat. She then sat down, took her clipboard from her flowery bag, and looked up expectantly, waiting for the class to begin.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Professor Trelawney pulled her shawls tight about her with slightly trembling hands and surveyed the class through her hugely magnify\-ing lenses. \ldblquote We shall be continuing our study of prophetic dreams to\-day,\rdblquote  she said in a brave attempt at her usual mystic tones, though her voice shook slightly. \ldblquote Divide into pairs, please, and interpret each other\rquote s latest nighttime visions with the aid of the \i Oracle.\i0\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She made as though to sweep back to her seat, saw Professor Um\-bridge sitting right beside it, and immediately veered left toward Par\-vati and Lavender, who were already deep in discussion about Parvati\rquote s most recent dream.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry opened his copy of \i The Dream Oracle,\i0  watching Umbridge covertly. She was making notes on her clipboard now. After a few min\-utes she got to her feet and began to pace the room in Trelawney\rquote s wake, listening to her conversations with students and posing ques\-tions here and there. Harry bent his head hurriedly over his book.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Think of a dream, quick,\rdblquote  he told Ron, \ldblquote in case the old toad comes our way.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I did it last time,\rdblquote  Ron protested, \ldblquote it\rquote s your turn, you tell me one.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, I dunno \'85\rdblquote  said Harry desperately, who could not remem\-ber dreaming anything at all over the last few days. \ldblquote Let\rquote s say I dreamed I was \'85 drowning Snape in my cauldron. Yeah, that\rquote ll do. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
