\lang1033 Harry and Ron were not the only people watching and listening sneakily from behind their books now; most of the class were staring transfixed at Professor Trelawney as she drew herself up to her full height, her beads and bangles clinking.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The Inner Eye does not See upon command!\rdblquote  she said in scandal\-ized tones.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I see,\rdblquote  said Professor Umbridge softly, making yet another note on her clipboard.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I \emdash  but \emdash  but\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 \i wait\i0 !\rdblquote\i  \i0 said Professor Trelawney suddenly, in an attempt at her usual ethereal voice, though the mystical effect was ruined somewhat by the way it was shaking with anger. \ldblquote I \'85 I think I \i do\i0  see something \'85 something that concerns \i you. \'85 \i0 Why, I sense something \'85 something dark \'85 some grave peril\lang3081  \lang1033\'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Professor Trelawney pointed a shaking finger at Professor Um\-bridge who continued to smile blandly at her, eyebrows raised.\lang3081\par
