\lang1033 She turned away, leaving Professor Trelawney standing rooted to the spot, her chest heaving. Harry caught Ron\rquote s eye and knew that Ron was thinking exactly the same as he was: They both knew that Professor Trelawney was an old fraud, but on the other hand, they loathed Umbridge so much that they felt very much on Tre\-lawney\rquote s side \emdash  until she swooped down on them a few seconds later, that was.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well?\rdblquote  she said, snapping her long fingers under Harry\rquote s nose, un\-characteristically brisk. \ldblquote Let me see the start you\rquote ve made on your dream diary, please.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And by the time she had interpreted Harry\rquote s dreams at the top of her voice (all of which, even the ones that involved eating porridge, apparently foretold a gruesome and early death), he was feeling much less sympathetic toward her. All the while, Professor Umbridge stood a few feet away, making notes on that clipboard, and when the bell rang she descended the silver ladder first so that she was waiting for them all when they reached their Defense Against the Dark Arts les\-son ten minutes later.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She was humming and smiling to herself when they entered the room. Harry and Ron told Hermione, who had been in Arithmancy, exactly what had happened in Divination while they all took out their copies of \i Defensive Magical Theory,\i0  but before Hermione could ask any questions Professor Umbridge had called them all to order and si\-lence fell.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Wands away,\rdblquote  she instructed them all smilingly, and those people who had been hopeful enough to take them out sadly returned them to their bags. \ldblquote As we finished chapter one last lesson, I would like you all to turn to page nineteen today and commence chapter two, \lquote Common De\-fensive Theories and Their Derivation.\rquote  There will be no need to talk.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Still smiling her wide, self-satisfied smile, she sat down at her desk. The class gave an audible sigh as it turned, as one, to page nineteen. Harry wondered dully whether there were enough chapters in the book to keep them reading through all this year\rquote s lessons and was on the point of checking the contents when he noticed that Hermione had her hand in the air again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Professor Umbridge had noticed too, and what was more, she seemed to have worked out a strategy for just such an eventuality. In\-stead of trying to pretend she had not noticed Hermione, she got to her feet and walked around the front row of desks until they were face-to-face, then she bent down and whispered, so that the rest of the class could not hear, \ldblquote What is it this time, Miss Granger?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
