\lang1033\ldblquote For disrupting my class with pointless interruptions,\rdblquote  said Profes\-sor Umbridge smoothly. \ldblquote I am here to teach you using a Ministry-approved method that does not include inviting students to give their opinions on matters about which they understand very little. Your pre\-vious teachers in this subject may have allowed you more license, but as none of them \emdash  with the possible exception of Professor Quirrell, who did at least appear to have restricted himself to age-appropriate subjects \emdash  would have passed a Ministry inspection \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, Quirrell was a great teacher,\rdblquote  said Harry loudly, \ldblquote there was just that minor drawback of him having Lord Voldemort sticking out of the back of his head.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
