\pard\nowidctlpar\fi284\qj\lang1033 The cut on the back of Harry\rquote s hand had barely healed and by the following morning, it was bleeding again. He did not complain dur\-ing the evening\rquote s detention; he was determined not to give Umbridge the satisfaction; over and over again he wrote \i I must not tell lies\i0  and not a sound escaped his lips, though the cut deepened with every letter.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The very worst part of this second week\rquote s worth of detentions was, just as George had predicted, Angelina\rquote s reaction. She cornered him just as he arrived at the Gryffindor table for breakfast on Tuesday and shouted so loudly that Professor McGonagall came sweeping down upon the pair of them from the staff table.\lang3081\par
