\lang1033 Professor Umbridge made a note.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Very well,\rdblquote  she said, \ldblquote you will receive the results of your inspection in ten days\rquote  time.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I can hardly wait,\rdblquote  said Professor McGonagall in a coldly indiffer\-ent voice, and she strode off toward the door. \ldblquote Hurry up, you three,\rdblquote  she added, sweeping Harry, Ron, and Hermione before her. Harry could not help giving her a faint smile and could have sworn he re\-ceived one in return.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He had thought that the next time he would see Umbridge would be in his detention that evening, but he was wrong. When they walked down the lawns toward the forest for Care of Magical Creatures, they\lang3081  \lang1033 found her and her clipboard waiting for them beside Professor Grubbly-Plank.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You do not usually take this class, is that correct?\rdblquote  Harry heard her ask as they arrived at the trestle table where the group of captive bowtruckles were scrabbling around for wood lice like so many living twigs.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Quite correct,\rdblquote  said Professor Grubbly-Plank, hands behind her back and bouncing on the balls of her feet. \ldblquote I am a substitute teacher standing in for Professor Hagrid.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry exchanged uneasy looks with Ron and Hermione. Malfoy was whispering with Crabbe and Goyle; he would surely love this op\-portunity to tell tales on Hagrid to a member of the Ministry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hmm,\rdblquote  said Professor Umbridge, dropping her voice, though Harry could still hear her quite clearly, \ldblquote I wonder \emdash  the headmaster seems strangely reluctant to give me any information on the matter \emdash  can \i you\i0  tell me what is causing Professor Hagrid\rquote s very extended leave of absence?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry saw Malfoy look up eagerly.\lang3081\par
\ldblquote  \rquote\lang1033 Fraid I can\rquote t,\rdblquote  said Professor Grubbly-Plank breezily. \ldblquote Don\rquote t know anything more about it than you do. Got an owl from Dumble\-dore, would I like a couple of weeks teaching work, accepted \emdash  that\rquote s as much as I know. Well\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 shall I get started then?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes, please do,\rdblquote  said Professor Umbridge, scribbling upon her clipboard.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Umbridge took a different tack in this class and wandered among the students, questioning them on magical creatures. Most people were able to answer well and Harry\rquote s spirits lifted somewhat; at least the class was not letting Hagrid down.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Overall,\rdblquote  said Professor Umbridge, returning to Professor Grubbly-Plank\rquote s side after a lengthy interrogation of Dean Thomas, \ldblquote how do you, as a temporary member of staff\lang3081  \lang1033\emdash  an objective outsider, I suppose\lang3081  \lang1033 you might say \emdash  how do you find Hogwarts? Do you feel you receive enough support from the school management?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, yes, Dumbledore\rquote s excellent,\rdblquote  said Professor Grubbly-Plank heartily. \ldblquote No, I\rquote m very happy with the way things are run, very happy indeed.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Looking politely incredulous, Umbridge made a tiny note on her clipboard and went on, \ldblquote And what are you planning to cover with this class this year \emdash  assuming, of course, that Professor Hagrid does not return?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, I\rquote ll take them through the creatures that most often come up in O.W.L.,\rdblquote  said Professor Grubbly-Plank. \ldblquote Not much left to do \emdash  they\rquote ve studied unicorns and nifflers, I thought we\rquote d cover porlocks and kneazles, make sure they can recognize crups and knarls, you know. \'85\lang3081\rdblquote\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, \i you \i0 seem to know what you\rquote re doing, at any rate,\rdblquote  said Pro\-fessor Umbridge, making a very obvious tick on her clipboard. Harry did not like the emphasis she put on \ldblquote\i you\i0\rdblquote\lang3081  \lang1033 and\i  \i0 liked it even less when she put her next question to Goyle: \ldblquote Now, I hear there have been in\-juries in this class?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
