\pard\nowidctlpar\fi284\qj\lang1033 It was nearly midnight when Harry left Umbridge\rquote s office that night, his hand now bleeding so severely that it was staining the scarf he had wrapped around it. He expected the common room to be empty when he returned, but Ron and Hermione had sat up waiting for him. He was pleased to see them, especially as Hermione was disposed to be sympathetic rather than critical.\lang3081\par
