Harry and Ron read the notice over the heads of some anxious-looking second years.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Does this mean they\rquote re going to shut down the Gobstones Club?\rdblquote  one of them asked his friend.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I reckon you\rquote ll be okay with Gobstones,\rdblquote  Ron said darkly, making the second year jump. \ldblquote I don\rquote t think we\rquote re going to be as lucky, though, do you?\rdblquote  he asked Harry as the second years hurried away.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry was reading the notice through again. The happiness that had filled him since Saturday was gone. His insides were pulsing with rage.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote This isn\rquote t a coincidence,\rdblquote  he said, his hands forming fists. \ldblquote She knows.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
