\lang1033 Hedwig was quivering; when Harry made to touch the wing she\lang3081  \lang1033 gave a little jump, all her feathers on end as though she was inflating herself, and gazed at him reproachfully.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Professor Binns,\rdblquote  said Harry loudly, and everyone in the class turned to look at him. \ldblquote I\rquote m not feeling well.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Professor Binns raised his eyes from his notes, looking amazed, as always, to find the room in front of him full of people.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Not feeling well?\rdblquote  he repeated hazily.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Not at all well,\rdblquote  said Harry firmly, getting to his feet while con\-cealing Hedwig behind his back. \ldblquote So I think I\rquote ll need to go to the hos\-pital wing.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes,\rdblquote  said Professor Binns, clearly very much wrong-footed. \ldblquote Yes \'85 yes, hospital wing \'85 well, off you go, then, Perkins \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Once outside the room Harry returned Hedwig to his shoulder and hurried off up the corridor, pausing to think only when he was out of sight of Binns\rquote s door. His first choice of somebody to cure Hedwig would have been Hagrid, of course, but as he had no idea where Hagrid was, his only remaining option was to find Professor Grubbly-Plank and hope she would help.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He peered out of a window at the blustery, overcast grounds. There was no sign of her anywhere near Hagrid\rquote s cabin; if she was not teach\-ing, she was probably in the staffroom. He set off downstairs, Hedwig hooting feebly as she swayed on his shoulder.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Two stone gargoyles flanked the staffroom door. As Harry ap\-proached, one of them croaked, \ldblquote You should be in class, sunny Jim.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote This is urgent,\rdblquote  said Harry curtly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ooooh, \i urgent,\i0  is it?\rdblquote  said the other gargoyle in a high-pitched voice. \ldblquote Well, that\rquote s put \i us\i0  in our place, hasn\rquote t it?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
