\lang1033\ldblquote Er \'85 have you been taking \i all\i0  the clothes Hermione\rquote s been leav\-ing out?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh no, sir,\rdblquote  said Dobby happily, \ldblquote Dobby has been taking some for Winky too, sir.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, how is Winky?\rdblquote  asked Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Dobby\rquote s ears drooped slightly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Winky is still drinking lots, sir,\rdblquote  he said sadly, his enormous round green eyes, large as tennis balls, downcast. \ldblquote She still does not care for clothes, Harry Potter. Nor do the other house-elves. None of them will clean Gryffindor Tower anymore, not with the hats and socks hid\-den everywhere, they finds them insulting, sir. Dobby does it all him\-self, sir, but Dobby does not mind, sir, for he always hopes to meet Harry Potter and tonight, sir, he has got his wish!\rdblquote  Dobby sank into a deep bow again. \ldblquote But Harry Potter does not seem happy,\rdblquote  Dobby went on, straightening up again and looking timidly at Harry. \ldblquote Dobby heard him muttering in his sleep. Was Harry Potter having bad dreams?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Not really bad,\rdblquote  said Harry, yawning and rubbing his eyes. \ldblquote I\rquote ve had worse.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The elf surveyed Harry out of his vast, orblike eyes. Then he said very seriously, his ears drooping, \ldblquote Dobby wishes he could help Harry Potter, for Harry Potter set Dobby free and Dobby is much, much happier now. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry smiled.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You can\rquote t help me, Dobby, but thanks for the offer. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He bent and picked up his Potions book. He\rquote d have to try and fin\-ish the essay tomorrow. He closed the book and as he did so the fire\-light illuminated the thin white scars on the back of his hand \emdash  the result of his detention with Umbridge.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Wait a moment \emdash  there \i is\i0  something you can do for me, Dobby,\rdblquote  said Harry slowly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The elf looked around, beaming.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Name it, Harry Potter, sir!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I need to find a place where twenty-eight people can practice De\-fense Against the Dark Arts without being discovered by any of the teachers. Especially,\rdblquote  Harry clenched his hand on the book, so that the scars shone pearly white, \ldblquote Professor Umbridge.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He expected the elf\rquote s smile to vanish, his ears to droop; he expected him to say that this was impossible, or else that he would try, but his hopes were not high. \'85 What he had not expected was for Dobby to give a little skip, his ears waggling happily, and clap his hands together.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Dobby knows the perfect place, sir!\rdblquote  he said happily. \ldblquote Dobby heard tell of it from the other house-elves when he came to Hogwarts, sir. It is known by us as the Come and Go Room, sir, or else as the Room of Requirement!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Why?\rdblquote  said Harry curiously.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Because it is a room that a person can only enter,\rdblquote  said Dobby se\-riously, \ldblquote when they have real need of it. Sometimes it is there, and sometimes it is not, but when it appears, it is always equipped for the\lang3081  \lang1033 seeker\rquote s needs. Dobby has used it, sir,\rdblquote  said the elf, dropping his voice and looking guilty, \ldblquote when Winky has been very drunk. He has hidden her in the Room of Requirement and he has found antidotes to butterbeer there, and a nice elf-sized bed to settle her on while she sleeps it off, sir. \'85 And Dobby knows Mr. Filch has found extra cleaning materials there when he has run short, sir, and \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\emdash  and if you really needed a bathroom,\rdblquote  said Harry, suddenly re\-membering something Dumbledore had said at the Yule Ball the pre\-vious Christmas, \ldblquote would it fill itself with chamber pots?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Dobby expects so, sir,\rdblquote  said Dobby, nodding earnestly. \ldblquote It is a most amazing room, sir.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote How many people know about it?\rdblquote  said Harry, sitting up straighter in his chair.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Very few, sir. Mostly people stumbles across it when they needs it, sir, but often they never finds it again, for they do not know that it is always there waiting to be called into service, sir.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It sounds brilliant,\rdblquote  said Harry, his heart racing. \ldblquote It sounds per\-fect, Dobby. When can you show me where it is?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Anytime, Harry Potter, sir,\rdblquote  said Dobby, looking delighted at Harry\rquote s enthusiasm. \ldblquote We could go now, if you like!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 For a moment Harry was tempted to go now; he was halfway out of his seat, intending to hurry upstairs for his Invisibility Cloak when, not for the first time, a voice very much like Hermione\rquote s whispered in his ear: \i reckless.\i0  It was, after all, very late, he was exhausted and had Snape\rquote s essay to finish.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Not tonight, Dobby,\rdblquote  said Harry reluctantly, sinking back into his chair. \ldblquote This is really important. \'85 I don\rquote t want to blow it, it\rquote ll need proper planning. \'85 Listen, can you just tell me exactly where this Room of Requirement is and how to get in there?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\par
\lang1033 Their robes billowed and swirled around them as they splashed across the flooded vegetable patch to double Herbology, where they could\lang3081  \lang1033 hardly hear what Professor Sprout was saying over the hammering of raindrops hard as hailstones on the greenhouse roof. The afternoon\rquote s Care of Magical Creatures lesson was to be relocated from the storm-swept grounds to a free classroom on the ground floor and, to their intense relief, Angelina sought out her team at lunch to tell them that Quidditch practice was canceled.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Good,\rdblquote  said Harry quietly, when she told him, \ldblquote because we\rquote ve found somewhere to have our first Defense meeting. Tonight, eight o\rquote clock, seventh floor opposite that tapestry of Barnabas the Barmy being clubbed by those trolls. Can you tell Katie and Alicia?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She looked slightly taken aback but promised to tell the others; Harry returned hungrily to his sausages and mash. When he looked up to take a drink of pumpkin juice, he found Hermione watching him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What?\rdblquote  he said thickly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well \'85 it\rquote s just that Dobby\rquote s plans aren\rquote t always that safe. Don\rquote t you remember when he lost you all the bones in your arm?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote This room isn\rquote t just some mad idea of Dobby\rquote s; Dumbledore knows about it too, he mentioned it to me at the Yule Ball.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione\rquote s expression cleared.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Dumbledore told you about it?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Just in passing,\rdblquote  said Harry, shrugging.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh well, that\rquote s all right then,\rdblquote  said Hermione briskly and she raised no more objections.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Together with Ron they had spent most of the day seeking out those people who had signed their names to the list in the Hog\rquote s Head and telling them where to meet that evening. Somewhat to Harry\rquote s disappointment, it was Ginny who managed to find Cho Chang and her friend first; however, by the end of dinner he was confident that the news had been passed to every one of the twenty-five people who had turned up in the Hog\rquote s Head.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 At half-past seven Harry, Ron, and Hermione left the Gryffindor\lang3081  \lang1033 common room, Harry clutching a certain piece of aged parchment in his hand. Fifth years were allowed to be out in the corridors until nine o\rquote clock, but all three of them kept looking around nervously as they made their way up to the seventh floor.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hold it,\rdblquote  said Harry warningly, unfolding the piece of parchment at the top of the last staircase, tapping it with his wand, and mutter\-ing, \ldblquote I solemnly swear that I am up to no good.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 A map of Hogwarts appeared upon the blank surface of the parch\-ment. Tiny black moving dots, labeled with names, showed where various people were.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Filch is on the second floor,\rdblquote  said Harry, holding the map close to his eyes and scanning it closely, \ldblquote and Mrs. Norris is on the fourth.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And Umbridge?\rdblquote  said Hermione anxiously.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote In her office,\rdblquote  said Harry, pointing. \ldblquote Okay, let\rquote s go.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They hurried along the corridor to the place Dobby had described to Harry, a stretch of blank wall opposite an enormous tapestry de\-picting Barnabas the Barmy\rquote s foolish attempt to train trolls for the ballet.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Okay,\rdblquote  said Harry quietly, while a moth-eaten troll paused in his relentless clubbing of the would-be ballet teacher to watch. \ldblquote Dobby said to walk past this bit of wall three times, concentrating hard on what we need.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They did so, turning sharply at the window just beyond the blank stretch of wall, then at the man-size vase on its other side. Ron had screwed up his eyes in concentration, Hermione was whispering something under her breath, Harry\rquote s fists were clenched as he stared ahead of him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\i We need somewhere to learn to fight. \'85\i0  he thought. \i Just give us a place to practice \i0\'85\i  somewhere they can\rquote t find us\i0  \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry,\rdblquote  said Hermione sharply, as they wheeled around after their third walk past.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 A highly polished door had appeared in the wall. Ron was staring\lang3081  \lang1033 at it, looking slightly wary. Harry reached out, seized the brass handle, pulled open the door, and led the way into a spacious room lit with flickering torches like those that illuminated the dungeons eight floors below.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The walls were lined with wooden bookcases, and instead of chairs there were large silk cushions on the floor. A set of shelves at the far end of the room carried a range of instruments such as Sneakoscopes, Secrecy Sensors, and a large, cracked Foe-Glass that Harry was sure had hung, the previous year, in the fake Moody\rquote s office.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote These will be good when we\rquote re practicing Stunning,\rdblquote  said Ron enthusiastically, prodding one of the cushions with his foot.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And just look at these books!\rdblquote  said Hermione excitedly, running a finger along the spines of the large leather-bound tomes. \ldblquote\i A Com\-pendium of Common Curses and Their Counter-Actions\i0  \'85 \i The Dark Arts Outsmarted\lang3081\i0  \lang1033\'85 \i Self-Defensive Spellwork\i0  \'85 wow \'85\rdblquote  She looked around at Harry, her face glowing, and he saw that the presence of hundreds of books had finally convinced Hermione that what they were doing was right. \ldblquote Harry, this is wonderful, there\rquote s everything we need here!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And without further ado she slid \i Jinxes for the Jinxed\i0  from its shelf, sank onto the nearest cushion, and began to read.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was a gentle knock on the door. Harry looked around; Ginny, Neville, Lavender, Parvati, and Dean had arrived.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Whoa,\rdblquote  said Dean, staring around, impressed. \ldblquote What is this place?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry began to explain, but before he had finished more people had arrived, and he had to start all over again. By the time eight o\rquote clock arrived, every cushion was occupied. Harry moved across to the door and turned the key protruding from the lock; it clicked in a satisfyingly loud way and everybody fell silent, looking at him. Hermione carefully marked her page of\lang3081  \lang1033\i Jinxes\lang3081  \lang1033 for the Jinxed\i0  and set the book aside.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well,\rdblquote  said Harry, slightly nervously. \ldblquote This is the place we\rquote ve found for practices, and you\rquote ve \emdash  er \emdash  obviously found it okay \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It\rquote s fantastic!\rdblquote  said Cho, and several people murmured their agreement.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It\rquote s bizarre,\rdblquote  said Fred, frowning around at it. \ldblquote We once hid from Filch in here, remember, George? But it was just a broom cupboard then. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hey, Harry, what\rquote s this stuff?\rdblquote  asked Dean from the rear of the room, indicating the Sneakoscopes and the Foe-Glass.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Dark Detectors,\rdblquote  said Harry, stepping between the cushions to reach them. \ldblquote Basically they all show when Dark wizards or enemies are around, but you don\rquote t want to rely on them too much, they can be fooled. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He gazed for a moment into the cracked Foe-Glass; shadowy fig\-ures were moving around inside it, though none was recognizable. He turned his back on it.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, I\rquote ve been thinking about the sort of stuff we ought to do first and \emdash  er \emdash\rdblquote  He noticed a raised hand. \ldblquote What, Hermione?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I think we ought to elect a leader,\rdblquote  said Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry\rquote s leader,\rdblquote  said Cho at once, looking at Hermione as though she were mad, and Harry\rquote s stomach did yet another back flip.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes, but I think we ought to vote on it properly,\rdblquote  said Hermione, unperturbed. \ldblquote It makes it formal and it gives him authority. So \emdash  everyone who thinks Harry ought to be our leader?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Everybody put up their hands, even Zacharias Smith, though he did it very halfheartedly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Er \emdash  right, thanks,\rdblquote  said Harry, who could feel his face burning. \ldblquote And \emdash  \i what,\i0  Hermione?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I also think we ought to have a name,\rdblquote  she said brightly, her hand still in the air. \ldblquote It would promote a feeling of team spirit and unity, don\rquote t you think?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Can we be the Anti-Umbridge League?\rdblquote  said Angelina hopefully.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Or the Ministry of Magic Are Morons Group?\rdblquote  suggested Fred.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I was thinking,\rdblquote  said Hermione, frowning at Fred, \ldblquote more of a name that didn\rquote t tell everyone what we were up to, so we can refer to it safely outside meetings.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The Defense Association?\rdblquote  said Cho. \ldblquote The D.A. for short, so no\-body knows what we\rquote re talking about?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, the D.A.\rquote s good,\rdblquote  said Ginny. \ldblquote Only let\rquote s make it stand for Dumbledore\rquote s Army because that\rquote s the Ministry\rquote s worst fear, isn\rquote t it?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was a good deal of appreciative murmuring and laughter at this.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote All in favor of the D.A.?\rdblquote  said Hermione bossily, kneeling up on her cushion to count. \ldblquote That\rquote s a majority \emdash  motion passed!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She pinned the piece of paper with all of their names on it on the wall and wrote DUMBLEDORE\rquote S ARMY across the top in large letters.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Right,\rdblquote  said Harry, when she had sat down again, \ldblquote shall we get practicing then? I was thinking, the first thing we should do is \i Expel\-liarmus,\i0  you know, the Disarming Charm. I know it\rquote s pretty basic but I\rquote ve found it really useful \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh \i please,\i0\rdblquote  said Zacharias Smith, rolling his eyes and folding his arms. \ldblquote I don\rquote t think \i Expelliarmus\i0  is exactly going to help us against You-Know-Who, do you?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote ve used it against him,\rdblquote  said Harry quietly. \ldblquote It saved my life last June.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Smith opened his mouth stupidly. The rest of the room was very quiet.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But if you think it\rquote s beneath you, you can leave,\rdblquote  Harry said.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Smith did not move. Nor did anybody else.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Okay,\rdblquote  said Harry, his mouth slightly drier than usual with all those eyes upon him, \ldblquote I reckon we should all divide into pairs and practice.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 It felt very odd to be issuing instructions, but not nearly as odd as\lang3081  \lang1033 seeing them followed. Everybody got to their feet at once and divided up. Predictably, Neville was left partnerless.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You can practice with me,\rdblquote  Harry told him. \ldblquote Right \emdash  on the count of three, then \emdash  one, two, three \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The room was suddenly full of shouts of \ldblquote\i Expelliarmus\i0 !\rdblquote : Wands flew in all directions, missed spells hit books on shelves and sent them flying into the air. Harry was too quick for Neville, whose wand went spinning out of his hand, hit the ceiling in a shower of sparks, and landed with a clatter on top of a bookshelf, from which Harry re\-trieved it with a Summoning Charm. Glancing around he thought he had been right to suggest that they practice the basics first; there was a lot of shoddy spellwork going on; many people were not succeeding in disarming their opponents at all, but merely causing them to jump backward a few paces or wince as the feeble spell whooshed over them.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Expelliarmus\i0 !\rdblquote  said Neville, and Harry, caught unawares, felt his wand fly out of his hand.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I DID IT!\rdblquote  said Neville gleefully. \ldblquote I\rquote ve never done it before \emdash  I DID IT!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Good one!\rdblquote  said Harry encouragingly, deciding not to point out that in a real duel situation Neville\rquote s opponent was unlikely to be star\-ing in the opposite direction with his wand held loosely at his side. \ldblquote Listen, Neville, can you take it in turns to practice with Ron and Hermione for a couple of minutes so I can walk around and see how the rest are doing?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry moved off into the middle of the room. Something very odd was happening to Zacharias Smith; every time he opened his mouth to disarm Anthony Goldstein, his own wand would fly out of his hand, yet Anthony did not seem to be making a sound. Harry did not have to look far for the solution of the mystery, however; Fred and George were several feet from Smith and taking it in turns to point their wands at his back.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Sorry, Harry,\rdblquote  said George hastily, when Harry caught his eye. \ldblquote Couldn\rquote t resist\lang3081  \lang1033\'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry walked around the other pairs, trying to correct those who were doing the spell wrong. Ginny was teamed with Michael Corner; she was doing very well, whereas Michael was either very bad or un\-willing to jinx her. Ernie Macmillan was flourishing his wand unnec\-essarily, giving his partner time to get in under his guard; the Creevey brothers were enthusiastic but erratic and mainly responsible for all the books leaping off the shelves around them. Luna Lovegood was similarly patchy, occasionally sending Justin Finch-Fletchley\rquote s wand spinning out of his hand, at other times merely causing his hair to stand on end.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Okay, stop!\rdblquote  Harry shouted. \ldblquote\i Stop\i0 ! \i STOP\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\i I need a whistle,\i0  he thought, and immediately spotted one lying on top of the nearest row of books. He caught it up and blew hard. Every\-one lowered their wands.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote That wasn\rquote t bad,\rdblquote  said Harry, \ldblquote but there\rquote s definite room for im\-provement.\rdblquote  Zacharias Smith glared at him. \ldblquote Let\rquote s try again. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He moved off around the room again, stopping here and there to make suggestions. Slowly the general performance improved. He avoided going near Cho and her friend for a while, but after walking twice around every other pair in the room felt he could not ignore them any longer.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh no,\rdblquote  said Cho rather wildly as he approached. \ldblquote\i Expelliarmious\i0 ! I mean, \i Expellimellius\i0 ! I \emdash  oh, sorry, Marietta!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Her curly-haired friend\rquote s sleeve had caught fire; Marietta extin\-guished it with her own wand and glared at Harry as though it was his fault.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You made me nervous, I was doing all right before then!\rdblquote  Cho told Harry ruefully.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote That was quite good,\rdblquote  Harry lied, but when she raised her eyebrows he said, \ldblquote Well, no, it was lousy, but I know you can do it prop\-erly, I was watching from over there. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She laughed. Her friend Marietta looked at them rather sourly and turned away.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Don\rquote t mind her,\rdblquote  Cho muttered. \ldblquote She doesn\rquote t really want to be here but I made her come with me. Her parents have forbidden her to do anything that might upset Umbridge, you see \emdash  her mum works for the Ministry.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What about your parents?\rdblquote  asked Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, they\rquote ve forbidden me to get on the wrong side of Umbridge too,\rdblquote  said Cho, drawing herself up proudly. \ldblquote But if they think I\rquote m not going to fight You-Know-Who after what happened to Cedric \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She broke off, looking rather confused, and an awkward silence fell between them; Terry Boot\rquote s wand went whizzing past Harry\rquote s ear and hit Alicia Spinnet hard on the nose.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, my father is \i very\i0  supportive of any anti-Ministry action!\rdblquote  said Luna Lovegood proudly from just behind Harry; evidently she had been eavesdropping on his conversation while Justin Finch-Fletchley attempted to disentangle himself from the robes that had flown up over his head. \ldblquote He\rquote s always saying he\rquote d believe anything of Fudge, I mean, the number of goblins Fudge has had assassinated! And of course he uses the Department of Mysteries to develop terrible poisons, which he feeds secretly to anybody who disagrees with him. And then there\rquote s his Umgubular Slashkilter \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Don\rquote t ask,\rdblquote  Harry muttered to Cho as she opened her mouth, looking puzzled. She giggled.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hey, Harry,\rdblquote  Hermione called from the other end of the room, \ldblquote have you checked the time?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He looked down at his watch and received a shock \emdash  it was al\-ready ten past nine, which meant they needed to get back to their common rooms immediately or risk being caught and punished by\lang3081  \lang1033 Filch for being out-of-bounds. He blew his whistle; everybody stopped shouting, \ldblquote\i Expelliarmus\i0 !\rdblquote  and the last couple of wands clat\-tered to the floor.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, that was pretty good,\rdblquote  said Harry, \ldblquote but we\rquote ve overrun, we\rquote d better leave it here. Same time, same place next week?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Sooner!\rdblquote  said Dean Thomas eagerly and many people nodded in agreement.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Angelina, however, said quickly, \ldblquote The Quidditch season\rquote s about to start, we need team practices too!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Let\rquote s say next Wednesday night, then,\rdblquote  said Harry, \ldblquote and we can decide on additional meetings then. \'85 Come on, we\rquote d better get going. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He pulled out the Marauder\rquote s Map again and checked it carefully for signs of teachers on the seventh floor. He let them all leave in threes and fours, watching their tiny dots anxiously to see that they re\-turned safely to their dormitories: the Hufflepuffs to the basement corridor that also led to the kitchens, the Ravenclaws to a tower on the west side of the castle, and the Gryffindors along the corridor to the seventh floor and the Fat Lady\rquote s portrait.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote That was really, really good, Harry,\rdblquote  said Hermione, when finally it was just her, Harry, and Ron left.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, it was!\rdblquote  said Ron enthusiastically, as they slipped out of the door and watched it melt back into stone behind them. \ldblquote Did you see me disarm Hermione, Harry?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Only once,\rdblquote  said Hermione, stung. \ldblquote I got you loads more than you got me \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I did not only get you once, I got you at least three times \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, if you\rquote re counting the one where you tripped over your own feet and knocked the wand out of my hand \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They argued all the way back to the common room, but Harry was not listening to them. He had one eye on the Marauder\rquote s Map, but he was also thinking of how Cho had said he made her nervous. \'85\lang3081\par
