Harry felt as though he were carrying some kind of talisman inside his chest over the following two weeks, a glowing se\-cret that supported him through Umbridge\rquote s classes and even made it possible for him to smile blandly as he looked into her horrible bulging eyes. He and the D.A. were resisting her under her very nose, doing the very thing that she and the Ministry most feared, and when\-ever he was supposed to be reading Wilbert Slinkhard\rquote s book during her lessons he dwelled instead on satisfying memories of their most re\-cent meetings, remembering how Neville had successfully disarmed Hermione, how Colin Creevey had mastered the Impediment Jinx af\-ter three meetings\rquote  hard effort, how Parvati Patil had produced such a good Reductor Curse that she had reduced the table carrying all the Sneakoscopes to dust.\par
He was finding it almost impossible to fix a regular night of the week for D.A. meetings, as they had to accommodate three separate Quidditch teams\rquote  practices, which were often rearranged depending on the weather conditions; but Harry was not sorry about this, he had a feeling that it was probably better to keep the timing of their meetings\lang3081  \lang1033 unpredictable. If anyone was watching them, it would be hard to make out a pattern.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione soon devised a very clever method of communicating the time and date of the next meeting to all the members in case they needed to change it at short notice, because it would look so suspi\-cious if people from different Houses were seen crossing the Great Hall to talk to each other too often. She gave each of the members of the D.A. a fake Galleon (Ron became very excited when he saw the basket at first, convinced that she was actually giving out gold).\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You see the numerals around the edge of the coins?\rdblquote  Hermione said, holding one up for examination at the end of their fourth meet\-ing. The coin gleamed fat and yellow in the light from the torches. \ldblquote On real Galleons that\rquote s just a serial number referring to the goblin who cast the coin. On these fake coins, though, the numbers will change to reflect the time and date of the next meeting. The coins will grow hot when the date changes, so if you\rquote re carrying them in a pocket you\rquote ll be able to feel them. We take one each, and when Harry sets the date of the next meeting he\rquote ll change the numbers on \i his\i0  coin, and be\-cause I\rquote ve put a Protean Charm on them, they\rquote ll all change to mimic his.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 A blank silence greeted Hermione\rquote s words. She looked around at all the faces upturned to her, rather disconcerted.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well \emdash  I thought it was a good idea,\rdblquote  she said uncertainly, \ldblquote I mean, even if Umbridge asked us to turn out our pockets, there\rquote s nothing fishy about carrying a Galleon, is there? But\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 well, if you don\rquote t want to use them \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
