Hermione plowed her way back to Hagrid\rquote s cabin through two feet of snow on Sunday morning. Harry and Ron wanted to go with her, but their mountain of homework had reached an alarm\-ing height again, so they grudgingly remained in the common room, trying to ignore the gleeful shouts drifting up from the grounds out\-side, where students were enjoying themselves skating on the frozen lake, tobogganing, and worst of all, bewitching snowballs to zoom up to Gryffindor Tower and rap hard on the windows.\par
