\lang1033\ldblquote Okay,\rdblquote  he said, calling them all to order. \ldblquote I thought this evening we should just go over the things we\rquote ve done so far, because it\rquote s the last\lang3081  \lang1033 meeting before the holidays and there\rquote s no point starting anything new right before a three-week break \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We\rquote re not doing anything new?\rdblquote  said Zacharias Smith, in a dis\-gruntled whisper loud enough to carry through the room. \ldblquote If I\rquote d known that, I wouldn\rquote t have come. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We\rquote re all really sorry Harry didn\rquote t tell you, then,\rdblquote  said Fred loudly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Several people sniggered. Harry saw Cho laughing and felt the fa\-miliar swooping sensation in his stomach, as though he had missed a step going downstairs.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We can practice in pairs,\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote We\rquote ll start with the Im\-pediment Jinx, just for ten minutes, then we can get out the cushions and try Stunning again.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They all divided up obediently; Harry partnered Neville as usual. The room was soon full of intermittent cries of \ldblquote\i Impedimenta\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081  \lang1033 People froze for a minute or so, during which their partners would stare aimlessly around the room watching other pairs at work, then would unfreeze and take their turn at the jinx.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Neville had improved beyond all recognition. After a while, when Harry had unfrozen three times in a row, he had Neville join Ron and Hermione again so that he could walk around the room and watch the others. When he passed Cho she beamed at him; he resisted the temp\-tation to walk past her several more times.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 After ten minutes on the Impediment Jinx, they laid out cushions all over the floor and started practicing Stunning again. Space was really too confined to allow them all to work this spell at once; half the group observed the others for a while, then swapped over. Harry felt himself positively swelling with pride as he watched them all. True, Neville did Stun Padma Patil rather than Dean, at whom he had been aiming, but it was a much closer miss than usual, and everybody else had made enormous progress.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 At the end of an hour, Harry called a halt.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote re getting really good,\rdblquote  he said, beaming around at them. \ldblquote When we get back from the holidays we can start doing some of the big stuff\lang3081  \lang1033\emdash  maybe even Patronuses.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was a murmur of excitement. The room began to clear in the usual twos and threes; most people wished Harry a Happy Christmas as they went. Feeling cheerful, he collected up the cushions with Ron and Hermione and stacked them neatly away. Ron and Hermione left before he did; he hung back a little, because Cho was still there and he was hoping to receive a Merry Christmas from her.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No, you go on,\rdblquote  he heard her say to her friend Marietta, and his heart gave a jolt that seemed to take it into the region of his Adam\rquote s apple.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He pretended to be straightening the cushion pile. He was quite sure they were alone now and waited for her to speak. Instead, he heard a hearty sniff.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He turned and saw Cho standing in the middle of the room, tears pouring down her face.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Wha \emdash  ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He didn\rquote t know what to do. She was simply standing there, crying silently.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What\rquote s up?\rdblquote  he said feebly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She shook her head and wiped her eyes on her sleeve. \ldblquote I\rquote m \emdash  sorry,\rdblquote  she said thickly. \ldblquote I suppose \'85 it\rquote s just\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 learning all this stuff. \'85 It just makes me \'85 wonder whether \'85 if \i he\rquote d\i0  known it all \'85 he\rquote d still be alive. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry\rquote s heart sank right back past its usual spot and settled some\-where around his navel. He ought to have known. She wanted to talk about Cedric.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He did know this stuff,\rdblquote  Harry said heavily. \ldblquote He was really good at it, or he could never have got to the middle of that maze. But if Voldemort really wants to kill you, you don\rquote t stand a chance.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She hiccuped at the sound of Voldemort\rquote s name, but stared at Harry without flinching.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i You \i0 survived when you were just a baby,\rdblquote  she said quietly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, well,\rdblquote  said Harry wearily, moving toward the door, \ldblquote I dunno why, nor does anyone else, so it\rquote s nothing to be proud of.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh don\rquote t go!\rdblquote  said Cho, sounding tearful again. \ldblquote I\rquote m really sorry to get all upset like this. \'85 I didn\rquote t mean to. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She hiccuped again. She was very pretty even when her eyes were red and puffy. Harry felt thoroughly miserable. He\rquote d have been so pleased just with a Merry Christmas. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I know it must be horrible for you,\rdblquote  she said, mopping her eyes on her sleeve again. \ldblquote Me mentioning Cedric, when you saw him die. \'85 I suppose you just want to forget about it. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry did not say anything to this; it was quite true, but he felt heartless saying it.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote re a r-really good teacher, you know,\rdblquote  said Cho, with a watery smile. \ldblquote I\rquote ve never been able to Stun anything before.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Thanks,\rdblquote  said Harry awkwardly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They looked at each other for a long moment. Harry felt a burning desire to run from the room and, at the same time, a complete inabil\-ity to move his feet.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Mistletoe,\rdblquote  said Cho quietly, pointing at the ceiling over his head.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah,\rdblquote  said Harry. His mouth was very dry. \ldblquote It\rquote s probably full of nargles, though.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What are nargles?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No idea,\rdblquote  said Harry. She had moved closer. His brain seemed to have been Stunned. \ldblquote You\rquote d have to ask Loony. Luna, I mean.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Cho made a funny noise halfway between a sob and a laugh. She was even nearer him now. He could have counted the freckles on her nose.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I really like you, Harry.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He could not think. A tingling sensation was spreading throughout him, paralyzing his arms, legs, and brain.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She was much too close. He could see every tear clinging to her eyelashes. \'85\lang3081\par
\par
\lang1033 He returned to the common room half an hour later to find Hermione and Ron in the best seats by the fire; nearly everybody else had gone to bed. Hermione was writing a very long letter; she had al\-ready filled half a roll of parchment, which was dangling from the edge of the table. Ron was lying on the hearthrug, trying to finish his Transfiguration homework.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What kept you?\rdblquote  he asked, as Harry sank into the armchair next to Hermione\rquote s.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry did not answer. He was in a state of shock. Half of him wanted to tell Ron and Hermione what had just happened, but the other half wanted to take the secret with him to the grave.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Are you all right, Harry?\rdblquote  Hermione asked, peering at him over the tip of her quill.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry gave a halfhearted shrug. In truth, he didn\rquote t know whether he was all right or not. \ldblquote What\rquote s up?\rdblquote  said Ron, hoisting himself up on his elbow to get a clearer view of Harry. \ldblquote What\rquote s happened?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry didn\rquote t quite know how to set about telling them, and still wasn\rquote t sure whether he wanted to. Just as he had decided not to say anything, Hermione took matters out of his hands.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Is it Cho?\rdblquote  she asked in a businesslike way. \ldblquote Did she corner you af\-ter the meeting?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Numbly surprised, Harry nodded. Ron sniggered, breaking off when Hermione caught his eye.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So \emdash  er \emdash  what did she want?\rdblquote  he asked in a mock casual voice.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote She \emdash\rdblquote  Harry began, rather hoarsely; he cleared his throat and tried again. \ldblquote She \emdash  er \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Did you kiss?\rdblquote  asked Hermione briskly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron sat up so fast that he sent his ink bottle flying all over the rug. Disregarding this completely he stared avidly at Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well?\rdblquote  he demanded.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry looked from Ron\rquote s expression of mingled curiosity and hilar\-ity to Hermione\rquote s slight frown, and nodded.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote HA!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron made a triumphant gesture with his fist and went into a rau\-cous peal of laughter that made several timid-looking second years over beside the window jump. A reluctant grin spread over Harry\rquote s face as he watched Ron rolling around on the hearthrug. Hermione gave Ron a look of deep disgust and returned to her letter.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well?\rdblquote  Ron said finally, looking up at Harry. \ldblquote How was it?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry considered for a moment.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Wet,\rdblquote  he said truthfully.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron made a noise that might have indicated jubilation or disgust, it was hard to tell.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Because she was crying,\rdblquote  Harry continued heavily.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh,\rdblquote  said Ron, his smile fading slightly. \ldblquote Are you that bad at kissing?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Dunno,\rdblquote  said Harry, who hadn\rquote t considered this, and immediately felt rather worried. \ldblquote Maybe I am.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Of course you\rquote re not,\rdblquote  said Hermione absently, still scribbling away at her letter.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote How do you know?\rdblquote  said Ron in a sharp voice.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Because Cho spends half her time crying these days,\rdblquote  said Her\-mione vaguely. \ldblquote She does it at mealtimes, in the loos, all over the place.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote d think a bit of kissing would cheer her up,\rdblquote  said Ron, grinning.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ron,\rdblquote  said Hermione in a dignified voice, dipping the point of her\lang3081  \lang1033 quill into her ink pot, \ldblquote you are the most insensitive wart I have ever had the misfortune to meet.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What\rquote s that supposed to mean?\rdblquote  said Ron indignantly. \ldblquote What sort of person cries while someone\rquote s kissing them?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah,\rdblquote  said Harry, slightly desperately, \ldblquote who does?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione looked at the pair of them with an almost pitying ex\-pression on her face.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Don\rquote t you understand how Cho\rquote s feeling at the moment?\rdblquote  she asked.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No,\rdblquote  said Harry and Ron together.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione sighed and laid down her quill.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, obviously, she\rquote s feeling very sad, because of Cedric dying. Then I expect she\rquote s feeling confused because she liked Cedric and now she likes Harry, and she can\rquote t work out who she likes best. Then she\rquote ll be feeling guilty, thinking it\rquote s an insult to Cedric\rquote s memory to be kiss\-ing Harry at all, and she\rquote ll be worrying about what everyone else might say about her if she starts going out with Harry. And she prob\-ably can\rquote t work out what her feelings toward Harry are anyway, be\-cause he was the one who was with Cedric when Cedric died, so that\rquote s all very mixed up and painful. Oh, and she\rquote s afraid she\rquote s going to be thrown off the Ravenclaw Quidditch team because she\rquote s been flying so badly.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 A slightly stunned silence greeted the end of this speech, then Ron said, \ldblquote One person can\rquote t feel all that at once, they\rquote d explode.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Just because you\rquote ve got the emotional range of a teaspoon doesn\rquote t mean we all have,\rdblquote  said Hermione nastily, picking up her quill again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote She was the one who started it,\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote I wouldn\rquote t\rquote ve \emdash  she just sort of came at me \emdash  and next thing she\rquote s crying all over me \emdash  I didn\rquote t know what to do \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Don\rquote t blame you, mate,\rdblquote  said Ron, looking alarmed at the very thought.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You just had to be nice to her,\rdblquote  said Hermione, looking up anx\-iously. \ldblquote You were, weren\rquote t you?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well,\rdblquote  said Harry, an unpleasant heat creeping up his face, \ldblquote I sort of\lang3081  \lang1033\emdash  patted her on the back a bit.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione looked as though she was restraining herself from rolling her eyes with extreme difficulty.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, I suppose it could have been worse,\rdblquote  she said. \ldblquote Are you go\-ing to see her again?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote ll have to, won\rquote t I?\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote We\rquote ve got D.A. meetings, haven\rquote t we?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You know what I mean,\rdblquote  said Hermione impatiently.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry said nothing. Hermione\rquote s words opened up a whole new vista of frightening possibilities. He tried to imagine going somewhere with Cho \emdash  Hogsmeade, perhaps \emdash  and being alone with her for hours at a time. Of course, she would have been expecting him to ask her out after what had just happened. \'85 The thought made his stomach clench painfully.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh well,\rdblquote  said Hermione distantly, buried in her letter once more, \ldblquote you\rquote ll have plenty of opportunities to ask her. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What if he doesn\rquote t want to ask her?\rdblquote  said Ron, who had been watching Harry with an unusually shrewd expression on his face.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Don\rquote t be silly,\rdblquote  said Hermione vaguely, \ldblquote Harry\rquote s liked her for ages, haven\rquote t you, Harry?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He did not answer. Yes, he had liked Cho for ages, but whenever he had imagined a scene involving the two of them it had always featured a Cho who was enjoying herself, as opposed to a Cho who was sob\-bing uncontrollably into his shoulder.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Who\rquote re you writing the novel to anyway?\rdblquote  Ron asked Hermione, trying to read the bit of parchment now trailing on the floor. Hermione hitched it up out of sight.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Viktor.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Krum\i0 ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote How many other Viktors do we know?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron said nothing, but looked disgruntled. They sat in silence for another twenty minutes, Ron finishing his Transfiguration essay with many snorts of impatience and crossings-out, Hermione writing steadily to the very end of the parchment, rolling it up carefully and sealing it, and Harry staring into the fire, wishing more than anything that Sirius\rquote s head would appear there and give him some advice about girls. But the fire merely crackled lower and lower, until the red-hot embers crumbled into ash and, looking around, Harry saw that they were, yet again, the last in the common room.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, \rquote night,\rdblquote  said Hermione, yawning widely, and she set off up the girls\rquote  staircase.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What does she see in Krum?\rdblquote  Ron demanded as he and Harry climbed the boys\rquote  stairs.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well,\rdblquote  said Harry, considering the matter, \ldblquote I s\rquote pose he\rquote s older, isn\rquote t he \'85 and he\rquote s an international Quidditch player. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, but apart from that,\rdblquote  said Ron, sounding aggravated. \ldblquote I mean he\rquote s a grouchy git, isn\rquote t he?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Bit grouchy, yeah,\rdblquote  said Harry, whose thoughts were still on Cho.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They pulled off their robes and put on pajamas in silence; Dean, Seamus, and Neville were already asleep. Harry put his glasses on his bedside table and got into bed but did not pull the hangings closed around his four-poster; instead he stared at the patch of starry sky vis\-ible through the window next to Neville\rquote s bed. If he had known, this time last night, that in twenty-four hours\rquote  time he would have kissed Cho Chang \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote  \rquote Night,\rdblquote  grunted Ron, from somewhere to his right.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote  \rquote Night,\rdblquote  said Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Maybe next time \'85 if there was a next time \'85 she\rquote d be a bit happier. He ought to have asked her out; she had probably been\lang3081  \lang1033 expecting it and was now really angry with him \'85 or was she lying in bed, still crying about Cedric? He did not know what to think. Hermione\rquote s explanation had made it all seem more complicated rather than easier to understand.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\i That\rquote s what they should teach us here, \i0 he thought, turning over onto his side, \i how girls\rquote  brains work \'85 it\rquote d be more useful than Divination anyway. \'85\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033 Neville snuffled in his sleep. An owl hooted somewhere out in the night.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry dreamed he was back in the D.A. room. Cho was accusing him of luring her there under false pretenses; she said that he had promised her a hundred and fifty Chocolate Frog cards if she showed up. Harry protested. \'85 Cho shouted, \ldblquote\i Cedric gave me loads of Choco\-late Frog cards, look\i0 !\rdblquote  And she pulled out fistfuls of cards from inside her robes and threw them into the air, and then turned into Hermione, who said, \ldblquote\i You did promise her, you know, Harry. \'85 I think you\rquote d better give her something else instead. \'85 How about your Firebolt\i0 ?\rdblquote  And Harry was protesting that he could not give Cho his Firebolt because Umbridge had it, and anyway the whole thing was ridiculous, he\rquote d only come to the D.A. room to put up some Christ\-mas baubles shaped like Dobby\rquote s head. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The dream changed. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 His body felt smooth, powerful, and flexible. He was gliding be\-tween shining metal bars, across dark, cold stone. \'85 He was flat against the floor, sliding along on his belly. \'85 It was dark, yet he could see objects around him shimmering in strange, vibrant colors. \'85 He was turning his head. \'85 At first glance, the corridor was empty\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 but no \'85 a man was sitting on the floor ahead, his chin drooping onto his chest, his outline gleaming in the dark. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry put out his tongue. \'85 He tasted the man\rquote s scent on the air. \'85 He was alive but drowsing \'85 sitting in front of a door at the end of the corridor \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry longed to bite the man \'85 but he must master the impulse. \'85 He had more important work to do. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But the man was stirring \'85 a silvery cloak fell from his legs as he jumped to his feet; and Harry saw his vibrant, blurred outline tower\-ing above him, saw a wand withdrawn from a belt. \'85 He had no choice. \'85 He reared high from the floor and struck once, twice, three times, plunging his fangs deeply into the man\rquote s flesh, feeling his ribs splinter beneath his jaws, feeling the warm gush of blood. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The man was yelling in pain \'85 then he fell silent. \'85 He slumped backward against the wall. \'85 Blood was splattering onto the floor. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 His forehead hurt terribly. \'85 It was aching fit to burst. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry! HARRY!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He opened his eyes. Every inch of his body was covered in icy sweat; his bedcovers were twisted all around him like a straitjacket; he felt as though a white-hot poker was being applied to his forehead.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Harry\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron was standing over him looking extremely frightened. There were more figures at the foot of Harry\rquote s bed. He clutched his head in his hands; the pain was blinding him. \'85 He rolled right over and vomited over the edge of the mattress.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He\rquote s really ill,\rdblquote  said a scared voice. \ldblquote Should we call someone?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry! \i Harry\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He had to tell Ron, it was very important that he tell him. \'85 Tak\-ing great gulps of air, Harry pushed himself up in bed, willing himself not to throw up again, the pain half-blinding him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Your dad,\rdblquote  he panted, his chest heaving. \ldblquote Your dad\rquote s \'85 been attacked. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What?\rdblquote  said Ron uncomprehendingly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Your dad! He\rquote s been bitten, it\rquote s serious, there was blood everywhere. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m going for help,\rdblquote  said the same scared voice, and Harry heard footsteps running out of the dormitory.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry, mate,\rdblquote  said Ron uncertainly, \ldblquote you\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 you were just dreaming. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No!\rdblquote  said Harry furiously; it was crucial that Ron understand. \ldblquote It wasn\rquote t a dream \'85 not an ordinary dream. \'85 I was there, I saw it. \'85 I \i did\i0  it. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He could hear Seamus and Dean muttering but did not care. The pain in his forehead was subsiding slightly, though he was still sweat\-ing and shivering feverishly. He retched again and Ron leapt backward out of the way.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry, you\rquote re not well,\rdblquote  he said shakily. \ldblquote Neville\rquote s gone for help. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m fine!\rdblquote  Harry choked, wiping his mouth on his pajamas and shaking uncontrollably. \ldblquote There\rquote s nothing wrong with me, it\rquote s your dad you\rquote ve got to worry about \emdash  we need to find out where he is \emdash  he\rquote s bleeding like mad \emdash  I was \emdash  it was a huge snake. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He tried to get out of bed but Ron pushed him back into it; Dean and Seamus were still whispering somewhere nearby. Whether one minute passed or ten, Harry did not know; he simply sat there shak\-ing, feeling the pain recede very slowly from his scar. \'85 Then there were hurried footsteps coming up the stairs, and he heard Neville\rquote s voice again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Over here, Professor \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Professor McGonagall came hurrying into the dormitory in her tar\-tan dressing gown, her glasses perched lopsidedly on the bridge of her bony nose.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What is it, Potter? Where does it hurt?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He had never been so pleased to see her; it was a member of the Or\-der of the Phoenix he needed now, not someone fussing over him and prescribing useless potions.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It\rquote s Ron\rquote s dad,\rdblquote  he said, sitting up again. \ldblquote He\rquote s been attacked by a snake and it\rquote s serious, I saw it happen.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What do you mean, you saw it happen?\rdblquote  said Professor McGona\-gall, her dark eyebrows contracting.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I don\rquote t know. \'85 I was asleep and then I was there. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You mean you dreamed this?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No!\rdblquote  said Harry angrily. Would none of them understand? \ldblquote I was having a dream at first about something completely different, some\-thing stupid \'85 and then this interrupted it. It was real, I didn\rquote t imag\-ine it, Mr. Weasley was asleep on the floor and he was attacked by a gigantic snake, there was a load of blood, he collapsed, someone\rquote s got to find out where he is. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Professor McGonagall was gazing at him through her lopsided spectacles as though horrified at what she was seeing.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m not lying, and I\rquote m not mad!\rdblquote  Harry told her, his voice rising to a shout. \ldblquote I tell you, I saw it happen!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I believe you, Potter,\rdblquote  said Professor McGonagall curtly. \ldblquote Put on your dressing-gown \emdash  we\rquote re going to see the headmaster.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
