\lang1033 They had arrived outside a large, old-fashioned, red brick depart\-ment store called Purge and Dowse Ltd. The place had a shabby, mis\-erable air; the window displays consisted of a few chipped dummies with their wigs askew, standing at random and modeling fashions at least ten years out of date. Large signs on all the dusty doors read CLOSED FOR REFURBISHMENT. Harry distinctly heard a large woman laden with plastic shopping bags say to her friend as they passed, \ldblquote It\rquote s \i never\i0  open, that place. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
