\lang1033 They nodded, clustering around her; Moody gave Harry another shove between the shoulder blades to urge him forward and Tonks leaned close to the glass, looking up at the very ugly dummy and said, her breath steaming up the glass, \ldblquote Wotcher \'85 We\rquote re here to see Arthur Weasley.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 For a split second, Harry thought how absurd it was for Tonks to ex\-pect the dummy to hear her talking that quietly through a sheet of glass, when there were buses rumbling along behind her and all the racket of a street full of shoppers. Then he reminded himself that dum\-mies could not hear anyway. Next second his mouth opened in shock as the dummy gave a tiny nod, beckoned its jointed finger, and Tonks had seized Ginny and Mrs. Weasley by the elbows, stepped right through the glass and vanished.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Fred, George, and Ron stepped after them; Harry glanced around at the jostling crowd; not one of them seemed to have a glance to spare\lang3081  \lang1033 for window displays as ugly as Purge and Dowse Ltd.\rquote s, nor did any of them seem to have noticed that six people had just melted into thin air in front of them.\lang3081\par
