\lang1033\ldblquote Realized what?\rdblquote  asked Snape sharply.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry did not answer at once; he was still savoring the moment of blinding realization as he rubbed his forehead. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He had been dreaming about a windowless corridor ending in a locked door for months, without once realizing that it was a real place. Now, seeing the memory again, he knew that all along he had been dreaming about the corridor down which he had run with Mr. Weasley on the twelfth of August as they hurried to the courtrooms in the Ministry. It was the corridor leading to the Department of Mys\-teries, and Mr. Weasley had been there the night that he had been at\-tacked by Voldemort\rquote s snake. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He looked up at Snape.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What\rquote s in the Department of Mysteries?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What did you say?\rdblquote  Snape asked quietly and Harry saw, with deep satisfaction, that Snape was unnerved.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I said, what\rquote s in the Department of Mysteries, \i sir\i0 ?\rdblquote  Harry said.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And why,\rdblquote  said Snape slowly, \ldblquote would you ask such a thing?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Because,\rdblquote  said Harry, watching Snape closely for a reaction, \ldblquote that corridor I\rquote ve just seen \emdash  I\rquote ve been dreaming about it for months \emdash  I\rquote ve just recognized it \emdash  it leads to the Department of Mysteries \'85 and I think Voldemort wants something from \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i I have told you not to say the Dark Lord\rquote s name\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They glared at each other. Harry\rquote s scar seared again, but he did not care. Snape looked agitated. When he spoke again he sounded as though he was trying to appear cool and unconcerned.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote There are many things in the Department of Mysteries, Potter, few of which you would understand and none of which concern you, do I make myself plain?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes,\rdblquote  Harry said, still rubbing his prickling scar, which was be\-coming more painful.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I want you back here same time on Wednesday, and we will con\-tinue work then.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Fine,\rdblquote  said Harry. He was desperate to get out of Snape\rquote s office and find Ron and Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You are to rid your mind of all emotion every night before sleep \emdash  empty it, make it blank and calm, you understand?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes,\rdblquote  said Harry, who was barely listening.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And be warned, Potter \'85 I shall know if you have not prac\-ticed \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Right,\rdblquote  Harry mumbled. He picked up his schoolbag, swung it over his shoulder, and hurried toward the office door. As he opened it he glanced back at Snape, who had his back to Harry and was scoop\-ing his own thoughts out of the Pensieve with the tip of his wand and replacing them carefully inside his own head. Harry left without an\-other word, closing the door carefully behind him, his scar still throb\-bing painfully.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry found Ron and Hermione in the library, where they were working on Umbridge\rquote s most recent ream of homework. Other stu\-dents, nearly all of them fifth years, sat at lamp-lit tables nearby, noses close to books, quills scratching feverishly, while the sky outside the mullioned windows grew steadily blacker. The only other sound was the slight squeaking of one of Madam Pince\rquote s shoes as the librarian prowled the aisles menacingly, breathing down the necks of those touching her precious books.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry felt shivery; his scar was still aching, he felt almost feverish. When he sat down opposite Ron and Hermione he caught sight of\lang3081  \lang1033 himself in the window opposite. He was very white, and his scar seemed to be showing up more clearly than usual.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote How did it go?\rdblquote  Hermione whispered, and then, looking con\-cerned, \ldblquote Are you all right, Harry?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah \'85 fine \'85 I dunno,\rdblquote  said Harry impatiently, wincing as pain shot through his scar again. \ldblquote Listen \'85 I\rquote ve just realized some\-thing. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And he told them what he had just seen and deduced.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So \'85 so, are you saying \'85\rdblquote  whispered Ron, as Madam Pince swept past, squeaking slightly, \ldblquote that the weapon \emdash  the thing You-Know-Who\rquote s after \emdash  is in the Ministry of Magic?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote In the Department of Mysteries, it\rquote s got to be,\rdblquote  Harry whispered. \ldblquote I saw that door when your dad took me down to the courtrooms for my hearing and it\rquote s definitely the same one he was guarding when the snake bit him.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione let out a long, slow sigh. \ldblquote Of course,\rdblquote  she breathed.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Of course what?\rdblquote  said Ron rather impatiently.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Ron, think about it. \'85 Sturgis Podmore was trying to get through a door at the Ministry of Magic. \'85 It must have been that one, it\rquote s too much of a coincidence!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
