\lang1033 With so much to worry about and so much to do \emdash  startling amounts of homework that frequently kept the fifth years working until past midnight, secret D.A. meetings, and regular classes with Snape \emdash  January seemed to be passing alarmingly fast. Before Harry knew it, February had arrived, bringing with it wetter and warmer weather and the prospect of the second Hogsmeade visit of the year. Harry had had very little time to spare on conversations with Cho since they had agreed to visit the village together, but suddenly found himself facing a Valentine\rquote s Day spent entirely in her company.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 On the morning of the fourteenth he dressed particularly carefully. He and Ron arrived at breakfast just in time for the arrival of the post owls. Hedwig was not there \emdash  not that he had expected her \emdash  but Hermione was tugging a letter from the beak of an unfamiliar brown owl as they sat down.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And about time! If it hadn\rquote t come today \'85\rdblquote  she said eagerly, tear\-ing open the envelope and pulling out a small piece of parchment. Her eyes sped from left to right as she read through the message and a grimly pleased expression spread across her face.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Listen, Harry,\rdblquote  she said, looking up at him. \ldblquote This is really impor\-tant. \'85 Do you think you could meet me in the Three Broomsticks around midday?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 I dunno,\rdblquote  said Harry dubiously. \ldblquote Cho might be expect\-ing me to spend the whole day with her. We never said what we were going to do.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, bring her along if you must,\rdblquote  said Hermione urgently. \ldblquote But will you come?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
