\lang1033 The notices had gone up all over the school overnight, but they did not explain how every single person within the castle seemed to know\lang3081  \lang1033 that Dumbledore had overcome two Aurors, the High Inquisitor, the Minister of Magic, and his Junior Assistant to escape. No matter where Harry went within the castle next day, the sole topic of conver\-sation was Dumbledore\rquote s flight, and though some of the details might have gone awry in the retelling (Harry overheard one second-year girl assuring another that Fudge was now lying in St. Mungo\rquote s with a pumpkin for a head), it was surprising how accurate the rest of their information was. Everybody seemed aware, for instance, that Harry and Marietta were the only students to have witnessed the scene in Dumbledore\rquote s office, and as Marietta was now in the hospital wing, Harry found himself besieged with requests to give a firsthand ac\-count wherever he went.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Dumbledore will be back before long,\rdblquote  said Ernie Macmillan con\-fidently on the way back from Herbology after listening intently to Harry\rquote s story. \ldblquote They couldn\rquote t keep him away in our second year and they won\rquote t be able to this time. The Fat Friar told me \'85\rdblquote  He dropped his voice conspiratorially, so that Harry, Ron, and Hermione had to lean closer to him to hear, \ldblquote\'85 that Umbridge tried to get back into his office last night after they\rquote d searched the castle and grounds for him. Couldn\rquote t get past the gargoyle. The Head\rquote s office has sealed itself against her.\rdblquote  Ernie smirked. \ldblquote Apparently she had a right little tantrum. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
