\lang1033 He fell silent. He could hear distant footsteps.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Is that Kreacher coming downstairs?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No,\rdblquote  said Sirius, glancing behind him. \ldblquote It must be somebody your end \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry\rquote s heart skipped several beats.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote d better go!\rdblquote  he said hastily and he pulled his head backward out of Grimmauld Place\rquote s fire. For a moment his head seemed to be re\-volving on his shoulders, and then he found himself kneeling in front of Umbridge\rquote s fire with his head firmly back on, watching the emerald flames flicker and die.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Quickly, quickly!\rdblquote  he heard a wheezy voice mutter right outside the office door. \ldblquote Ah, she\rquote s left it open. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry dived for the Invisibility Cloak and had just managed to pull it back over himself when Filch burst into the office. He looked ab\-solutely delighted about something and was talking to himself fever\-ishly as he crossed the room, pulled open a drawer in Umbridge\rquote s desk, and began rifling through the papers inside it.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Approval for Whipping \'85 Approval for Whipping \'85 I can do it at last. \'85 They\rquote ve had it coming to them for years. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He pulled out a piece of parchment, kissed it, then shuffled rapidly back out of the door, clutching it to his chest.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry leapt to his feet and, making sure that he had his bag and the Invisibility Cloak was completely covering him, he wrenched open the door and hurried out of the office after Filch, who was hobbling along faster than Harry had ever seen him go.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 One landing down from Umbridge\rquote s office and Harry thought it was safe to become visible again; he pulled off the cloak, shoved it in his bag and hurried onward. There was a great deal of shouting and movement coming from the entrance hall. He ran down the marble staircase and found what looked like most of the school assembled there.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 It was just like the night when Trelawney had been sacked. Stu\-dents were standing all around the walls in a great ring (some of them, Harry noticed, covered in a substance that looked very like Stinksap); teachers and ghosts were also in the crowd. Prominent among the on\-lookers were members of the Inquisitorial Squad, who were all look\-ing exceptionally pleased with themselves, and Peeves, who was bobbing overhead, gazed down upon Fred and George, who stood in the middle of the floor with the unmistakable look of two people who had just been cornered.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So!\rdblquote  said Umbridge triumphantly, whom Harry realized was\lang3081  \lang1033 standing just a few stairs in front of him, once more looking down upon her prey. \ldblquote So \'85 you think it amusing to turn a school corridor into a swamp, do you?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Pretty amusing, yeah,\rdblquote  said Fred, looking back up at her without the slightest sign of fear.\lang3081\par
