\lang1033 He turned to his twin.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote George,\rdblquote  said Fred, \ldblquote I think we\rquote ve outgrown full-time education.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, I\rquote ve been feeling that way myself,\rdblquote  said George lightly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Time to test our talents in the real world, d\rquote you reckon?\rdblquote  asked Fred.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Definitely,\rdblquote  said George.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And before Umbridge could say a word, they raised their wands and said together, \ldblquote\i Accio Brooms\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry heard a loud crash somewhere in the distance. Looking to his left he ducked just in time \emdash  Fred and George\rquote s broomsticks, one still trailing the heavy chain and iron peg with which Umbridge had fastened them to the wall, were hurtling along the corridor to\-ward their owners. They turned left, streaked down the stairs, and stopped sharply in front of the twins, the chain clattering loudly on the flagged stone floor.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We won\rquote t be seeing you,\rdblquote  Fred told Professor Umbridge, swinging his leg over his broomstick.\lang3081\par
