He was gibbering, trying to pull away from Professor Tofty, who was looking at him with much concern, and who had just helped Harry out into the entrance hall while the students all around them stared.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m \emdash  I\rquote m fine, sir,\rdblquote  Harry stammered, wiping the sweat from his face. \ldblquote Really \'85 I just fell asleep. \'85 Had a nightmare \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Pressure of examinations!\rdblquote  said the old wizard sympathetically, patting Harry shakily on the shoulder. \ldblquote It happens, young man, it happens! Now, a cooling drink of water, and perhaps you will be ready to return to the Great Hall? The examination is nearly over, but you may be able to round off your last answer nicely?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes,\rdblquote  said Harry wildly. \ldblquote I mean \'85 no \'85 I\rquote ve done \emdash  done as much as I can, I think. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Very well, very well,\rdblquote  said the old wizard gently. \ldblquote I shall go and collect your examination paper, and I suggest that you go and have a nice lie down. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote ll do that,\rdblquote  said Harry, nodding vigorously. \ldblquote Thanks very much.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He waited for the second when the old man\rquote s heels disappeared over the threshold into the Great Hall, then ran up the marble stair\-case and then more staircases toward the hospital wing, hurtling along the corridors so fast that the portraits he passed muttered reproaches, and burst through the double doors like a hurricane, causing Madam Pomfrey, who had been spooning some bright blue liquid into Mon\-tague\rquote s open mouth, to shriek in alarm.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Potter, what do you think you\rquote re doing?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I need to see Professor McGonagall,\rdblquote  gasped Harry, the breath tearing his lungs. \ldblquote Now \'85 It\rquote s urgent. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote She\rquote s not here, Potter,\rdblquote  said Madam Pomfrey sadly. \ldblquote She was trans\-ferred to St. Mungo\rquote s this morning. Four Stunning Spells straight to the chest at her age? It\rquote s a wonder they didn\rquote t kill her.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote She\rquote s \'85 gone?\rdblquote  said Harry, stunned.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The bell rang just outside the dormitory, and he heard the usual distant rumbling of students starting to flood out into the corridors above and below him. He remained quite still, looking at Madam Pomfrey. Terror was rising inside him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was nobody left to tell. Dumbledore had gone, Hagrid had gone, but he had always expected Professor McGonagall to be there, irascible and inflexible, perhaps, but always dependably, solidly present. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I don\rquote t wonder you\rquote re shocked, Potter,\rdblquote  said Madam Pomfrey with a kind of fierce approval in her face. \ldblquote As if one of them could have Stunned Minerva McGonagall face on by daylight! Cowardice, that\rquote s what it was. \'85 Despicable cowardice \'85 If I wasn\rquote t worried what would happen to you students without me, I\rquote d resign in protest. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes,\rdblquote  said Harry blankly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He strode blindly from the hospital wing into the teeming corridor where he stood, buffeted by the crowd, the panic expanding inside\lang3081  \lang1033 him like poison gas so that his head swam and he could not think what to do. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\i Ron and Hermione,\i0  said a voice in his head.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He was running again, pushing students out of the way, oblivious to their angry protests and shouts. He sprinted back down two floors and was at the top of the marble staircase when he saw them hurrying toward him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry!\rdblquote  said Hermione at once, looking very frightened. \ldblquote What happened? Are you all right? Are you ill?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Where have you been?\rdblquote  demanded Ron.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Come with me,\rdblquote  Harry said quickly. \ldblquote Come on, I\rquote ve got to tell you something. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He led them along the first-floor corridor, peering through door\-ways, and at last found an empty classroom into which he dived, clos\-ing the door behind Ron and Hermione the moment they were inside and leaning against it, facing them.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Voldemort\rquote s got Sirius.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i What\i0 ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote How d\rquote you \emdash  ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Saw it. Just now. When I fell asleep in the exam.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But \emdash  but where? How?\rdblquote  said Hermione, whose face was white.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I dunno how,\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote But I know exactly where. There\rquote s a room in the Department of Mysteries full of shelves covered in these little glass balls, and they\rquote re at the end of row ninety-seven \'85 He\rquote s trying to use Sirius to get whatever it is he wants from in there. \'85 He\rquote s torturing him. \'85 Says he\rquote ll end by killing him \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry found his voice was shaking, as were his knees. He moved over to a desk and sat down on it, trying to master himself.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote How\rquote re we going to get there?\rdblquote  he asked them.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was a moment\rquote s silence. Then Ron said, \ldblquote G-get there?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Get to the Department of Mysteries, so we can rescue Sirius!\rdblquote  Harry said loudly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But \emdash  Harry \'85\rdblquote  said Ron weakly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What? \i What\i0 ?\rdblquote  said Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He could not understand why they were both gaping at him as though he was asking them something unreasonable.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry,\rdblquote  said Hermione in a rather frightened voice, \ldblquote er \'85 how \'85 how did Voldemort get into the Ministry of Magic without any\-body realizing he was there?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote How do I know?\rdblquote  bellowed Harry. \ldblquote The question is how \i we\rquote re\i0  going to get in there!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 Harry, think about this,\rdblquote  said Hermione, taking a step toward him, \ldblquote it\rquote s five o\rquote clock in the afternoon. \'85 The Ministry of Magic must be full of workers. \'85 How would Voldemort and Sirius have got in without being seen? Harry \'85 they\rquote re probably the two most wanted wizards in the world. \'85 You think they could get into a building full of Aurors undetected?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I dunno, Voldemort used an Invisibility Cloak or something!\rdblquote  Harry shouted. \ldblquote Anyway, the Department of Mysteries has always been completely empty whenever I\rquote ve been \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote ve never been there, Harry,\rdblquote  said Hermione quietly. \ldblquote You\rquote ve dreamed about the place, that\rquote s all.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
