\lang1033\ldblquote He\rquote s got Padfoot!\rdblquote  he shouted. \ldblquote He\rquote s got Padfoot at the place where it\rquote s hidden!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Snape had stopped with his hand on Umbridge\rquote s door handle.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Padfoot?\rdblquote  cried Professor Umbridge, looking eagerly from Harry to Snape. \ldblquote What is Padfoot? Where what is hidden? What does he mean, Snape?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Snape looked around at Harry. His face was inscrutable. Harry could not tell whether he had understood or not, but he did not dare speak more plainly in front of Umbridge.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I have no idea,\rdblquote  said Snape coldly. \ldblquote Potter, when I want nonsense shouted at me I shall give you a Babbling Beverage. And Crabbe, loosen your hold a little, if Longbottom suffocates it will mean a lot of tedious paperwork, and I am afraid I shall have to mention it on your reference if ever you apply for a job.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He closed the door behind him with a snap, leaving Harry in a state of worse turmoil than before: Snape had been his very last hope. He looked at Umbridge, who seemed to be feeling the same way; her chest was heaving with rage and frustration.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Very well,\rdblquote  she said, and she pulled out her wand. \ldblquote Very well\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 I am left with no alternative. \'85 This is more than a matter of school discipline. \'85 This is an issue of Ministry security. \'85 Yes \'85 yes \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She seemed to be talking herself into something. She was shifting her weight nervously from foot to foot, staring at Harry, beating her wand against her empty palm and breathing heavily. Harry felt horri\-bly powerless without his own wand as he watched her.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You are forcing me, Potter. \'85 I do not want to,\rdblquote  said Umbridge, still moving restlessly on the spot, \ldblquote but sometimes circumstances jus\-tify the use \'85 I am sure the Minister will understand that I had no choice. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Malfoy was watching her with a hungry expression on his face.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The Cruciatus Curse ought to loosen your tongue,\rdblquote  said Um\-bridge quietly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No!\rdblquote  shrieked Hermione. \ldblquote Professor Umbridge \emdash  it\rquote s illegal\rdblquote  \emdash  but Umbridge took no notice. There was a nasty, eager, excited look on her face that Harry had never seen before. She raised her wand.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The Minister wouldn\rquote t want you to break the law, Professor Um\-bridge!\rdblquote  cried Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What Cornelius doesn\rquote t know won\rquote t hurt him,\rdblquote  said Umbridge, who was now panting slightly as she pointed her wand at different\lang3081  \lang1033 parts of Harry\rquote s body in turn, apparently trying to decide what would hurt the most. \ldblquote He never knew I ordered dementors after Potter last summer, but he was delighted to be given the chance to expel him, all the same. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It was \i you\i0 ?\rdblquote  gasped Harry. \ldblquote\i You\i0  sent the dementors after me?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Somebody\i0  had to act,\rdblquote  breathed Umbridge, as her wand came to rest pointing directly at Harry\rquote s forehead. \ldblquote They were all bleating about silencing you somehow \emdash  discrediting you \emdash  but I was the one who actually \i did\i0  something about it. \'85 Only you wriggled out of that one, didn\rquote t you, Potter? Not today, though, not now \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And taking a deep breath, she cried, \ldblquote\i Cruc\i0  \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote NO!\rdblquote  shouted Hermione in a cracked voice from behind Milli\-cent Bulstrode. \ldblquote No \emdash  Harry \emdash  Harry, we\rquote ll have to tell her!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No way!\rdblquote  yelled Harry, staring at the little of Hermione he could see.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We\rquote ll have to, Harry, she\rquote ll force it out of you anyway, what\rquote s \'85 what\rquote s the point\'85 ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And Hermione began to cry weakly into the back of Millicent Bul\-strode\rquote s robes. Millicent stopped trying to squash her against the wall immediately and dodged out of her way looking disgusted.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, well, well!\rdblquote  said Umbridge, looking triumphant. \ldblquote Little Miss Question-All is going to give us some answers! Come on then, girl, come on!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Er \emdash  my \emdash  nee \emdash  no!\rdblquote  shouted Ron through his gag.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ginny was staring at Hermione as though she had never seen her before; Neville, still choking for breath, was gazing at her too. But Harry had just noticed something. Though Hermione was sobbing desperately into her hands, there was no trace of a tear. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m \emdash  I\rquote m sorry everyone,\rdblquote  said Hermione. \ldblquote But \emdash  I can\rquote t stand it\lang3081  \lang1033\emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote That\rquote s right, that\rquote s right, girl!\rdblquote  said Umbridge, seizing Hermione\lang3081  \lang1033 by the shoulders, thrusting her into the abandoned chintz chair and leaning over her. \ldblquote Now then \'85 with whom was Potter communicat\-ing just now?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well,\rdblquote  gulped Hermione into her hands, \ldblquote well, he was \i trying\i0  to speak to Professor Dumbledore. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron froze, his eyes wide; Ginny stopped trying to stamp on her Slytherin captor\rquote s toes; even Luna looked mildly surprised. Fortu\-nately, the attention of Umbridge and her minions was focused too exclusively upon Hermione to notice these suspicious signs.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Dumbledore?\rdblquote  said Umbridge eagerly. \ldblquote You know where Dumb\-ledore is, then?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 no!\rdblquote  sobbed Hermione. \ldblquote We\rquote ve tried the Leaky Caul\-dron in Diagon Alley and the Three Broomsticks and even the Hog\rquote s Head \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Idiot girl, Dumbledore won\rquote t be sitting in a pub when the whole Ministry\rquote s looking for him!\rdblquote  shouted Umbridge, disappointment etched in every sagging line of her face.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But \emdash  but we needed to tell him something important!\rdblquote  wailed Hermione, holding her hands more tightly over her face, not, Harry knew, out of anguish, but to disguise the continued absence of tears.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes?\rdblquote  said Umbridge with a sudden resurgence of excitement. \ldblquote What was it you wanted to tell him?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We \'85 we wanted to tell him it\rquote s r-ready!\rdblquote  choked Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What\rquote s ready?\rdblquote  demanded Umbridge, and now she grabbed Hermione\rquote s shoulders again and shook her slightly. \ldblquote What\rquote s ready, girl?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The \'85 the weapon,\rdblquote  said Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Weapon? Weapon?\rdblquote  said Umbridge, and her eyes seemed to pop with excitement. \ldblquote You have been developing some method of resis\-tance? A weapon you could use against the Ministry? On Professor Dumbledore\rquote s orders, of course?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Y-y-yes,\rdblquote  gasped Hermione. \ldblquote But he had to leave before it was fin\-ished and n-n-now we\rquote ve finished it for him, and we c-c-can\rquote t find him t-t-to tell him!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What kind of weapon is it?\rdblquote  said Umbridge harshly, her stubby hands still tight on Hermione\rquote s shoulders.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We don\rquote t r-r-really understand it,\rdblquote  said Hermione, sniffing loudly. \ldblquote We j-j-just did what P-P-Professor Dumbledore told us t-t-to do \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Umbridge straightened up, looking exultant.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Lead me to the weapon,\rdblquote  she said.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m not showing \'85 \i them\i0 ,\rdblquote  said Hermione shrilly, looking around at the Slytherins through her fingers.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It is not for you to set conditions,\rdblquote  said Professor Umbridge harshly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Fine,\rdblquote  said Hermione, now sobbing into her hands again, \ldblquote fine \'85 let them see it, I hope they use it on you! In fact, I wish you\rquote d in\-vite loads and loads of people to come and see! Th-that would serve you right \emdash  oh, I\rquote d love it if the wh-whole school knew where it was, and how to u-use it, and then if you annoy any of them they\rquote ll be able to s-sort you out!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 These words had a powerful impact on Umbridge. She glanced swiftly and suspiciously around at her Inquisitorial Squad, her bulging eyes resting for a moment on Malfoy, who was too slow to disguise the look of eagerness and greed that had appeared on his face.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Umbridge contemplated Hermione for another long moment and then spoke in what she clearly thought was a motherly voice. \ldblquote All right, dear, let\rquote s make it just you and me \'85 and we\rquote ll take Potter too, shall we? Get up, now \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
