Harry had no idea what Hermione was planning, or even whether she had a plan. He walked half a pace behind her as they headed down the corridor outside Umbridge\rquote s office, knowing it would look very suspicious if he appeared not to know where they were going. He did not dare attempt to talk to her; Umbridge was walking so closely behind them that he could hear her ragged breathing.\par
Hermione led the way down the stairs into the entrance hall. The din of loud voices and the clatter of cutlery on plates echoed from out of the double doors to the Great Hall. It seemed incredible to Harry that twenty feet away were people who were enjoying dinner, cele\-brating the end of exams, not a care in the world. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione walked straight out of the oak front doors and down the stone steps into the balmy evening air. The sun was falling toward the tops of the trees in the Forbidden Forest now as Hermione marched purposefully across the grass, Umbridge jogging to keep up. Their long dark shadows rippled over the grass behind them like cloaks.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It\rquote s hidden in Hagrid\rquote s hut, is it?\rdblquote  said Umbridge eagerly in Harry\rquote s ear.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Of course not,\rdblquote  said Hermione scathingly. \ldblquote Hagrid might have set it off accidentally.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes,\rdblquote  said Umbridge, whose excitement seemed to be mounting. \ldblquote Yes, he would have done, of course, the great half-breed oaf. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She laughed. Harry felt a strong urge to swing around and seize her by the throat, but resisted. His scar was throbbing in the soft evening air but it had not yet burned white-hot, as he knew it would if Volde\-mort had moved in for the kill. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Then \'85 where is it?\rdblquote  asked Umbridge, with a hint of uncertainty in her voice as Hermione continued to stride toward the forest.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote In there, of course,\rdblquote  said Hermione, pointing into the dark trees. \ldblquote It had to be somewhere that students weren\rquote t going to find it acci\-dentally, didn\rquote t it?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Of course,\rdblquote  said Umbridge, though she sounded a little apprehen\-sive now. \ldblquote Of course \'85 very well, then \'85 you two stay ahead of me.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Can we have your wand, then, if we\rquote re going first?\rdblquote  Harry asked her.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No, I don\rquote t think so, Mr. Potter,\rdblquote  said Umbridge sweetly, poking him in the back with it. \ldblquote The Ministry places a rather higher value on my life than yours, I\rquote m afraid.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 As they reached the cool shade of the first trees, Harry tried to catch Hermione\rquote s eye; walking into the forest without wands seemed to him to be more foolhardy than anything they had done so far this evening. She, however, merely gave Umbridge a contemptuous glance and plunged straight into the trees, moving at such a pace that Umbridge, with her shorter legs, had difficulty in keeping up.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Is it very far in?\rdblquote  Umbridge asked, as her robe ripped on a bramble.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh yes,\rdblquote  said Hermione. \ldblquote Yes, it\rquote s well hidden.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry\rquote s misgivings increased. Hermione was not taking the path\lang3081  \lang1033 they had followed to visit Grawp, but the one he had followed three years ago to the lair of the monster Aragog. Hermione had not been with him on that occasion; he doubted she had any idea what danger lay at the end of it.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Er \emdash  are you sure this is the right way?\rdblquote  he asked her pointedly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh yes,\rdblquote  she said in a steely voice, crashing through the under\-growth with what he thought was a wholly unnecessary amount of noise. Behind them, Umbridge tripped over a fallen sapling. Neither of them paused to help her up again; Hermione merely strode on, calling loudly over her shoulder, \ldblquote It\rquote s a bit further in!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hermione, keep your voice down,\rdblquote  Harry muttered, hurrying to catch up with her. \ldblquote Anything could be listening in here \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I want us heard,\rdblquote  she answered quietly, as Umbridge jogged nois\-ily after them. \ldblquote You\rquote ll see. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They walked on for what seemed a long time, until they were once again so deep into the forest that the dense tree canopy blocked out all light. Harry had the feeling he had had before in the forest, one of be\-ing watched by unseen eyes. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote How much further?\rdblquote  demanded Umbridge angrily from behind him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Not far now!\rdblquote  shouted Hermione, as they emerged into a dim, dank clearing. \ldblquote Just a little bit \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 An arrow flew through the air and landed with a menacing thud in the tree just over her head. The air was suddenly full of the sound of hooves. Harry could feel the forest floor trembling; Umbridge gave a little scream and pushed him in front of her like a shield \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He wrenched himself free of her and turned. Around fifty centaurs were emerging on every side, their bows raised and loaded, pointing at Harry, Hermione, and Umbridge, who backed slowly into the center of the clearing, Umbridge uttering odd little whimpers of terror. Harry looked sideways at Hermione. She was wearing a triumphant smile.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Who are you?\rdblquote  said a voice.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry looked left. The chestnut-bodied centaur called Magorian was walking toward them out of the circle; his bow, like the others\rquote , was raised. On Harry\rquote s right, Umbridge was still whimpering, her wand trembling violently as she pointed it at the advancing centaur.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I asked you who are you, human,\rdblquote  said Magorian roughly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I am Dolores Umbridge!\rdblquote  said Umbridge in a high-pitched, terri\-fied voice. \ldblquote Senior Undersecretary to the Minister of Magic and Head\-mistress and High Inquisitor of Hogwarts!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You are from the Ministry of Magic?\rdblquote  said Magorian, as many of the centaurs in the surrounding circle shifted restlessly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote That\rquote s right!\rdblquote  said Umbridge in an even higher voice. \ldblquote So be very careful! By the laws laid down by the Department for the Regulation and Control of Magical Creatures, any attack by half-breeds such as yourselves on a human \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i What\i0  did you call us?\rdblquote  shouted a wild-looking black centaur, whom Harry recognized as Bane. There was a great deal of angry mut\-tering and tightening of bowstrings around them.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Don\rquote t call them that!\rdblquote  Hermione said furiously, but Umbridge did not appear to have heard her. Still pointing her shaking wand at Magorian, she continued, \ldblquote Law Fifteen B states clearly that \lquote Any at\-tack by a magical creature who is deemed to have near-human intelli\-gence, and therefore considered responsible for its actions \emdash\rquote  \rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote  \lquote Near-human intelligence\rquote ?\rdblquote  repeated Magorian, as Bane and sev\-eral others roared with rage and pawed the ground. \ldblquote We consider that a great insult, human! Our intelligence, thankfully, far outstrips your own \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What are you doing in our forest?\rdblquote  bellowed the hard-faced gray centaur whom Harry and Hermione had seen on their last trip into the forest. \ldblquote Why are you here?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Your\i0  forest?\rdblquote  said Umbridge, shaking now not only with fright but also, it seemed, with indignation. \ldblquote I would remind you that you live\lang3081  \lang1033 here only because the Ministry of Magic permits you certain areas of land \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 An arrow flew so close to her head that it caught at her mousy hair in passing. She let out an earsplitting scream and threw her hands over her head while some of the centaurs bellowed their approval and oth\-ers laughed raucously. The sound of their wild, neighing laughter echoing around the dimly lit clearing and the sight of their pawing hooves was extremely unnerving.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Whose forest is it now, human?\rdblquote  bellowed Bane.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Filthy half-breeds!\rdblquote  she screamed, her hands still tight over her head. \ldblquote Beasts! Uncontrolled animals!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Be quiet!\rdblquote  shouted Hermione, but it was too late \emdash  Umbridge pointed her wand at Magorian and screamed, \ldblquote\i Incarcerous\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ropes flew out of midair like thick snakes, wrapping themselves tightly around the centaur\rquote s torso and trapping his arms. He gave a cry of rage and reared onto his hind legs, attempting to free himself, while the other centaurs charged.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry grabbed Hermione and pulled her to the ground. Facedown on the forest floor he knew a moment of terror as hooves thundered around him, but the centaurs leapt over and around them, bellowing and screaming with rage.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Nooooo!\rdblquote  he heard Umbridge shriek. \ldblquote Noooooo \'85 I am Senior Undersecretary \'85 you cannot \'85 unhand me, you animals \'85 nooooo!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He saw a flash of red light and knew that she had attempted to Stun one of them \emdash  then she screamed very loudly. Lifting his head a few inches, Harry saw that Umbridge had been seized from behind by Bane and lifted high into the air, wriggling and yelling with fright. Her wand fell from her hand to the ground and Harry\rquote s heart leapt, if he could just reach it \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But as he stretched out a hand toward it, a centaur\rquote s hoof descended upon the wand and it broke cleanly in half.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Now!\rdblquote  roared a voice in Harry\rquote s ear and a thick hairy arm de\-scended from thin air and dragged him upright; Hermione too had been pulled to her feet. Over the plunging, many-colored backs and heads of the centaurs Harry saw Umbridge being borne away through the trees by Bane, still screaming nonstop; her voice grew fainter and fainter until they could no longer hear it over the trampling of hooves surrounding them.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And these?\rdblquote  said the hard-faced, gray centaur holding Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote They are young,\rdblquote  said a slow, doleful voice from behind Harry. \ldblquote We do not attack foals.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote They brought her here, Ronan,\rdblquote  replied the centaur who had such a firm grip on Harry. \ldblquote And they are not so young. \'85 He is nearing manhood, this one. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He shook Harry by the neck of his robes.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Please,\rdblquote  said Hermione breathlessly, \ldblquote please, don\rquote t attack us, we don\rquote t think like her, we aren\rquote t Ministry of Magic employees! We only came in here because we hoped you\rquote d drive her off for us \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry knew at once from the look on the face of the gray centaur holding Hermione that she had made a terrible mistake in saying this. The gray centaur threw back his head, his back legs stamping furi\-ously, and bellowed, \ldblquote You see, Ronan? They already have the arro\-gance of their kind! So we were to do your dirty work, were we, human girl? We were to act as your servants, drive away your enemies like obedient hounds?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No!\rdblquote  said Hermione in a horrorstruck squeak. \ldblquote Please \emdash  I didn\rquote t mean that! I just hoped you\rquote d be able to \emdash  to help us \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But she seemed to be going from bad to worse.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We do not help humans!\rdblquote  snarled the centaur holding Harry, tightening his grip and rearing a little at the same time, so that Harry\rquote s feet left the ground momentarily. \ldblquote We are a race apart and proud to be so. \'85 We will not permit you to walk from here, boasting that we did your bidding!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We\rquote re not going to say anything like that!\rdblquote  Harry shouted. \ldblquote We know you didn\rquote t do anything because we wanted you to \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But nobody seemed to be listening to him. A bearded centaur to\-ward the back of the crowd shouted, \ldblquote They came here unasked, they must pay the consequences!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 A roar of approval met these words and a dun-colored centaur shouted, \ldblquote They can join the woman!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You said you didn\rquote t hurt the innocent!\rdblquote  shouted Hermione, real tears sliding down her face now. \ldblquote We haven\rquote t done anything to hurt you, we haven\rquote t used wands or threats, we just want to go back to school, please let us go back \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We are not all like the traitor Firenze, human girl!\rdblquote  shouted the gray centaur, to more neighing roars of approval from his fellows. \ldblquote Perhaps you thought us pretty talking horses? We are an ancient peo\-ple who will not stand wizard invasions and insults! We do not recog\-nize your laws, we do not acknowledge your superiority, we are \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But they did not hear what else centaurs were, for at that moment there came a crashing noise on the edge of the clearing so loud that all of them \emdash  Harry, Hermione, and the fifty or so centaurs filling the clearing \emdash  looked around. Harry\rquote s centaur let him fall to the ground again as his hands flew to his bow and quiver of arrows; Hermione had been dropped too, and Harry hurried toward her as two thick tree trunks parted ominously and the monstrous form of Grawp the giant appeared in the gap.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The centaurs nearest him backed into those behind. The clearing was now a forest of bows and arrows waiting to be fired, all pointing upward at the enormous grayish face now looming over them from just beneath the thick canopy of branches. Grawp\rquote s lopsided mouth was gaping stupidly. They could see his bricklike yellow teeth glim\-mering in the half-light, his dull sludge-colored eyes narrowed as he squinted down at the creatures at his feet. Broken ropes trailed from both ankles.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He opened his mouth even wider.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hagger.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry did not know what \ldblquote hagger\rdblquote  meant, or what language it was from, nor did he much care \emdash  he was watching Grawp\rquote s feet, which were almost as long as Harry\rquote s whole body. Hermione gripped his arm tightly; the centaurs were quite silent, staring up at the giant, whose huge, round head moved from side to side as he continued to peer amongst them as though looking for something he had dropped.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Hagger\i0 !\rdblquote  he said again, more insistently.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Get away from here, giant!\rdblquote  called Magorian. \ldblquote You are not wel\-come among us!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 These words seemed to make no impression whatsoever on Grawp. He stooped a little (the centaurs\rquote  arms tensed on their bows) and then bellowed, \ldblquote HAGGER!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 A few of the centaurs looked worried now. Hermione, however, gave a gasp.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry!\rdblquote  she whispered. \ldblquote I think he\rquote s trying to say \lquote Hagrid\rquote !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 At this precise moment Grawp caught sight of them, the only two humans in a sea of centaurs. He lowered his head another foot or so, staring intently at them. Harry could feel Hermione shaking as Grawp opened his mouth wide again and said, in a deep, rumbling voice, \ldblquote Hermy.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Goodness,\rdblquote  said Hermione, gripping Harry\rquote s arm so tightly it was growing numb and looking as though she was about to faint, \ldblquote he \emdash  he remembered!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote HERMY!\rdblquote  roared Grawp. \ldblquote WHERE HAGGER?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I don\rquote t know!\rdblquote  squealed Hermione, terrified. \ldblquote I\rquote m sorry, Grawp, I don\rquote t know!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote GRAWP WANT HAGGER!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 One of the giant\rquote s massive hands swooped down upon them \emdash  Hermione let out a real scream, ran a few steps backward and fell over. Wandless, Harry braced himself to punch, kick, bite, or whatever else\lang3081  \lang1033 it took as the hand flew toward him and knocked a snow-white cen\-taur off his legs.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 It was what the centaurs had been waiting for \emdash  Grawp\rquote s out\-stretched fingers were a foot from Harry when fifty arrows went soar\-ing through the air at the giant, peppering his enormous face, causing him to howl with pain and rage and straighten up again, rubbing his face with his enormous hands, breaking off the arrow shafts but forc\-ing the heads in still deeper.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He yelled and stamped his enormous feet and the centaurs scat\-tered out of the way. Pebble-sized droplets of Grawp\rquote s blood showered Harry as he pulled Hermione to her feet and the pair of them ran as fast as they could for the shelter of the trees. Once there they looked back \emdash  Grawp was snatching blindly at the centaurs as blood ran all down his face; they were retreating in disorder, galloping away through the trees on the other side of the clearing. As Harry and Hermione watched, Grawp gave another roar of fury and plunged af\-ter them, smashing more trees aside as he went.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh no,\rdblquote  said Hermione, quaking so badly that her knees gave way. \ldblquote Oh, that was horrible. And he might kill them all. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m not that fussed, to be honest,\rdblquote  said Harry bitterly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The sounds of the galloping centaurs and the blundering giant were growing fainter and fainter. As Harry listened to them his scar gave another great throb and a wave of terror swept over him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They had wasted so much time \emdash  they were even further from res\-cuing Sirius than they had been when he had had the vision. Not only had Harry managed to lose his wand but they were stuck in the mid\-dle of the Forbidden Forest with no means of transport whatsoever.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Smart plan,\rdblquote  he spat at Hermione, keen to release some of his fury. \ldblquote Really smart plan. Where do we go from here?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We need to get back up to the castle,\rdblquote  said Hermione faintly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote By the time we\rquote ve done that, Sirius\rquote ll probably be dead!\rdblquote  said Harry, kicking a nearby tree in temper; there was a high-pitched\lang3081  \lang1033 chattering overhead and he looked up to see an angry bowtruckle flex\-ing its long twiglike fingers at him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, we can\rquote t do anything without wands,\rdblquote  said Hermione hope\-lessly, dragging herself up again. \ldblquote Anyway, Harry, how exactly were you planning to get all the way to London?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, we were just wondering that,\rdblquote  said a familiar voice from be\-hind her.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry and Hermione moved instinctively together, peering through the trees, as Ron came into sight, with Ginny, Neville, and Luna hur\-rying along behind him. All of them looked a little the worse for wear \emdash  there were several long scratches running the length of Ginny\rquote s cheek, a large purple lump was swelling above Neville\rquote s right eye, Ron\rquote s lip was bleeding worse than ever \emdash  but all were looking rather pleased with themselves.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So,\rdblquote  said Ron, pushing aside a low-hanging branch and holding out Harry\rquote s wand, \ldblquote had any ideas?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote How did you get away?\rdblquote  asked Harry in amazement, taking his wand from Ron.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Couple of Stunners, a Disarming Charm, Neville brought off a re\-ally nice little Impediment Jinx,\rdblquote  said Ron airily, now handing back Hermione\rquote s wand too. \ldblquote But Ginny was best, she got Malfoy \emdash  Bat-Bogey Hex \emdash  it was superb, his whole face was covered in the great flapping things. Anyway, we saw you heading into the forest out of the window and followed. What\rquote ve you done with Umbridge?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote She got carried away,\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote By a herd of centaurs.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And they left you behind?\rdblquote  asked Ginny, looking astonished.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No, they got chased off by Grawp,\rdblquote  said Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Who\rquote s Grawp?\rdblquote  Luna asked interestedly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hagrid\rquote s little brother,\rdblquote  said Ron promptly. \ldblquote Anyway, never mind that now. Harry, what did you find out in the fire? Has You-Know-Who got Sirius or \emdash  ?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes,\rdblquote  said Harry, as his scar gave another painful prickle, \ldblquote and I\rquote m\lang3081  \lang1033 sure Sirius is still alive, but I can\rquote t see how we\rquote re going to get there to help him.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They all fell silent, looking rather scared. The problem facing them seemed insurmountable.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, we\rquote ll have to fly, won\rquote t we?\rdblquote  said Luna in the closest thing to a matter-of-fact voice Harry had ever heard her use.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Okay,\rdblquote  said Harry irritably, rounding on her, \ldblquote first of all, \lquote we\rquote  aren\rquote t doing anything if you\rquote re including yourself in that, and second of all, Ron\rquote s the only one with a broomstick that isn\rquote t being guarded by a security troll, so \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote ve got a broom!\rdblquote  said Ginny.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, but you\rquote re not coming,\rdblquote  said Ron angrily.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Excuse me, but I care what happens to Sirius as much as you do!\rdblquote  said Ginny, her jaw set so that her resemblance to Fred and George was suddenly striking.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote re too \emdash\rdblquote  Harry began.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m three years older than you were when you fought You-Know-Who over the Sorcerer\rquote s Stone,\rdblquote  she said fiercely, \ldblquote and it\rquote s because of me Malfoy\rquote s stuck back in Umbridge\rquote s office with giant flying bogeys attacking him \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, but \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We were all in the D.A. together,\rdblquote  said Neville quietly. \ldblquote It was all supposed to be about fighting You-Know-Who, wasn\rquote t it? And this is the first chance we\rquote ve had to do something real \emdash  or was that all just a game or something?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No \emdash  of course it wasn\rquote t \emdash\rdblquote  said Harry impatiently.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Then we should come too,\rdblquote  said Neville simply. \ldblquote We want to help.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote That\rquote s right,\rdblquote  said Luna, smiling happily.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry\rquote s eyes met Ron\rquote s. He knew that Ron was thinking exactly what he was: If he could have chosen any members of the D.A. in ad\-dition to himself, Ron, and Hermione to join him in the attempt to rescue Sirius, he would not have picked Ginny, Neville, or Luna.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, it doesn\rquote t matter anyway,\rdblquote  said Harry frustratedly, \ldblquote because we still don\rquote t know how to get there \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I thought we\rquote d settled that?\rdblquote  said Luna maddeningly. \ldblquote We\rquote re flying!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Look,\rdblquote  said Ron, barely containing his anger, \ldblquote you might be able to fly without a broomstick but the rest of us can\rquote t sprout wings when\-ever we \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote There are other ways of flying than with broomsticks,\rdblquote  said Luna serenely.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I s\rquote pose we\rquote re going to ride on the back of the Kacky Snorgle or whatever it is?\rdblquote  Ron demanded.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The Crumple-Horned Snorkack can\rquote t fly,\rdblquote  said Luna in a dignified voice, \ldblquote but \i they\i0  can, and Hagrid says they\rquote re very good at finding places their riders are looking for.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry whirled around. Standing between two trees, their white eyes gleaming eerily, were two thestrals, watching the whispered con\-versation as though they understood every word.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes!\rdblquote  he whispered, moving toward them. They tossed their reptil\-ian heads, throwing back long black manes, and Harry stretched out his hand eagerly and patted the nearest one\rquote s shining neck. How could he ever have thought them ugly?\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Is it those mad horse things?\rdblquote  said Ron uncertainly, staring at a point slightly to the left of the thestral Harry was patting. \ldblquote Those ones you can\rquote t see unless you\rquote ve watched someone snuff it?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah,\rdblquote  said Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote How many?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Just two.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, we need three,\rdblquote  said Hermione, who was still looking a lit\-tle shaken, but determined just the same.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Four, Hermione,\rdblquote  said Ginny, scowling.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I think there are six of us, actually,\rdblquote  said Luna calmly, counting.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Don\rquote t be stupid, we can\rquote t all go!\rdblquote  said Harry angrily. \ldblquote Look, you\lang3081  \lang1033 three\rdblquote  \emdash  he pointed at Neville, Ginny, and Luna \emdash  \ldblquote you\rquote re not in\-volved in this, you\rquote re not \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They burst into more protests. His scar gave another, more painful, twinge. Every moment they delayed was precious; he did not have time to argue.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Okay, fine, it\rquote s your choice,\rdblquote  he said curtly. \ldblquote But unless we can find more thestrals you\rquote re not going to be able \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, more of them will come,\rdblquote  said Ginny confidently, who like Ron was squinting in quite the wrong direction, apparently under the impression that she was looking at the horses.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What makes you think that?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Because in case you hadn\rquote t noticed, you and Hermione are both covered in blood,\rdblquote  she said coolly, \ldblquote and we know Hagrid lures thes\-trals with raw meat, so that\rquote s probably why these two turned up in the first place. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry felt a soft tug on his robes at that moment and looked down to see the closest thestral licking his sleeve, which was damp with Grawp\rquote s blood.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Okay, then,\rdblquote  he said, a bright idea occurring. \ldblquote Ron and I will take these two and go ahead, and Hermione can stay here with you three and she\rquote ll attract more thestrals \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m not staying behind!\rdblquote  said Hermione furiously.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote There\rquote s no need,\rdblquote  said Luna, smiling. \ldblquote Look, here come more now. \'85 You two must really smell. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry turned. No fewer than six or seven thestrals were picking their way through the trees now, their great leathery wings folded tight to their bodies, their eyes gleaming through the darkness. He had no excuse now. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote All right,\rdblquote  he said angrily, \ldblquote pick one and get on, then.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
