Harry wound his hand tightly into the mane of the nearest thestral, placed a foot on a stump nearby, and scrambled clumsily onto the horse\rquote s silken back. It did not object, but twisted its head around, fangs bared, and attempted to continue its eager licking of his robes.\par
He found there was a way of lodging his knees behind the wing joints that made him feel more secure and looked around at the oth\-ers. Neville had heaved himself over the back of the next thestral and was now attempting to swing one short leg over the creature\rquote s back. Luna was already in place, sitting sidesaddle and adjusting her robes as though she did this every day. Ron, Hermione, and Ginny, however, were still standing motionless on the spot, openmouthed and staring.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What?\rdblquote  he said.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote How\rquote re we supposed to get on?\rdblquote  said Ron faintly. \ldblquote When we can\rquote t see the things?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh it\rquote s easy,\rdblquote  said Luna, sliding obligingly from her thestral and marching over to him, Hermione, and Ginny. \ldblquote Come here. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She pulled them over to the other thestrals standing around and one by one managed to help them onto the backs of their mounts. All three looked extremely nervous as she wound their hands into the horses\rquote  manes and told them to grip tightly before getting back onto her own steed.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote This is mad,\rdblquote  Ron said faintly, moving his free hand gingerly up and down his horse\rquote s neck. \ldblquote Mad \'85 if I could just see it \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote d better hope it stays invisible,\rdblquote  said Harry darkly. \ldblquote We all ready, then?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They all nodded and he saw five pairs of knees tighten beneath their robes.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Okay\lang3081  \lang1033\'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He looked down at the back of his thestral\rquote s glossy black head and swallowed. \ldblquote Ministry of Magic, visitors\rquote  entrance, London, then,\rdblquote  he said uncertainly. \ldblquote Er \'85 if you know \'85 where to go \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 For a moment his thestral did nothing at all. Then, with a sweep\-ing movement that nearly unseated him, the wings on either side ex\-tended, the horse crouched slowly and then rocketed upward so fast and so steeply that Harry had to clench his arms and legs tightly around the horse to avoid sliding backward over its bony rump. He closed his eyes and put his face down into the horse\rquote s silky mane as they burst through the topmost branches of the trees and soared out into a bloodred sunset.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry did not think he had ever moved so fast: The thestral streaked over the castle, its wide wings hardly beating. The cooling air was slapping Harry\rquote s face; eyes screwed up against the rushing wind, he looked around and saw his five fellows soaring along behind him, each of them bent as low as possible into the neck of their thestral to protect themselves from its slipstream.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They were over the Hogwarts grounds, they had passed Hogs\-meade. Harry could see mountains and gullies below them. In the\lang3081  \lang1033 falling darkness Harry saw small collections of lights as they passed over more villages, then a winding road on which a single car was beetling its way home through the hills. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote This is bizarre!\rdblquote  Harry heard Ron yell from somewhere behind him, and he imagined how it must feel to be speeding along at this height with no visible means of support. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Twilight fell: The sky turned to a light, dusky purple littered with tiny silver stars, and soon it was only the lights of Muggle towns that gave them any clue of how far from the ground they were or how very fast they were traveling. Harry\rquote s arms were wrapped tightly around his horse\rquote s neck as he willed it to go even faster. How much time had elapsed since he had seen Sirius lying on the Department of Mysteries floor? How much longer would he be able to resist Voldemort? All Harry knew for sure was that Sirius had neither done as Voldemort wanted, nor died, for he was convinced that either outcome would cause him to feel Voldemort\rquote s jubilation or fury course through his own body, making his scar sear as painfully as it had on the night Mr. Weasley was attacked. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 On they flew through the gathering darkness; Harry\rquote s face felt stiff and cold, his legs numb from gripping the thestral\rquote s sides so tightly, but he did not dare shift positions lest he slip. \'85 He was deaf from the thundering in his ears and his mouth was dry and frozen from the rush of cold night air. He had lost all sense of how far they had come; all his faith was in the beast below him, still streaking purposefully through the night, barely flapping its wings as it sped ever onward. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 If they were too late \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\i He\rquote s still alive, he\rquote s still fighting, I can feel it. \'85\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033 If Voldemort decided Sirius was not going to crack \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\i I\rquote d know. \'85\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033 Harry\rquote s stomach gave a jolt. The thestral\rquote s head was suddenly point\-ing toward the ground and he had actually slid forward a few inches along its neck. They were descending at last. \'85 He heard one of the\lang3081  \lang1033 girls shriek behind him and twisted around dangerously but could see no sign of a falling body. \'85 Presumably they had received a shock from the change of position, just as he had. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And now bright orange lights were growing larger and rounder on all sides. They could see the tops of buildings, streams of headlights like luminous insect eyes, squares of pale yellow that were windows. Quite suddenly, it seemed, they were hurtling toward the pavement. Harry gripped the thestral with every last ounce of his strength, braced for a sudden impact, but the horse touched the dark ground as lightly as a shadow and Harry slid from his back, looking around at the street where the overflowing dumpster still stood a short way from the vandalized telephone box, both drained of color in the flat orange glare of the streetlights.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron landed a short way away and toppled immediately off his thes\-tral onto the pavement.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Never again,\rdblquote  he said, struggling to his feet. He made as though to stride away from his thestral, but, unable to see it, collided with its hindquarters and almost fell over again. \ldblquote Never, ever again \'85 that was the worst \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione and Ginny touched down on either side of him. Both slid off their mounts a little more gracefully than Ron, though with similar expressions of relief at being back on firm ground. Neville jumped down, shaking, but Luna dismounted smoothly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Where do we go from here, then?\rdblquote  she asked Harry in a politely interested voice, as though this was all a rather interesting day-trip.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Over here,\rdblquote  he said. He gave his thestral a quick, grateful pat, then led the way quickly to the battered telephone box and opened the door. \ldblquote Come \i on\i0 !\rdblquote  he urged the others as they hesitated.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron and Ginny marched in obediently; Hermione, Neville, and Luna squashed themselves in after them; Harry took one glance back at the thestrals, now foraging for scraps of rotten food inside the dumpster, then forced himself into the box after Luna.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Whoever\rquote s nearest the receiver, dial six two four four two!\rdblquote  he said.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ron did it, his arm bent bizarrely to reach the dial. As it whirred back into place the cool female voice sounded inside the box, \ldblquote Wel\-come to the Ministry of Magic. Please state your name and business.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry Potter, Ron Weasley, Hermione Granger,\rdblquote  Harry said very quickly, \ldblquote Ginny Weasley, Neville Longbottom, Luna Lovegood \'85 We\rquote re here to save someone, unless your Ministry can do it first!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Thank you,\rdblquote  said the cool female voice. \ldblquote Visitors, please take the badges and attach them to the front of your robes.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Half a dozen badges slid out of the metal chute where returned coins usually appeared. Hermione scooped them up and handed them mutely to Harry over Ginny\rquote s head; he glanced at the topmost one.\par
