Harry stared at it.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What is it?\rdblquote  Ron asked, sounding unnerved. \ldblquote What\rquote s your name doing down here?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He glanced along at the other labels on that stretch of shelf.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m not here,\rdblquote  he said, sounding perplexed. \ldblquote None of the rest of us are here. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry, I don\rquote t think you should touch it,\rdblquote  said Hermione sharply, as he stretched out his hand.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Why not?\rdblquote  he said. \ldblquote It\rquote s something to do with me, isn\rquote t it?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Don\rquote t, Harry,\rdblquote  said Neville suddenly. Harry looked around at him. Neville\rquote s round face was shining slightly with sweat. He looked as though he could not take much more suspense.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It\rquote s got my name on,\rdblquote  said Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And feeling slightly reckless, he closed his fingers around the dusty ball\rquote s surface. He had expected it to feel cold, but it did not. On the contrary, it felt as though it had been lying in the sun for hours, as though the glow of light within was warming it. Expecting, even hop\-ing, that something dramatic was going to happen, something excit\-ing that might make their long and dangerous journey worthwhile after all, he lifted the glass ball down from its shelf and stared at it.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Nothing whatsoever happened. The others moved in closer around Harry, gazing at the orb as he brushed it free of the clogging dust.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And then, from right behind them, a drawling voice said, \ldblquote Very good, Potter. Now turn around, nice and slowly, and give that to me.\rdblquote\par
