Black shapes were emerging out of thin air all around them, block\-ing their way left and right; eyes glinted through slits in hoods, a dozen lit wand tips were pointing directly at their hearts. Ginny gave a gasp of horror.\par
\ldblquote To me, Potter,\rdblquote  repeated the drawling voice of Lucius Malfoy as he held out his hand, palm up.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry\rquote s insides plummeted sickeningly. They were trapped and outnumbered two to one.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote To me,\rdblquote  said Malfoy yet again.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Where\rquote s Sirius?\rdblquote  Harry said.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Several of the Death Eaters laughed. A harsh female voice from the midst of the shadowy figures to Harry\rquote s left said triumphantly, \ldblquote The Dark Lord always knows!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Always,\rdblquote  echoed Malfoy softly. \ldblquote Now, give me the prophecy, Potter.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I want to know where Sirius is!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i I want to know where Sirius is\i0 !\rdblquote  mimicked the woman to his left.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She and her fellow Death Eaters had closed in so that they were\lang3081  \lang1033 mere feet away from Harry and the others, the light from their wands dazzling Harry\rquote s eyes.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote ve got him,\rdblquote  said Harry, ignoring the rising panic in his chest, the dread he had been fighting since they had first entered the ninety-seventh row. \ldblquote He\rquote s here. I know he is.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i The little baby woke up fwightened and fort what it dweamed was twoo,\i0\rdblquote\lang3081  \lang1033 said the woman in a horrible, mock-baby voice. Harry felt Ron stir beside him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Don\rquote t do anything,\rdblquote  he muttered. \ldblquote Not yet \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The woman who had mimicked him let out a raucous scream of laughter.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You hear him? \i You hear him\i0 ? Giving instructions to the other chil\-dren as though he thinks of fighting us!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, you don\rquote t know Potter as I do, Bellatrix,\rdblquote  said Malfoy softly. \ldblquote He has a great weakness for heroics; the Dark Lord understands this about him. \i Now give me the prophecy, Potter.\i0\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I know Sirius is here,\rdblquote  said Harry, though panic was causing his chest to constrict and he felt as though he could not breathe properly. \ldblquote\i I know you\rquote ve got him\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 More of the Death Eaters laughed, though the woman still laughed loudest of all.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It\rquote s time you learned the difference between life and dreams, Pot\-ter,\rdblquote  said Malfoy. \ldblquote Now give me the prophecy, or we start using wands.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Go on, then,\rdblquote  said Harry, raising his own wand to chest height. As he did so, the five wands of Ron, Hermione, Neville, Ginny, and Luna rose on either side of him. The knot in Harry\rquote s stomach tightened. If Sirius really was not here, he had led his friends to their deaths for no reason at all. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But the Death Eaters did not strike.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Hand over the prophecy and no one need get hurt,\rdblquote  said Malfoy coolly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 It was Harry\rquote s turn to laugh.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, right!\rdblquote  he said. \ldblquote I give you this \emdash  prophecy, is it? And you\rquote ll just let us skip off home, will you?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The words were hardly out of his mouth when the female Death Eater shrieked, \ldblquote\i Accio Proph\lang3081\i0  \lang1033\emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry was just ready for her. He shouted \ldblquote\i Protego\i0 !\rdblquote  before she had finished her spell, and though the glass sphere slipped to the tips of his fingers he managed to cling on to it.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Oh, he knows how to play, little bitty baby Potter,\rdblquote  she said, her mad eyes staring through the slits in her hood. \ldblquote Very well, then \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I TOLD YOU, NO!\rdblquote  Lucius Malfoy roared at the woman. \ldblquote If you smash it \emdash  !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry\rquote s mind was racing. The Death Eaters wanted this dusty spun-glass sphere. He had no interest in it. He just wanted to get them all out of this alive, make sure that none of his friends paid a ter\-rible price for his stupidity \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The woman stepped forward, away from her fellows, and pulled off her hood. Azkaban had hollowed Bellatrix Lestrange\rquote s face, making it gaunt and skull-like, but it was alive with a feverish, fanatical glow.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You need more persuasion?\rdblquote  she said, her chest rising and falling rapidly. \ldblquote Very well \emdash  take the smallest one,\rdblquote  she ordered the Death Eaters beside her. \ldblquote Let him watch while we torture the little girl. I\rquote ll do it.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry felt the others close in around Ginny. He stepped sideways so that he was right in front of her, the prophecy held up to his chest.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote ll have to smash this if you want to attack any of us,\rdblquote  he told Bellatrix. \ldblquote I don\rquote t think your boss will be too pleased if you come back without it, will he?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She did not move; she merely stared at him, the tip of her tongue moistening her thin mouth.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So,\rdblquote  said Harry, \ldblquote what kind of prophecy are we talking about anyway?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He could not think what to do but to keep talking. Neville\rquote s arm was pressed against his, and he could feel him shaking. He could feel one of the other\rquote s quickened breath on the back of his head. He was hoping they were all thinking hard about ways to get out of this, be\-cause his mind was blank.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What kind of prophecy?\rdblquote  repeated Bellatrix, the grin fading from her face. \ldblquote You jest, Harry Potter.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Nope, not jesting,\rdblquote  said Harry, his eyes flicking from Death Eater to Death Eater, looking for a weak link, a space through which they could escape. \ldblquote How come Voldemort wants it?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Several of the Death Eaters let out low hisses.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You dare speak his name?\rdblquote  whispered Bellatrix.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah,\rdblquote  said Harry, maintaining his tight grip on the glass ball, ex\-pecting another attempt to bewitch it from him. \ldblquote Yeah, I\rquote ve got no problem saying Vol \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Shut your mouth!\rdblquote  Bellatrix shrieked. \ldblquote You dare speak his name with your unworthy lips, you dare besmirch it with your half-blood\rquote s tongue, you dare \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Did you know he\rquote s a half-blood too?\rdblquote  said Harry recklessly. Hermione gave a little moan in his ear. \ldblquote Voldemort? Yeah, his mother was a witch but his dad was a Muggle \emdash  or has he been telling you lot he\rquote s pureblood?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i STUPEF\lang3081\i0  \lang1033\emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i NO\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 A jet of red light had shot from the end of Bellatrix Lestrange\rquote s wand, but Malfoy had deflected it. His spell caused hers to hit the shelf a foot to the left of Harry and several of the glass orbs there shattered.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Two figures, pearly white as ghosts, fluid as smoke, unfurled them\-selves from the fragments of broken glass upon the floor and each began to speak. Their voices vied with each other, so that only fragments\lang3081  \lang1033 of what they were saying could be heard over Malfoy and Bellatrix\rquote s shouts.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\'85 \i at the Solstice will come a new\i0  \'85\rdblquote  said the figure of an old, bearded man.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote DO NOT ATTACK! WE NEED THE PROPHECY!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He dared \emdash  he dares \emdash\rdblquote  shrieked Bellatrix incoherently. \ldblquote\emdash  He stands there \emdash  filthy half-blood \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote WAIT UNTIL WE\rquote VE GOT THE PROPHECY!\rdblquote  bawled Malfoy.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\'85 \i and none will come after\lang3081\i0  \lang1033\'85\rdblquote  said the figure of\lang3081  \lang1033 a young woman.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The two figures that had burst from the shattered spheres had melted into thin air. Nothing remained of them or their erstwhile homes but fragments of glass upon the floor. They had, however, given Harry an idea. The problem was going to be conveying it to the others.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You haven\rquote t told me what\rquote s so special about this prophecy I\rquote m sup\-posed to be handing over,\rdblquote  he said, playing for time. He moved his foot slowly sideways, feeling around for someone else\rquote s.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Do not play games with us, Potter,\rdblquote  said Malfoy.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I\rquote m not playing games,\rdblquote  said Harry, half his mind on the conver\-sation, half on his wandering foot. And then he found someone\rquote s toes and pressed down upon them. A sharp intake of breath behind him told him they were Hermione\rquote s.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What?\rdblquote  she whispered.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Dumbledore never told you that the reason you bear that scar was hidden in the bowels of the Department of Mysteries?\rdblquote  said Malfoy sneeringly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I \emdash  what?\rdblquote  said Harry, and for a moment he quite forgot his plan. \ldblquote What about my scar?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i What\i0 ?\rdblquote\lang3081  \lang1033 whispered Hermione more urgently behind him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Can this be?\rdblquote  said Malfoy, sounding maliciously delighted; some of the Death Eaters were laughing again, and under cover of their\lang3081  \lang1033 laughter, Harry hissed to Hermione, moving his lips as little as possi\-ble, \ldblquote Smash shelves \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Dumbledore never told you?\rdblquote  Malfoy repeated. \ldblquote Well, this ex\-plains why you didn\rquote t come earlier, Potter, the Dark Lord wondered why \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\emdash  when I say go \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\emdash  you didn\rquote t come running when he showed you the place where it was hidden in your dreams. He thought natural curiosity would make you want to hear the exact wording. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Did he?\rdblquote  said Harry. Behind him he felt rather than heard Hermione passing his message to the others and he sought to keep talking, to distract the Death Eaters. \ldblquote So he wanted me to come and get it, did he? Why?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Why\i0 ?\rdblquote  Malfoy sounded incredulously delighted. \ldblquote Because the only people who are permitted to retrieve a prophecy from the De\-partment of Mysteries, Potter, are those about whom it was made, as the Dark Lord discovered when he attempted to use others to steal it for him.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote And why did he want to steal a prophecy about me?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote About both of you, Potter, about both of you \'85 Haven\rquote t you ever wondered why the Dark Lord tried to kill you as a baby?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry stared into the slitted eyeholes through which Malfoy\rquote s gray eyes were gleaming. Was this prophecy the reason Harry\rquote s parents had died, the reason he carried his lightning-bolt scar? Was the answer to all of this clutched in his hand?\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Someone made a prophecy about Voldemort and me?\rdblquote  he said quietly, gazing at Lucius Malfoy, his fingers tightening over the warm glass sphere in his hand. It was hardly larger than a Snitch and still gritty with dust. \ldblquote And he\rquote s made me come and get it for him? Why couldn\rquote t he come and get it himself?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Get it himself?\rdblquote  shrieked Bellatrix on a cackle of mad laughter.\lang3081  \lang1033\ldblquote The Dark Lord, walk into the Ministry of Magic, when they are so sweetly ignoring his return? The Dark Lord, reveal himself to the Au\-rors, when at the moment they are wasting their time on my dear cousin?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So he\rquote s got you doing his dirty work for him, has he?\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote Like he tried to get Sturgis to steal it \emdash  and Bode?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Very good, Potter, very good \'85\rdblquote  said Malfoy slowly. \ldblquote But the Dark Lord knows you are not unintell \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote NOW!\rdblquote  yelled Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Five different voices behind him bellowed \ldblquote\i REDUCTO\i0 !\rdblquote  Five curses flew in five different directions and the shelves opposite them exploded as they hit. The towering structure swayed as a hundred glass spheres burst apart, pearly-white figures unfurled into the air and floated there, their voices echoing from who knew what long-dead past amid the torrent of crashing glass and splintered wood now rain\-ing down upon the floor \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote RUN!\rdblquote  Harry yelled, and as the shelves swayed precariously and more glass spheres began to pour from above, he seized a handful of Hermione\rquote s robes and dragged her forward, one arm over his head as chunks of shelf and shards of glass thundered down upon them. A Death Eater lunged forward through the cloud of dust and Harry el\-bowed him hard in the masked face. They were all yelling, there were cries of pain, thunderous crashes as the shelves collapsed upon them\-selves, weirdly echoing fragments of the Seers unleashed from their spheres \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry found the way ahead clear and saw Ron, Ginny, and Luna sprint past him, their arms over their heads. Something heavy struck him on the side of the face but he merely ducked his head and sprinted onward; a hand caught him by the shoulder; he heard Her\-mione shout \ldblquote\i Stupefy\i0 !\rdblquote  and the hand released him at once.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They were at the end of row ninety-seven; Harry turned right and\lang3081  \lang1033 began to sprint in earnest. He could hear footsteps right behind him and Hermione\rquote s voice urging Neville on. The door through which they had come was ajar straight ahead, Harry could see the glittering light of the bell jar, he pelted through it, the prophecy still clutched tight and safe in his hand, waited for the others to hurtle over the threshold before slamming the door behind them \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Colloportus\i0 !\rdblquote  gasped Hermione and the door sealed itself with an odd squelching noise.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Where \emdash  where are the others?\rdblquote  gasped Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He had thought that Ron, Luna, and Ginny had been ahead of them, that they would be waiting in this room, but there was nobody there.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote They must have gone the wrong way!\rdblquote  whispered Hermione, ter\-ror in her face.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Listen!\rdblquote  whispered Neville.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Footsteps and shouts echoed from behind the door they had just sealed. Harry put his ear close to the door to listen and heard Lucius Malfoy roar: \ldblquote Leave Nott, \i leave him, I say,\i0  the Dark Lord will not care for Nott\rquote s injuries as much as losing that prophecy \emdash  Jugson, come back here, we need to organize! We\rquote ll split into pairs and search, and don\rquote t forget, be gentle with Potter until we\rquote ve got the prophecy, you can kill the others if necessary \emdash  Bellatrix, Rodolphus, you take the left, Crabbe, Rabastan, go right \emdash  Jugson, Dolohov, the door straight ahead \emdash  Macnair and Avery, through here \emdash  Rookwood, over there \emdash  Mulciber, come with me!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What do we do?\rdblquote  Hermione asked Harry, trembling from head to foot.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, we don\rquote t stand here waiting for them to find us, for a start,\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote Let\rquote s get away from this door. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They ran, quietly as they could, past the shimmering bell jar where the tiny egg was hatching and unhatching, toward the exit into the\lang3081  \lang1033 circular hallway at the far end of the room. They were almost there when Harry heard something large and heavy collide with the door Hermione had charmed shut.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Stand aside!\rdblquote  said a rough voice. \ldblquote\i Alohomora\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 As the door flew open, Harry, Hermione, and Neville dived under desks. They could see the bottom of the two Death Eaters\rquote  robes drawing nearer, their feet moving rapidly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote They might\rquote ve run straight through to the hall,\rdblquote  said the rough voice.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Check under the desks,\rdblquote  said another.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry saw the knees of the Death Eaters bend. Poking his wand out from under the desk he shouted, \ldblquote\i STUPEFY\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 A jet of red light hit the nearest Death Eater; he fell backward into a grandfather clock and knocked it over. The second Death Eater, however, had leapt aside to avoid Harry\rquote s spell and now pointed his own wand at Hermione, who had crawled out from under the desk to get a better aim.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Avada \i0\emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry launched himself across the floor and grabbed the Death Eater around the knees, causing him to topple and his aim to go awry. Neville overturned his desk in his anxiety to help; pointing his wand wildly at the struggling pair he cried, \ldblquote\i EXPELLIARMUS\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Both Harry\rquote s and the Death Eater\rquote s wands flew out of their hands and soared back toward the entrance to the Hall of Prophecy; both scrambled to their feet and charged after them, the Death Eater in front and Harry hot on his heels, Neville bringing up the rear, plainly horrorstruck at what he had done.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Get out of the way, Harry!\rdblquote  yelled Neville, clearly determined to repair the damage.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry flung himself sideways as Neville took aim again and shouted, \ldblquote\i STUPEFY\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The jet of red light flew right over the Death Eater\rquote s shoulder and hit a glass-fronted cabinet on the wall full of variously shaped hour\-glasses. The cabinet fell to the floor and burst apart, glass flying every\-where, then sprang back up onto the wall, fully mended, then fell down again, and shattered \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The Death Eater had snatched up his wand, which lay on the floor beside the glittering bell jar. Harry ducked down behind another desk as the man turned \emdash  his mask had slipped so that he could not see, he ripped it off with his free hand and shouted, \ldblquote\i STUP\lang3081  \lang1033\i0\emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i STUPEFY\i0 !\rdblquote  screamed Hermione, who had just caught up with them. The jet of red light hit the Death Eater in the middle of his chest; he froze, his arm still raised, his wand fell to the floor with a clatter and he collapsed backward toward the bell jar. Harry expected to hear a \i clunk,\i0  for the man to hit solid glass and slide off the jar onto the floor, but instead, his head sank through the surface of the bell jar as though it was nothing but a soap bubble and he came to rest, sprawled on his back on the table, with his head lying inside the jar full of glittering wind.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Accio Wand\i0 !\rdblquote  cried Hermione. Harry\rquote s wand flew from a dark cor\-ner into her hand and she threw it to him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Thanks,\rdblquote  he said, \ldblquote right, let\rquote s get out of\lang3081  \lang1033\emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Look out!\rdblquote  said Neville, horrified, staring at the Death Eater\rquote s head in the bell jar.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 All three of them raised their wands again, but none of them struck. They were all gazing, openmouthed, appalled, at what was happening to the man\rquote s head.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 It was shrinking very fast, growing balder and balder, the black hair and stubble retracting into his skull, his cheeks smooth, his skull round and covered with a peachlike fuzz. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 A baby\rquote s head now sat grotesquely on top of the thick, muscled neck of the Death Eater as he struggled to get up again. But even as they watched, their mouths open, the head began to swell to its previ\-ous proportions again, thick black hair was sprouting from the pate and chin. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It\rquote s time,\rdblquote  said Hermione in an awestruck voice. \ldblquote\i Time\lang3081\i0  \lang1033\'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The Death Eater shook his ugly head again, trying to clear it, but before he could pull himself together again, it began to shrink back to babyhood once more. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was a shout from a room nearby, then a crash and a scream.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote RON?\rdblquote  Harry yelled, turning quickly from the monstrous trans\-formation taking place before them. \ldblquote GINNY? LUNA?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry!\rdblquote  Hermione screamed.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The Death Eater had pulled his head out of the bell jar. His ap\-pearance was utterly bizarre, his tiny baby\rquote s head bawling loudly while his thick arms flailed dangerously in all directions, narrowly missing Harry, who ducked. Harry raised his wand but to his amazement Hermione seized his arm.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You can\rquote t hurt a baby!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was no time to argue the point. Harry could hear more foot\-steps growing louder from the Hall of Prophecy they had just left and knew, too late, that he ought not to have shouted and given away their position.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Come on!\rdblquote  he said again, and leaving the ugly baby-headed Death Eater staggering behind them, they took off for the door that stood ajar at the other end of the room, leading back into the black hallway.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They had run halfway toward it when Harry saw through the open door two more Death Eaters running across the black room toward them. Veering left he burst instead into a small, dark, cluttered office and slammed the door behind them.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Collo\i0  \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081  \lang1033 began Hermione, but before she could complete the spell the door had burst open again and the two Death Eaters had come hurtling inside. With a cry of triumph, both yelled, \ldblquote\i IMPEDIMENTA\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry, Hermione, and Neville were all knocked backward off their feet. Neville was thrown over the desk and disappeared from view,\lang3081  \lang1033 Hermione smashed into a bookcase and was promptly deluged in a cascade of heavy books; the back of Harry\rquote s head slammed into the stone wall behind him, tiny lights burst in front of his eyes, and for a moment he was too dizzy and bewildered to react.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote WE\rquote VE GOT HIM!\rdblquote  yelled the Death Eater nearest Harry, \ldblquote IN AN OFFICE OFF \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Silencio\i0 !\rdblquote  cried Hermione, and the man\rquote s voice was extinguished. He continued to mouth through the hole in his mask, but no sound came out; he was thrust aside by his fellow.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Petrificus Totalus\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081  \lang1033 shouted Harry, as the second Death Eater raised his wand. His arms and legs snapped together and he fell forward, facedown onto the rug at Harry\rquote s feet, stiff as a board and unable to move at all.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well done, Ha\lang3081  \lang1033\emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But the Death Eater Hermione had just struck dumb made a sud\-den slashing movement with his wand from which flew a streak of what looked like purple flame. It passed right across Hermione\rquote s chest; she gave a tiny \ldblquote oh!\rdblquote  as though of surprise and then crumpled onto the floor where she lay motionless.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote HERMIONE!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry fell to his knees beside her as Neville crawled rapidly toward her from under the desk, his wand held up in front of him. The Death Eater kicked out hard at Neville\rquote s head as he emerged \emdash  his foot broke Neville\rquote s wand in two and connected with his face \emdash  Neville gave a howl of pain and recoiled, clutching his mouth and nose. Harry twisted around, his own wand held high, and saw that the Death Eater had ripped off his mask and was pointing his wand directly at Harry, who recognized the long, pale, twisted face from the \i Daily Prophet\i0 : Antonin Dolohov, the wizard who had murdered the Prewetts.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Dolohov grinned. With his free hand, he pointed from the prophecy still clutched in Harry\rquote s hand, to himself, then at Hermione.\lang3081  \lang1033 Though he could no longer speak his meaning could not have been clearer: \i Give me the prophecy, or you get the same as her. \'85\lang3081\i0\par
