\lang1033\ldblquote What?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote DUBBLEDORE!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry turned to look where Neville was staring. Directly above them, framed in the doorway from the Brain Room, stood Albus Dumbledore, his wand aloft, his face white and furious. Harry felt a kind of electric charge surge through every particle of his body \emdash  \i they were saved.\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033 Dumbledore sped down the steps past Neville and Harry, who had no more thought of leaving. Dumbledore was already at the foot of the steps when the Death Eaters nearest realized he was there. There were yells; one of the Death Eaters ran for it, scrabbling like a monkey up the stone steps opposite. Dumbledore\rquote s spell pulled him back as easily and effortlessly as though he had hooked him with an invisible line \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Only one couple were still battling, apparently unaware of the new arrival. Harry saw Sirius duck Bellatrix\rquote s jet of red light: He was laugh\-ing at her. \ldblquote Come on, you can do better than that!\rdblquote  he yelled, his voice echoing around the cavernous room.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The second jet of light hit him squarely on the chest.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The laughter had not quite died from his face, but his eyes widened in shock.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry released Neville, though he was unaware of doing so. He was jumping down the steps again, pulling out his wand, as Dumbledore turned to the dais too.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 It seemed to take Sirius an age to fall. His body curved in a grace\-ful arc as he sank backward through the ragged veil hanging from the arch. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And Harry saw the look of mingled fear and surprise on his god\-father\rquote s wasted, once-handsome face as he fell through the ancient doorway and disappeared behind the veil, which fluttered for a mo\-ment as though in a high wind and then fell back into place.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry heard Bellatrix Lestrange\rquote s triumphant scream, but knew it meant nothing \emdash  Sirius had only just fallen through the archway, he would reappear from the other side any second. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But Sirius did not reappear.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote SIRIUS!\rdblquote  Harry yelled, \ldblquote SIRIUS!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He had reached the floor, his breath coming in searing gasps. Sirius must be just behind the curtain, he, Harry, would pull him back out again. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But as he reached the ground and sprinted toward the dais, Lupin grabbed Harry around the chest, holding him back.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote There\rquote s nothing you can do, Harry \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Get him, save him, he\rquote s only just gone through!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
