He did not believe it, he would not believe it; still he fought Lupin with every bit of strength he had: Lupin did not under\-stand, people hid behind that curtain, he had heard them whispering the first time he had entered the room \emdash  Sirius was hiding, simply lurking out of sight \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote SIRIUS!\rdblquote  he bellowed, \ldblquote SIRIUS!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He can\rquote t come back, Harry,\rdblquote  said Lupin, his voice breaking as he struggled to contain Harry. \ldblquote He can\rquote t come back, because he\rquote s d \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote HE \emdash  IS \emdash  NOT \emdash  DEAD!\rdblquote  roared Harry. \ldblquote SIRIUS!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was movement going on around them, pointless bustling, the flashes of more spells. To Harry it was meaningless noise, the de\-flected curses flying past them did not matter, nothing mattered ex\-cept that Lupin stop pretending that Sirius, who was standing feet from them behind that old curtain, was not going to emerge at any moment, shaking back his dark hair and eager to reenter the battle \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Lupin dragged Harry away from the dais, Harry still staring at the archway, angry at Sirius now for keeping him waiting \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But some part of him realized, even as he fought to break free from Lupin, that Sirius had never kept him waiting before. \'85 Sirius had risked everything, always, to see Harry, to help him. \'85 If Sirius was not reappearing out of that archway when Harry was yelling for him as though his life depended on it, the only possible explanation was that he could not come back. \'85 That he really was \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Dumbledore had most of the remaining Death Eaters grouped in the middle of the room, seemingly immobilized by invisible ropes. Mad-Eye Moody had crawled across the room to where Tonks lay and was attempting to revive her. Behind the dais there were still flashes of light, grunts, and cries \emdash  Kingsley had run forward to continue Sir\-ius\rquote s duel with Bellatrix.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Neville had slid down the stone benches one by one to the place where Harry stood. Harry was no longer struggling against Lupin, who maintained a precautionary grip on his arm nevertheless.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 I\rquote b really sorry. \'85\rdblquote  said Neville. His legs were still dancing uncontrollably. \ldblquote Was dat man \emdash  was Sirius Black a \emdash  a friend of yours?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry nodded.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Here,\rdblquote  said Lupin quietly, and pointing his wand at Neville\rquote s legs he said, \ldblquote\i Finite.\i0\rdblquote  The spell was lifted. Neville\rquote s legs fell back onto the floor and remained still. Lupin\rquote s face was pale. \ldblquote Let\rquote s \emdash  let\rquote s find the others. Where are they all, Neville?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Lupin turned away from the archway as he spoke. It sounded as though every word was causing him pain.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Dey\rquote re all back dere,\rdblquote  said Neville. \ldblquote A brain addacked Ron bud I dink he\rquote s all righd \emdash  and Herbione\rquote s unconscious, bud we could feel a bulse \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was a loud bang and a yell from behind the dais. Harry saw Kingsley, yelling in pain, hit the ground. Bellatrix Lestrange turned\lang3081  \lang1033 tail and ran as Dumbledore whipped around. He aimed a spell at her but she deflected it. She was halfway up the steps now \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Harry \emdash  no!\rdblquote  cried Lupin, but Harry had already ripped his arm from Lupin\rquote s slackened grip.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote SHE KILLED SIRIUS!\rdblquote  bellowed Harry. \ldblquote SHE KILLED HIM \emdash  I\rquote LL KILL HER!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And he was off, scrambling up the stone benches. People were shouting behind him but he did not care. The hem of Bellatrix\rquote s robes whipped out of sight ahead and they were back in the room where the brains were swimming. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 She aimed a curse over her shoulder. The tank rose into the air and tipped. Harry was deluged in the foul-smelling potion within. The brains slipped and slid over him and began spinning their long, col\-ored tentacles, but he shouted, \ldblquote\i Wingardium Leviosa\i0 !\rdblquote  and they flew into the air away from him. Slipping and sliding he ran on toward the door. He leapt over Luna, who was groaning on the floor, past Ginny, who said, \ldblquote Harry \emdash  what \emdash  ?\rdblquote  past Ron, who giggled feebly, and Hermione, who was still unconscious. He wrenched open the door into the circular black hall and saw Bellatrix disappearing through a door on the other side of the room \emdash  beyond her was the corridor leading back to the lifts.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He ran, but she had slammed the door behind her and the walls had begun to rotate again. Once more he was surrounded by streaks of blue light from the whirling candelabra.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Where\rquote s the exit?\rdblquote  he shouted desperately, as the wall rumbled to a halt again. \ldblquote Where\rquote s the way out?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The room seemed to have been waiting for him to ask. The door right behind him flew open, and the corridor toward the lifts stretched ahead of him, torch-lit and empty. He ran. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He could hear a lift clattering ahead of him. He sprinted up the passageway, swung around the corner, and slammed his fist onto the\lang3081  \lang1033 button to call a second lift. It jangled and banged lower and lower; the grilles slid open and Harry dashed inside, now hammering the button marked Atrium. The doors slid shut and he was rising. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He forced his way out of the lift before the grilles were fully open and looked around. Bellatrix was almost at the telephone lift at the other end of the hall, but she looked back as he sprinted toward her, and aimed another spell at him. He dodged behind the Fountain of Magical Brethren; the spell zoomed past him and hit the wrought gold gates at the other end of the Atrium so that they rang like bells. There were no more footsteps. She had stopped running. He crouched be\-hind the statues, listening.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Come out, come out, little Harry\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081  \lang1033 she called in her mock-baby voice, which echoed off the polished wooden floors. \ldblquote What did you come af\-ter me for, then? I thought you were here to avenge my dear cousin!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I am!\rdblquote  shouted Harry, and a score of ghostly Harry\rquote s seemed to chorus \i I\lang3081  \lang1033 am\i0 !\lang3081  \lang1033\i I\lang3081  \lang1033 am\i0 !\lang3081  \lang1033\i I\lang3081  \lang1033 am\i0 !\lang3081  \lang1033 all around the room.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Aaaaaah \'85 did you \i love\i0  him, little baby Potter?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hatred rose in Harry such as he had never known before. He flung himself out from behind the fountain and bellowed \ldblquote\i Crucio\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Bellatrix screamed. The spell had knocked her off her feet, but she did not writhe and shriek with pain as Neville had \emdash  she was already on her feet again, breathless, no longer laughing. Harry dodged be\-hind the golden fountain again \emdash  her counterspell hit the head of the handsome wizard, which was blown off and landed twenty feet away, gouging long scratches into the wooden floor.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Never used an Unforgivable Curse before, have you, boy?\rdblquote  she yelled. She had abandoned her baby voice now. \ldblquote You need to \i mean\i0  them, Potter! You need to really want to cause pain \emdash  to enjoy it \emdash  righteous anger won\rquote t hurt me for long \emdash  I\rquote ll show you how it is done, shall I? I\rquote ll give you a lesson \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry had been edging around the fountain on the other side. She screamed, \ldblquote\i Crucio\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081  \lang1033 and he was forced to duck down again as the cen\-taur\rquote s arm, holding its bow, spun off and landed with a crash on the floor a short distance from the golden wizard\rquote s head.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Potter, you cannot win against me!\rdblquote  she cried. He could hear her moving to the right, trying to get a clear shot of him. He backed around the statue away from her, crouching behind the centaur\rquote s legs, his head level with the house-elf\rquote s. \ldblquote I was and am the Dark Lord\rquote s most loyal servant, I learned the Dark Arts from him, and I know spells of such power that you, pathetic little boy, can never hope to compete \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Stupefy\i0 !\rdblquote  yelled Harry. He had edged right around to where the goblin stood beaming up at the now headless wizard and taken aim at her back as she peered around the fountain for him. She reacted so fast he barely had time to duck.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Protego\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The jet of red light, his own Stunning Spell, bounced back at him. Harry scrambled back behind the fountain, and one of the goblin\rquote s ears went flying across the room.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Potter, I am going to give you one chance!\rdblquote  shouted Bellatrix. \ldblquote Give me the prophecy \emdash  roll it out toward me now \emdash  and I may spare your life!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, you\rquote re going to have to kill me, because it\rquote s gone!\rdblquote  Harry roared \emdash  and as he shouted it, pain seared across his forehead. His scar was on fire again, and he felt a surge of fury that was quite un\-connected with his own rage. \ldblquote And he knows!\rdblquote  said Harry with a mad laugh to match Bellatrix\rquote s own. \ldblquote Your dear old mate Voldemort knows it\rquote s gone! He\rquote s not going to be happy with you, is he?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What? What do you mean?\rdblquote  she cried, and for the first time there was fear in her voice.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The prophecy smashed when I was trying to get Neville up the steps! What do you think Voldemort\rquote ll say about that, then?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 His scar seared and burned. \'85 The pain of it was making his eyes stream. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote LIAR!\rdblquote  she shrieked, but he could hear the terror behind the anger now. \ldblquote YOU\rquote VE GOT IT, POTTER, AND YOU WILL GIVE IT TO ME \emdash  \i Accio Prophecy\i0 !\lang3081  \lang1033\i ACCIO PROPHECY\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry laughed again because he knew it would incense her, the pain building in his head so badly he thought his skull might burst. He waved his empty hand from behind the one-eared goblin and withdrew it quickly as she sent another jet of green light flying at him.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Nothing there!\rdblquote  he shouted. \ldblquote Nothing to summon! It smashed and nobody heard what it said, tell your boss that \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No!\rdblquote  she screamed. \ldblquote It isn\rquote t true, you\rquote re lying \emdash  MASTER, I TRIED, I TRIED \emdash  DO NOT PUNISH ME \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Don\rquote t waste your breath!\rdblquote  yelled Harry, his eyes screwed up against the pain in his scar, now more terrible than ever. \ldblquote He can\rquote t hear you from here!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Can\rquote t I, Potter?\rdblquote  said a high, cold voice.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry opened his eyes.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Tall, thin, and black-hooded, his terrible snakelike face white and gaunt, his scarlet, slit-pupiled eyes staring \'85 Lord Voldemort had appeared in the middle of the hall, his wand pointing at Harry who stood frozen, quite unable to move.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So you smashed my prophecy?\rdblquote  said Voldemort softly, staring at Harry with those pitiless red eyes. \ldblquote No, Bella, he is not lying. \'85 I see the truth looking at me from within his worthless mind. \'85 Months of preparation, months of effort\lang3081  \lang1033\'85 and my Death Eaters have let Harry Potter thwart me again. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Master, I am sorry, I knew not, I was fighting the Animagus Black!\rdblquote  sobbed Bellatrix, flinging herself down at Voldemort\rquote s feet as he paced slowly nearer. \ldblquote Master, you should know \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Be quiet, Bella,\rdblquote  said Voldemort dangerously. \ldblquote I shall deal with you in a moment. Do you think I have entered the Ministry of Magic to hear your sniveling apologies?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote But Master \emdash  he is here \emdash  he is below \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Voldemort paid no attention.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I have nothing more to say to you, Potter,\rdblquote  he said quietly. \ldblquote You have irked me too often, for too long. \i AVADA KEDAVRA\i0 !\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry had not even opened his mouth to resist. His mind was blank, his wand pointing uselessly at the floor.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But the headless golden statue of the wizard in the fountain had sprung alive, leaping from its plinth, and landed on the floor with a crash between Harry and Voldemort. The spell merely glanced off its chest as the statue flung out its arms, protecting Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What \emdash  ?\rdblquote  said Voldemort, staring around. And then he breathed, \ldblquote Dumbledore!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry looked behind him, his heart pounding. Dumbledore was standing in front of the golden gates.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Voldemort raised his wand and sent another jet of green light at Dumbledore, who turned and was gone in a whirling of his cloak; next second he had reappeared behind Voldemort and waved his wand toward the remnants of the fountain; the other statues sprang to life too. The statue of the witch ran at Bellatrix, who screamed and sent spells streaming uselessly off its chest, before it dived at her, pin\-ning her to the floor. Meanwhile, the goblin and the house-elf scuttled toward the fireplaces set along the wall, and the one-armed centaur galloped at Voldemort, who vanished and reappeared beside the pool. The headless statue thrust Harry backward, away from the fight, as Dumbledore advanced on Voldemort and the golden centaur can\-tered around them both.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote It was foolish to come here tonight, Tom,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore calmly. \ldblquote The Aurors are on their way \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote By which time I shall be gone, and you dead!\rdblquote  spat Voldemort. He sent another Killing Curse at Dumbledore but missed, instead hitting the security guards desk, which burst into flame.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Dumbledore flicked his own wand. The force of the spell that em\-anated from it was such that Harry, though shielded by his stone\lang3081  \lang1033 guard, felt his hair stand on end as it passed, and this time Voldemort was forced to conjure a shining silver shield out of thin air to deflect it. The spell, whatever it was, caused no visible damage to the shield, though a deep, gonglike note reverberated from it, an oddly chilling sound. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You do not seek to kill me, Dumbledore?\rdblquote  called Voldemort, his scarlet eyes narrowed over the top of the shield. \ldblquote Above such brutality, are you?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote We both know that there are other ways of destroying a man, Tom,\rdblquote  Dumbledore said calmly, continuing to walk toward Volde\-mort as though he had not a fear in the world, as though nothing had happened to interrupt his stroll up the hall. \ldblquote Merely taking your life would not satisfy me, I admit \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote There is nothing worse than death, Dumbledore!\rdblquote  snarled Voldemort.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You are quite wrong,\rdblquote  said Dumbledore, still closing in upon Voldemort and speaking as lightly as though they were discussing the matter over drinks. Harry felt scared to see him walking along, unde\-fended, shieldless. He wanted to cry out a warning, but his headless guard kept shunting him backward toward the wall, blocking his every attempt to get out from behind it. \ldblquote Indeed, your failure to un\-derstand that there are things much worse than death has always been your greatest weakness \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Another jet of green light flew from behind the silver shield. This time it was the one-armed centaur, galloping in front of Dumbledore, that took the blast and shattered into a hundred pieces, but before the fragments had even hit the floor, Dumbledore had drawn back his wand and waved it as though brandishing a whip. A long thin flame flew from the tip; it wrapped itself around Voldemort, shield and all. For a moment, it seemed Dumbledore had won, but then the fiery rope became a serpent, which relinquished its hold upon Voldemort at once and turned, hissing furiously, to face Dumbledore.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Voldemort vanished. The snake reared from the floor, ready to strike \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 There was a burst of flame in midair above Dumbledore just as Voldemort reappeared, standing on the plinth in the middle of the pool where so recently the five statues had stood.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Look out\i0 !\rdblquote  Harry yelled.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 But even as he shouted, one more jet of green light had flown at Dumbledore from Voldemort\rquote s wand and the snake had struck \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Fawkes swooped down in front of Dumbledore, opened his beak wide, and swallowed the jet of green light whole. He burst into flame and fell to the floor, small, wrinkled, and flightless. At the same mo\-ment, Dumbledore brandished his wand in one, long, fluid move\-ment \emdash  the snake, which had been an instant from sinking its fangs into him, flew high into the air and vanished in a wisp of dark smoke; the water in the pool rose up and covered Voldemort like a cocoon of molten glass \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 For a few seconds Voldemort was visible only as a dark, rippling, faceless figure, shimmering and indistinct upon the plinth, clearly struggling to throw off the suffocating mass \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Then he was gone, and the water fell with a crash back into its pool, slopping wildly over the sides, drenching the polished floor.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote MASTER!\rdblquote  screamed Bellatrix.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Sure it was over, sure Voldemort had decided to flee, Harry made to run out from behind his statue guard, but Dumbledore bellowed, \ldblquote Stay where you are, Harry!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 For the first time, Dumbledore sounded frightened. Harry could not see why. The hall was quite empty but for themselves, the sobbing Bellatrix still trapped under her statue, and the tiny baby Fawkes croaking feebly on the floor \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And then Harry\rquote s scar burst open. He knew he was dead: it was pain beyond imagining, pain past endurance \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He was gone from the hall, he was locked in the coils of a creature\lang3081  \lang1033 with red eyes, so tightly bound that Harry did not know where his body ended and the creature\rquote s began. They were fused together, bound by pain, and there was no escape \emdash\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And when the creature spoke, it used Harry\rquote s mouth, so that in his agony he felt his jaw move. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i Kill me now, Dumbledore. \'85\i0\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Blinded and dying, every part of him screaming for release, Harry felt the creature use him again. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote\i If death is nothing, Dumbledore, kill the boy. \'85\i0\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\i Let the pain stop,\i0  thought Harry. \i Let him kill us. \'85 End it, Dumb\-ledore. \'85 Death is nothing compared to this. \'85\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033\i And I\rquote ll see Sirius again. \'85\lang3081\i0\par
\lang1033 And as Harry\rquote s heart filled with emotion, the creature\rquote s coils loos\-ened, the pain was gone, Harry was lying facedown on the floor, his glasses gone, shivering as though he lay upon ice, not wood. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 And there were voices echoing through the hall, more voices than there should have been: Harry opened his eyes, saw his glasses lying at the heel of the headless statue that had been guarding him, but which now lay flat on its back, cracked and immobile. He put them on and raised his head an inch to find Dumbledore\rquote s crooked nose inches from his own.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Are you all right, Harry?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes,\rdblquote  said Harry, shaking so violently he could not hold his head up properly. \ldblquote Yeah, I\rquote m \emdash  where\rquote s Voldemort, where \emdash  who are all these \emdash  what\rquote s \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
