\lang1033 She winced slightly and put a hand to her ribs. The curse Dolohov had used on her, though less effective than it would have been had he been able to say the incantation aloud, had nevertheless caused, in Madam Pomfrey\rquote s words, \ldblquote quite enough damage to be going on with.\rdblquote  Hermione was having to take ten different types of potion every day and although she was improving greatly, was already bored with the hospital wing.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote  \lquote\i You-Know-Who\rquote s Last Attempt to Take Over, pages two to four, What the Ministry Should Have Told Us, page five, Why Nobody Listened to Al\-bus Dumbledore, pages six to eight, Exclusive Interview with Harry Pot\-ter, page nine\lang3081  \lang1033\i0\'85\rquote\i  \i0 Well,\rdblquote  said Hermione, folding up the newspaper and throwing it aside, \ldblquote it\rquote s certainly given them lots to write about. And that interview with Harry isn\rquote t exclusive, it\rquote s the one that was in \i The Quibbler\i0  months ago. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Daddy sold it to them,\rdblquote  said Luna vaguely, turning a page of \i The Quibbler.\i0  \ldblquote He got a very good price for it too, so we\rquote re going to go on an expedition to Sweden this summer and see if we can catch a Crumple-Horned Snorkack.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione seemed to struggle with herself for a moment, then said, \ldblquote That sounds lovely.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Ginny caught Harry\rquote s eye and looked away quickly, grinning.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So anyway,\rdblquote  said Hermione, sitting up a little straighter and winc\-ing again, \ldblquote what\rquote s going on in school?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, Flitwick\rquote s got rid of Fred and George\rquote s swamp,\rdblquote  said Ginny. \ldblquote He did it in about three seconds. But he left a tiny patch under the window and he\rquote s roped it off\lang3081  \lang1033\emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
