\lang1033\ldblquote I think he left it as a monument to Fred and George,\rdblquote  said Ron through a mouthful of chocolate. \ldblquote They sent me all these, you know,\rdblquote  he told Harry, pointing at the small mountain of Frogs beside him. \ldblquote Must be doing all right out of that joke shop, eh?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione looked rather disapproving and asked, \ldblquote So has all the trouble stopped now Dumbledore\rquote s back?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yes,\rdblquote  said Neville, \ldblquote everything\rquote s settled right back down again.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I s\rquote pose Filch is happy, is he?\rdblquote  asked Ron, propping a Chocolate Frog card featuring Dumbledore against his water jug.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Not at all,\rdblquote  said Ginny. \ldblquote He\rquote s really, really miserable, actually. \'85\rdblquote  She lowered her voice to a whisper. \ldblquote He keeps saying Umbridge was the best thing that ever happened to Hogwarts. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 All six of them looked around. Professor Umbridge was lying in a bed opposite them, gazing up at the ceiling. Dumbledore had strode alone into the forest to rescue her from the centaurs. How he had done it \emdash  how he had emerged from the trees supporting Professor Umbridge without so much as a scratch on him \emdash  nobody knew, and\lang3081  \lang1033 Umbridge was certainly not telling. Since she had returned to the cas\-tle she had not, as far as any of them knew, uttered a single word. No\-body really knew what was wrong with her either. Her usually neat mousy hair was very untidy and there were bits of twig and leaf in it, but otherwise she seemed to be quite unscathed.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Madam Pomfrey says she\rquote s just in shock,\rdblquote  whispered Hermione.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Sulking, more like,\rdblquote  said Ginny\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, she shows signs of life if you do this,\rdblquote  said Ron, and with his tongue he made soft clip-clopping noises. Umbridge sat bolt upright, looking wildly around.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Anything wrong, Professor?\rdblquote  called Madam Pomfrey, poking her head around her office door.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote No \'85 no \'85\rdblquote  said Umbridge, sinking back into her pillows, \ldblquote no, I must have been dreaming. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Hermione and Ginny muffled their laughter in the bedclothes.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Speaking of centaurs,\rdblquote  said Hermione, when she had recovered a little, \ldblquote who\rquote s Divination teacher now? Is Firenze staying?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote He\rquote s got to,\rdblquote  said Harry, \ldblquote the other centaurs won\rquote t take him back, will they?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
