\lang1033 Harry gave a wave of his hand to show he had heard and under\-stood as he left the dormitory.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The castle seemed very quiet even for a Sunday. Everybody was clearly out in the sunny grounds, enjoying the end of their exams and the prospect of a last few days of term unhampered by studying or homework. Harry walked slowly along the deserted corridor, peering out of windows as he went. He could see people messing around in the air over the Quidditch pitch and a couple of students swimming in the lake, accompanied by the giant squid.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He was finding it hard at the moment to decide whether he wanted to be with people or not. Whenever he was in company he wanted to get away, and whenever he was alone he wanted company. He thought he might really go and visit Hagrid, though; he had not talked to him properly since he had returned. \'85\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry had just descended the last marble step into the entrance hall when Malfoy, Crabbe, and Goyle emerged from a door on the right that Harry knew led down to the Slytherin common room. Harry stopped dead; so did Malfoy and the others. For a few moments, the only sounds were the shouts, laughter, and splashes drifting into the hall from the grounds through the open front doors.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Malfoy glanced around. Harry knew he was checking for signs of teachers. Then he looked back at Harry and said in a low voice, \ldblquote You\rquote re dead, Potter.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry raised his eyebrows. \ldblquote Funny,\rdblquote  he said, \ldblquote you\rquote d think I\rquote d have stopped walking around. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Malfoy looked angrier than Harry had ever seen him. He felt a kind of detached satisfaction at the sight of his pale, pointed face contorted with rage.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You\rquote re going to pay,\rdblquote  said Malfoy in a voice barely louder than a whisper. \ldblquote\i I\rquote m\i0  going to make you pay for what you\rquote ve done to my father. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, I\rquote m terrified now,\rdblquote  said Harry sarcastically. \ldblquote I s\rquote pose Lord Voldemort\rquote s just a warm-up act compared to you three \emdash  what\rquote s the matter?\rdblquote  he said, for Malfoy, Crabbe, and Goyle had all looked stricken at the sound of the name. \ldblquote He\rquote s your dad\rquote s mate, isn\rquote t he? Not scared of him, are you?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote You think you\rquote re such a big man, Potter,\rdblquote  said Malfoy, advancing now, Crabbe and Goyle flanking him. \ldblquote You wait. I\rquote ll have you. You can\rquote t land my father in prison \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote I thought I just had,\rdblquote  said Harry.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote The dementors have left Azkaban,\rdblquote  said Malfoy quietly. \ldblquote Dad and the others\rquote ll be out in no time. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Yeah, I expect they will,\rdblquote  said Harry. \ldblquote Still, at least everyone knows what scumbags they are now \emdash\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Malfoy\rquote s hand flew toward his wand, but Harry was too quick for him. He had drawn his own wand before Malfoy\rquote s fingers had even entered the pocket of his robes.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Potter!\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The voice rang across the entrance hall; Snape had emerged from the staircase leading down to his office, and at the sight of him Harry felt a great rush of hatred beyond anything he felt toward Malfoy. \'85 What\-ever Dumbledore said, he would never forgive Snape \'85 never \'85\lang3081\par
