\lang1033\ldblquote Here,\rdblquote  said Professor McGonagall, thrusting her carpetbag into Crabbe\rquote s chest and her cloak into Goyle\rquote s, \ldblquote take these up to my office for me.\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 They turned and stumped away up the marble staircase.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Right then,\rdblquote  said Professor McGonagall, looking up at the hour\-glasses on the wall, \ldblquote well, I think Potter and his friends ought to have fifty points apiece for alerting the world to the return of You-Know-Who! What say you, Professor Snape?\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote What?\rdblquote  snapped Snape, though Harry knew he had heard per\-fectly well. \ldblquote Oh \emdash  well \emdash  I suppose \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote So that\rquote s fifty each for Potter, the two Weasleys, Longbottom, and Miss Granger,\rdblquote  said Professor McGonagall, and a shower of rubies fell down into the bottom bulb of Gryffindor\rquote s hourglass as she spoke. \ldblquote Oh \emdash  and fifty for Miss Lovegood, I suppose,\rdblquote  she added, and a number of sapphires fell into Ravenclaw\rquote s glass. \ldblquote Now, you wanted to take ten from Mr. Potter, I think, Professor Snape \emdash  so there we\lang3081  \lang1033 are. \'85\rdblquote\lang3081\par
\lang1033 A few rubies retreated into the upper bulb, leaving a respectable amount below nevertheless.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote Well, Potter, Malfoy, I think you ought to be outside on a glorious day like this,\rdblquote  Professor McGonagall continued briskly.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Harry did not need telling twice. He thrust his wand back inside his robes and headed straight for the front doors without another glance at Snape and Malfoy.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 The hot sun hit him with a blast as he walked across the lawns toward Hagrid\rquote s cabin. Students lying around on the grass sun\-bathing, talking, reading the \i Sunday Prophet,\i0  and eating sweets looked up at him as he passed. Some called out to him, or else waved, clearly eager to show that they, like the \i Prophet,\i0  had decided he was something of a hero. Harry said nothing to any of them. He had no idea how much they knew of what had happened three days ago, but he had so far avoided being questioned and preferred it that way.\lang3081\par
\lang1033 He thought at first when he knocked on Hagrid\rquote s cabin door that he was out, but then Fang came charging around the corner and al\-most bowled him over with the enthusiasm of his welcome. Hagrid, it transpired, was picking runner beans in his back garden.\lang3081\par
\lang1033\ldblquote All righ\rquote , Harry!\rdblquote  he said, beaming, when Harry approached the fence. \ldblquote Come in, come in, we\rquote ll have a cup o\rquote  dandelion juice. \'85\lang3081\par
